13   LESSON 18.
14   
15   I am not alone in experiencing the effects of my seeing.
16   W-pI.18.1. The idea for today is another step in learning that the thoughts which give 
17   rise to what you see are never neutral or unimportant. 2 It also emphasizes the idea that 
18   minds are joined, which will be given increasing stress later on.
19   W-pI.18.2. Today's idea does not refer to what you see as much as to how you see it. 2 
20   Therefore, the exercises for today emphasize this aspect of your perception. 3 The three or four
21   practice periods which are recommended should be done as follows:
22   W-pI.18.3. Look about you, selecting subjects for the application of the idea for today
23   as randomly as possible, and keeping your eyes on each one long enough to say: 
24   
25   2 I am not alone in experiencing the effects of how I see ___. 
26   
27   3 Conclude each practice period by repeating the more general statement: 
28   
29   4 I am not alone in experiencing the effects of my seeing. 
30   
31   5 A minute or so, or even less, will be sufficient for each practice period.
