35   LESSON 19.
36   
37   I am not alone in experiencing the effects of my thoughts.
38   W-pI.19.1. The idea for today is obviously the reason why your seeing does not affect 
39   you alone. 2 You will notice that at times the ideas related to thinking precede those 
40   related to perceiving, while at other times the order is reversed. 3 The reason is that the 
41   order does not matter. 4 Thinking and its results are really simultaneous, for cause and 
42   effect are never separate.
43   W-pI.19.2. Today we are again emphasizing the fact that minds are joined. 2 This is 
44   rarely a wholly welcome idea at first, since it seems to carry with it an enormous sense of 
45   responsibility, and may even be regarded as an "invasion of privacy." 3 Yet it is a fact that there 
46   are no private thoughts. 4 Despite your initial resistance to this idea, you will yet 
47   understand that it must be true if salvation is possible at all. 5 And salvation must be possible
48   because it is the Will of God.
49   W-pI.19.3. The minute or so of mind searching which today's exercises require is to be 
50   undertaken with eyes closed. 2 The idea for today is to be repeated first, and then the mind 
0421
 1   should be carefully searched for the thoughts it contains at that time. 3 As you consider 
 2   each one, name it in terms of the central person or theme it contains, and holding it in 
 3   your mind as you do so, say: 
 4   
 5   4 I am not alone in experiencing the effects of this thought about ___.
 6   
 7   W-pI.19.4. The requirement of as much indiscriminateness as possible in selecting 
 8   subjects for the practice periods should be quite familiar to you by now, and will no longer be
 9   repeated each day, although it will occasionally be included as a reminder. 2 Do not 
10   forget, however, that random selection of subjects for all practice periods remains essential
11   throughout. 3 Lack of order in this connection will ultimately make the recognition of 
12   lack of order in miracles meaningful to you.
13   W-pI.19.5. Apart from the "as needed" application of today's idea, at least three 
14   practice periods are required, shortening the length of time involved, if necessary. 2 Do not 
15   attempt more than four.
