19   LESSON 20.
20   
21   I am determined to see.
22   W-pI.20.1. We have been quite casual about our practice periods thus far. 2 There has 
23   been virtually no attempt to direct the time for undertaking them, minimal effort has been 
24   required, and not even active cooperation and interest have been asked. 3 This approach has 
25   been intentional, and very carefully planned. 4 We have not lost sight of the crucial 
26   importance of the reversal of your thinking. 5 The salvation of the world depends on it. 6 Yet 
27   you will not see if you regard yourself as being coerced, and if you give in to resentment
28   and opposition.
29   W-pI.20.2. This is our first attempt to introduce structure. 2 Do not misconstrue it as
30   an effort to exert force or pressure. 3 You want salvation. 4 You want to be happy. 5 
31   You want peace. 6 You do not have them now, because your mind is totally undisciplined, 
32   and you cannot distinguish between joy and sorrow, pleasure and pain, love and fear. 7 You
33   are now learning how to tell them apart. 8 And great indeed will be your reward.
34   W-pI.20.3. Your decision to see is all that vision requires. 2 What you want is yours. 
35   3 Do not mistake the little effort that is asked of you for an indication that our goal 
36   is of little worth. 4 Can the salvation of the world be a trivial purpose? 5 And can the 
37   world be saved if you are not? 6 God has one Son, and he is the resurrection and the life. 7
38   His will is done because all power is given him in Heaven and on earth. 8 In your 
39   determination to see is vision given you.
40   W-pI.20.4. The exercises for today consist in reminding yourself throughout the day 
41   that you want to see. 2 Today's idea also tacitly implies the recognition that you do not 
42   see now. 3 Therefore, as you repeat the idea, you are stating that you are determined to 
43   change your present state for a better one, and one you really want.
44   W-pI.20.5. Repeat today's idea slowly and positively at least twice an hour today, 
45   attempting to do so every half hour. 2 Do not be distressed if you forget to do so, but make a 
46   real effort to remember. 3 The extra repetitions should be applied to any situation, person
47   or event that upsets you. 4 You can see them differently, and you will. 5 What you 
48   desire you will see. 6 Such is the real law of cause and effect as it operates in the world.
49   
