0422
 1   
 2   LESSON 21.
 3   
 4   I am determined to see things differently.
 5   W-pI.21.1. The idea for today is obviously a continuation and extension of the 
 6   preceding one. 2 This time, however, specific mind-searching periods are necessary, in addition 
 7   to applying the idea to particular situations as they may arise. 3 Five practice periods 
 8   are urged, allowing a full minute for each.
 9   W-pI.21.2. In the practice periods, begin by repeating the idea to yourself. 2 Then 
10   close your eyes and search your mind carefully for situations past, present or anticipated 
11   that arouse anger in you. 3 The anger may take the form of any reaction ranging from mild 
12   irritation to rage. 4 The degree of the emotion you experience does not matter. 5 You will become
13   increasingly aware that a slight twinge of annoyance is nothing but a veil drawn over 
14   intense fury.
15   W-pI.21.3. Try, therefore, not to let the "little" thoughts of anger escape you in the 
16   practice periods. 2 Remember that you do not really recognize what arouses anger in you, and 
17   nothing that you believe in this connection means anything. 3 You will probably be tempted to 
18   dwell more on some situations or persons than on others, on the fallacious grounds that they
19   are more "obvious." 4 This is not so. 5 It is merely an example of the belief that some
20   forms of attack are more justified than others.
21   W-pI.21.4. As you search your mind for all the forms in which attack thoughts present 
22   themselves, hold each one in mind while you tell yourself: 
23   
24   2 I am determined to see___[name of person] differently. 
25   3 I am determined to see___[specify the situation] differently.
26   
27   W-pI.21.5. Try to be as specific as possible. 2 You may, for example, focus your anger 
28   on a particular attribute of a particular person, believing that the anger is limited to 
29   this aspect. 3 If your perception is suffering from this form of distortion, say: 
30   
31   4 I am determined to see___[specify the attribute] in___[name of person] differently.
32   
