 5   LESSON 27.
 6   
 7   Above all else I want to see.
 8   W-pI.27.1. Today's idea expresses something stronger than mere determination. 2 It 
 9   gives vision priority among your desires. 3 You may feel hesitant about using the idea, on 
10   the grounds that you are not sure you really mean it. 4 This does not matter. 5 The 
11   purpose of today's exercises is to bring the time when the idea will be wholly true a little 
12   nearer.
13   W-pI.27.2. There may be a great temptation to believe that some sort of sacrifice is 
14   being asked of you when you say you want to see above all else. 2 If you become uneasy about
15   the lack of reservation involved, add: 
16   
17   3 Vision has no cost to anyone.
18   
19   4 If fear of loss still persists, add further: 
20   
21   5 It can only bless.
22   
23   W-pI.27.3. The idea for today needs many repetitions for maximum benefit. 2 It should 
24   be used at least every half hour, and more if possible. 3 You might try for every fifteen
25   or twenty minutes. 4 It is recommended that you set a definite time interval for using 
26   the idea when you wake or shortly afterwards, and attempt to adhere to it throughout the 
27   day. 5 It will not be difficult to do this, even if you are engaged in conversation, or 
28   otherwise occupied at the time. 6 You can still repeat one short sentence to yourself without 
29   disturbing anything.
30   W-pI.27.4. The real question is, how often will you remember? 2 How much do you want 
31   today's idea to be true? 3 Answer one of these questions, and you have answered the other. 4 
32   You will probably miss several applications, and perhaps quite a number. 5 Do not be 
33   disturbed by this, but do try to keep on your schedule from then on. 6 If only once during the 
34   day you feel that you were perfectly sincere while you were repeating today's idea, you 
35   can be sure that you have saved yourself many years of effort.
