39   LESSON 29.
40   
41   God is in everything I see.
42   W-pI.29.1. The idea for today explains why you can see all purpose in everything. 2 It 
43   explains why nothing is separate, by itself or in itself. 3 And it explains why nothing you see
44   means anything. 4 In fact, it explains every idea we have used thus far, and all 
45   subsequent ones as well. 5 Today's idea is the whole basis for vision.
46   W-pI.29.2. You will probably find this idea very difficult to grasp at this point. 2 
47   You may find it silly, irreverent, senseless, funny and even objectionable. 3 Certainly 
48   God is not in a table, for example, as you see it. 4 Yet we emphasized yesterday that a 
49   table shares the purpose of the universe. 5 And what shares the purpose of the universe 
50   shares the purpose of its Creator.
0429
 1   W-pI.29.3. Try then, today, to begin to learn how to look on all things with love, 
 2   appreciation and open-mindedness. 2 You do not see them now. 3 Would you know what is in them? 4 
 3   Nothing is as it appears to you. 5 Its holy purpose stands beyond your little range. 6 When 
 4   vision has shown you the holiness that lights up the world, you will understand today's idea 
 5   perfectly. 7 And you will not understand how you could ever have found it difficult.
 6   W-pI.29.4. Our six two-minute practice periods for today should follow a now familiar 
 7   pattern: Begin with repeating the idea to yourself, and then apply it to randomly chosen 
 8   subjects about you, naming each one specifically. 2 Try to avoid the tendency toward 
 9   self-directed selection, which may be particularly tempting in connection with today's idea because 
10   of its wholly alien nature. 3 Remember that any order you impose is equally alien to 
11   reality.
12   W-pI.29.5. Your list of subjects should therefore be as free of self-selection as 
13   possible. 2 For example, a suitable list might include: 
14   
15   3 God is in this coat hanger. 
16   4 God is in this magazine. 
17   5 God is in this finger. 
18   6 God is in this lamp. 
19   7 God is in that body. 
20   8 God is in that door. 
21   9 God is in that waste basket. 
22   
23   10 In addition to the assigned practice periods, repeat the idea for today at least 
24   once an hour, looking slowly about you as you say the words unhurriedly to yourself. 11 At 
25   least once or twice, you should experience a sense of restfulness as you do this.
