29   LESSON 30.
30   
31   God is in everything I see because God is in my mind.
32   W-pI.30.1. The idea for today is the springboard for vision. 2 From this idea will the 
33   world open up before you, and you will look upon it and see in it what you have never seen 
34   before. 3 Nor will what you saw before be even faintly visible to you.
35   W-pI.30.2. Today we are trying to use a new kind of "projection." 2 We are not 
36   attempting to get rid of what we do not like by seeing it outside. 3 Instead, we are trying to 
37   see in the world what is in our minds, and what we want to recognize is there. 4 Thus, we 
38   are trying to join with what we see, rather than keeping it apart from us. 5 That is the 
39   fundamental difference between vision and the way you see.
40   W-pI.30.3. Today's idea should be applied as often as possible throughout the day. 2 
41   Whenever you have a moment or so, repeat it to yourself slowly, looking about you, and trying 
42   to realize that the idea applies to everything you do see now, or could see now if it 
43   were within the range of your sight.
44   W-pI.30.4. Real vision is not limited to concepts such as "near" and "far." 2 To help 
45   you begin to get used to this idea, try to think of things beyond your present range as 
46   well as those you can actually see, as you apply today's idea.
47   W-pI.30.5. Real vision is not only unlimited by space and distance, but it does not 
48   depend on the body's eyes at all. 2 The mind is its only source. 3 To aid in helping you to 
49   become more accustomed to this idea as well, devote several practice periods to applying 
50   today's idea with your eyes closed, using whatever subjects come to mind, and looking within 
0430
 1   rather than without. 4 Today's idea applies equally to both.
 2   
