37   I have invented the world I see.
38   W-pI.32.1. Today we are continuing to develop the theme of cause and effect. 2 You are 
39   not the victim of the world you see because you invented it. 3 You can give it up as 
40   easily as you made it up. 4 You will see it or not see it, as you wish. 5 While you want it 
41   you will see it; when you no longer want it, it will not be there for you to see.
42   W-pI.32.2. The idea for today, like the preceding ones, applies to your inner and outer
43   worlds, which are actually the same. 2 However, since you see them as different, the 
44   practice periods for today will again include two phases, one involving the world you see 
45   outside you, and the other the world you see in your mind. 3 In today's exercises, try to 
46   introduce the thought that both are in your own imagination.
47   W-pI.32.3. Again we will begin the practice periods for the morning and evening by 
48   repeating the idea for today two or three times while looking around at the world you see as 
49   outside yourself. 2 Then close your eyes and look around your inner world. 3 Try to treat them
50   both as equally as possible. 4 Repeat the idea for today unhurriedly as often as you 
0431
 1   wish, as you watch the images your imagination presents to your awareness.
 2   W-pI.32.4. For the two longer practice periods three to five minutes are recommended, 
 3   with not less than three required. 2 More than five can be utilized, if you find the 
 4   exercise restful. 3 To facilitate this, select a time when few distractions are anticipated, 
 5   and when you yourself feel reasonably ready.
 6   W-pI.32.5. These exercises are also to be continued during the day, as often as 
 7   possible. 2 The shorter applications consist of repeating the idea slowly, as you survey either
 8   your inner or outer world. 3 It does not matter which you choose.
 9   W-pI.32.6. The idea for today should also be applied immediately to any situation that 
10   may distress you. 2 Apply the idea by telling yourself: 
11   
12   3 I have invented this situation as I see it.
