43   I could see peace instead of this.
44   W-pI.34.1. The idea for today begins to describe the conditions that prevail in the 
45   other way of seeing. 2 Peace of mind is clearly an internal matter. 3 It must begin with 
46   your own thoughts, and then extend outward. 4 It is from your peace of mind that a peaceful
47   perception of the world arises.
48   W-pI.34.2. Three longer practice periods are required for today's exercises. 2 One in 
49   the morning and one in the evening are advised, with an additional one to be undertaken at
50   any time in between that seems most conducive to readiness. 3 All applications should 
0432
 1   be done with your eyes closed. 4 It is your inner world to which the applications of 
 2   today's idea should be made.
 3   W-pI.34.3. Some five minutes of mind searching are required for each of the longer 
 4   practice periods. 2 Search your mind for fear thoughts, anxiety-provoking situations, "
 5   offending" personalities or events, or anything else about which you are harboring unloving 
 6   thoughts. 3 Note them all casually, repeating the idea for today slowly as you watch them arise
 7   in your mind, and let each one go, to be replaced by the next.
 8   W-pI.34.4. If you begin to experience difficulty in thinking of specific subjects, 
 9   continue to repeat the idea to yourself in an unhurried manner, without applying it to anything
10   in particular. 2 Be sure, however, not to make any specific exclusions.
11   W-pI.34.5. The shorter applications are to be frequent, and made whenever you feel your
12   peace of mind is threatened in any way. 2 The purpose is to protect yourself from 
13   temptation throughout the day. 3 If a specific form of temptation arises in your awareness, the 
14   exercise should take this form: 
15   
16   4 I could see peace in this situation instead of what I now see in it.
17   
18   W-pI.34.6. If the inroads on your peace of mind take the form of more generalized 
19   adverse emotions, such as depression, anxiety or worry, use the idea in its original form. 2 
20   If you find you need more than one application of today's idea to help you change your 
21   mind in any specific context, try to take several minutes and devote them to repeating the 
22   idea until you feel some sense of relief. 3 It will help you if you tell yourself 
23   specifically: 
24   
25   4 I can replace my feelings of depression, anxiety or worry [or my thoughts about this 
26   situation, personality or event] with peace.
