41   LESSON 36.
42   
43   My holiness envelops everything I see.
44   W-pI.36.1. Today's idea extends the idea for yesterday from the perceiver to the 
45   perceived. 2 You are holy because your mind is part of God's. 3 And because you are holy, your 
46   sight must be holy as well. 4 "Sinless" means without sin. 5 You cannot be without sin a 
47   little. 6 You are sinless or not. 7 If your mind is part of God's you must be sinless, or a 
48   part of His Mind would be sinful. 8 Your sight is related to His Holiness, not to your ego,
49   and therefore not to your body.
50   W-pI.36.2. Four three-to-five-minute practice periods are required for today. 2 Try to 
0434
 1   distribute them fairly evenly, and make the shorter applications frequently, to protect your 
 2   protection throughout the day. 3 The longer practice periods should take this form:
 3   W-pI.36.3. First, close your eyes and repeat the idea for today several times, slowly. 
 4   2 Then open your eyes and look quite slowly about you, applying the idea specifically to
 5   whatever you note in your casual survey. 3 Say, for example: 
 6   
 7   4 My holiness envelops that rug. 
 8   5 My holiness envelops that wall. 
 9   6 My holiness envelops these fingers. 
10   7 My holiness envelops that chair. 
11   8 My holiness envelops that body. 
12   9 My holiness envelops this pen. 
13   
14   10 Several times during these practice periods, close your eyes and repeat the idea to 
15   yourself. 11 Then open your eyes, and continue as before.
16   W-pI.36.4. For the shorter exercise periods, close your eyes and repeat the idea; look 
17   about you as you repeat it again; and conclude with one more repetition with your eyes 
18   closed. 2 All applications should, of course, be made quite slowly, as effortlessly and 
19   unhurriedly as possible.
