18   LESSON 38.
19   
20   There is nothing my holiness cannot do.
21   W-pI.38.1. Your holiness reverses all the laws of the world. 2 It is beyond every 
22   restriction of time, space, distance and limits of any kind. 3 Your holiness is totally unlimited 
23   in its power because it establishes you as a Son of God, at one with the Mind of his 
24   Creator.
25   W-pI.38.2. Through your holiness the power of God is made manifest. 2 Through your 
26   holiness the power of God is made available. 3 And there is nothing the power of God cannot do.
27   4 Your holiness, then, can remove all pain, can end all sorrow, and can solve all 
28   problems. 5 It can do so in connection with yourself and with anyone else. 6 It is equal in its
29   power to help anyone because it is equal in its power to save anyone.
30   W-pI.38.3. If you are holy, so is everything God created. 2 You are holy because all 
31   things He created are holy. 3 And all things He created are holy because you are. 4 In 
32   today's exercises, we will apply the power of your holiness to all problems, difficulties or 
33   suffering in any form that you happen to think of, in yourself or in someone else. 5 We will 
34   make no distinctions because there are no distinctions.
35   W-pI.38.4. In the four longer practice periods, each preferably to last a full five 
36   minutes, repeat the idea for today, close your eyes, and then search your mind for any sense 
37   of loss or unhappiness of any kind as you see it. 2 Try to make as little distinction as 
38   possible between a situation that is difficult for you, and one that is difficult for someone 
39   else. 3 Identify the situation specifically, and also the name of the person concerned. 4 
40   Use this form in applying the idea for today: 
41   
42   5 In the situation involving ___ in which I see myself, there is nothing that my 
43   holiness cannot do. 
44   6 In the situation involving___in which___sees himself, there is nothing my holiness 
45   cannot do.
46   
47   W-pI.38.5. From time to time you may want to vary this procedure, and add some relevant
48   thoughts of your own. 2 You might like, for example, to include thoughts such as: 
49   
50   3 There is nothing my holiness cannot do because the power of God lies in it. 
0436
 1   
 2   4 Introduce whatever variations appeal to you, but keep the exercises focused on the 
 3   theme, "There is nothing my holiness cannot do." 5 The purpose of today's exercises is to 
 4   begin to instill in you a sense that you have dominion over all things because of what you 
 5   are.
 6   W-pI.38.6. In the frequent shorter applications, apply the idea in its original form 
 7   unless a specific problem concerning you or someone else arises, or comes to mind. 2 In that 
 8   event, use the more specific form in applying the idea to it.
