27   LESSON 40.
28   
29   I am blessed as a Son of God.
30   W-pI.40.1. Today we will begin to assert some of the happy things to which you are 
31   entitled, being what you are. 2 No long practice periods are required today, but very frequent 
32   short ones are necessary. 3 Once every ten minutes would be highly desirable, and you are 
33   urged to attempt this schedule and to adhere to it whenever possible. 4 If you forget, try 
34   again. 5 If there are long interruptions, try again. 6 Whenever you remember, try again.
35   W-pI.40.2. You need not close your eyes for the exercise periods, although you will 
36   probably find it more helpful if you do. 2 However, you may be in a number of situations during
37   the day when closing your eyes would not be feasible. 3 Do not miss a practice period 
38   because of this. 4 You can practice quite well under any circumstances, if you really want to.
39   W-pI.40.3. Today's exercises take little time and no effort. 2 Repeat the idea for 
40   today, and then add several of the attributes you associate with being a Son of God, 
41   applying them to yourself. 3 One practice period might, for example, consist of the following: 
42   
43   4 I am blessed as a Son of God
44   5 I am happy, peaceful, loving and contented. 
45   
46   6 Another might take this form: 
47   
48   7 I am blessed as a Son of God
49   8 I am calm, quiet, assured and confident. 
