 6   LESSON 41.
 7   
 8   God goes with me wherever I go.
 9   W-pI.41.1. Today's idea will eventually overcome completely the sense of loneliness and
10   abandonment all the separated ones experience. 2 Depression is an inevitable 
11   consequence of separation. 3 So are anxiety, worry, a deep sense of helplessness, misery, 
12   suffering and intense fear of loss.
13   W-pI.41.2. The separated ones have invented many "cures" for what they believe to be "
14   the ills of the world." 2 But the one thing they do not do is to question the reality of 
15   the problem. 3 Yet its effects cannot be cured because the problem is not real. 4 The idea
16   for today has the power to end all this foolishness forever. 5 And foolishness it is, 
17   despite the serious and tragic forms it may take.
18   W-pI.41.3. Deep within you is everything that is perfect, ready to radiate through you 
19   and out into the world. 2 It will cure all sorrow and pain and fear and loss because it 
20   will heal the mind that thought these things were real, and suffered out of its allegiance 
21   to them.
22   W-pI.41.4. You can never be deprived of your perfect holiness because its Source goes 
23   with you wherever you go. 2 You can never suffer because the Source of all joy goes with 
24   you wherever you go. 3 You can never be alone because the Source of all life goes with you
25   wherever you go. 4 Nothing can destroy your peace of mind because God goes with you 
26   wherever you go.
27   W-pI.41.5. We understand that you do not believe all this. 2 How could you, when the 
28   truth is hidden deep within, under a heavy cloud of insane thoughts, dense and obscuring, 
29   yet representing all you see? 3 Today we will make our first real attempt to get past this
30   dark and heavy cloud, and to go through it to the light beyond.
31   W-pI.41.6. There will be only one long practice period today. 2 In the morning, as soon
32   as you get up if possible, sit quietly for some three to five minutes, with your eyes 
33   closed. 3 At the beginning of the practice period, repeat today's idea very slowly. 4 Then 
34   make no effort to think of anything. 5 Try, instead, to get a sense of turning inward, past
35   all the idle thoughts of the world. 6 Try to enter very deeply into your own mind, 
36   keeping it clear of any thoughts that might divert your attention.
37   W-pI.41.7. From time to time, you may repeat the idea if you find it helpful. 2 But 
38   most of all, try to sink down and inward, away from the world and all the foolish thoughts 
39   of the world. 3 You are trying to reach past all these things. 4 You are trying to leave 
40   appearances and approach reality.
41   W-pI.41.8. It is quite possible to reach God. 2 In fact it is very easy, because it is 
42   the most natural thing in the world. 3 You might even say it is the only natural thing in 
43   the world. 4 The way will open, if you believe that it is possible. 5 This exercise can 
44   bring very startling results even the first time it is attempted, and sooner or later it is 
45   always successful. 6 We will go into more detail about this kind of practice as we go along. 
46   7 But it will never fail completely, and instant success is possible.
47   W-pI.41.9. Throughout the day use today's idea often, repeating it very slowly, 
48   preferably with eyes closed. 2 Think of what you are saying; what the words mean. 3 Concentrate 
49   on the holiness that they imply about you; on the unfailing companionship that is yours; 
50   on the complete protection that surrounds you.
0439
 1   W-pI.41.10. You can indeed afford to laugh at fear thoughts, remembering that God goes 
 2   with you wherever you go.
