 6   LESSON 43.
 7   
 8   God is my Source. I cannot see apart from Him.
 9   W-pI.43.1. Perception is not an attribute of God. 2 His is the realm of knowledge. 3 
10   Yet He has created the Holy Spirit as the Mediator between perception and knowledge. 4 
11   Without this link with God, perception would have replaced knowledge forever in your mind. 5 
12   With this link with God, perception will become so changed and purified that it will lead 
13   to knowledge. 6 That is its function as the Holy Spirit sees it. 7 Therefore, that is its
14   function in truth.
15   W-pI.43.2. In God you cannot see. 2 Perception has no function in God, and does not 
16   exist. 3 Yet in salvation, which is the undoing of what never was, perception has a mighty 
17   purpose. 4 Made by the Son of God for an unholy purpose, it must become the means for the 
18   restoration of his holiness to his awareness. 5 Perception has no meaning. 6 Yet does the Holy 
19   Spirit give it a meaning very close to God's. 7 Healed perception becomes the means by which 
20   the Son of God forgives his brother, and thus forgives himself.
21   W-pI.43.3. You cannot see apart from God because you cannot be apart from God. 2 
22   Whatever you do you do in Him, because whatever you think, you think with His Mind. 3 If vision
23   is real, and it is real to the extent to which it shares the Holy Spirit's purpose, 
24   then you cannot see apart from God.
25   W-pI.43.4. Three five-minute practice periods are required today, one as early and one 
26   as late as possible in the day. 2 The third may be undertaken at the most convenient and 
27   suitable time that circumstances and readiness permit. 3 At the beginning of these practice 
28   periods, repeat the idea for today to yourself with eyes open. 4 Then glance around you for a 
29   short time, applying the idea specifically to what you see. 5 Four or five subjects for this
30   phase of the practice period are sufficient. 6 You might say, for example: 
31   
32   7 God is my Source. 8 I cannot see this desk apart from Him
33   9 God is my Source. 10 I cannot see that picture apart from Him.
34   
35   W-pI.43.5. Although this part of the exercise period should be relatively short, be 
36   sure that you select the subjects for this phase of practice indiscriminately, without 
37   self-directed inclusion or exclusion. 2 For the second and longer phase, close your eyes, repeat 
38   today's idea again, and then let whatever relevant thoughts occur to you add to the idea in 
39   your own personal way. 3 Thoughts such as: 
40   
41   4 I see through the eyes of forgiveness
42   5 I see the world as blessed
43   6 The world can show me myself
44   7 I see my own thoughts, which are like God's. 
45   
46   8 Any thought related more or less directly to today's idea is suitable. 9 The thoughts
47   need not bear any obvious relationship to the idea, but they should not be in 
48   opposition to it.
49   W-pI.43.6. If you find your mind wandering; if you begin to be aware of thoughts which 
50   are clearly out of accord with today's idea, or if you seem to be unable to think of 
0441
 1   anything, open your eyes, repeat the first phase of the exercise period, and then attempt the 
 2   second phase again. 2 Do not allow any protracted period to occur in which you become 
 3   preoccupied with irrelevant thoughts. 3 Return to the first phase of the exercises as often as 
 4   necessary to prevent this.
 5   W-pI.43.7. In applying today's idea in the shorter practice periods, the form may vary 
 6   according to the circumstances and situations in which you find yourself during the day. 2 When 
 7   you are with someone else, for example, try to remember to tell him silently: 
 8   
 9   3 God is my Source. 4 I cannot see you apart from Him. 
10   
11   5 This form is equally applicable to strangers as it is to those you think are closer 
12   to you. 6 In fact, try not to make distinctions of this kind at all.
13   W-pI.43.8. Today's idea should also be applied throughout the day to various situations
14   and events that may occur, particularly to those which seem to distress you in any way.
15   2 For this purpose, apply the idea in this form: 
16   
17   3 God is my Source. 4 I cannot see this apart from Him.
18   
19   W-pI.43.9. If no particular subject presents itself to your awareness at the time, 
20   merely repeat the idea in its original form. 2 Try today not to allow any long periods of 
21   time to slip by without remembering today's idea, and thus remembering your function.
