25   LESSON 44.
26   
27   God is the light in which I see.
28   W-pI.44.1. Today we are continuing the idea for yesterday, adding another dimension to 
29   it. 2 You cannot see in darkness, and you cannot make light. 3 You can make darkness and 
30   then think you see in it, but light reflects life, and is therefore an aspect of creation. 
31   4 Creation and darkness cannot coexist, but light and life must go together, being but 
32   different aspects of creation.
33   W-pI.44.2. In order to see, you must recognize that light is within, not without. 2 You
34   do not see outside yourself, nor is the equipment for seeing outside you. 3 An 
35   essential part of this equipment is the light that makes seeing possible. 4 It is with you 
36   always, making vision possible in every circumstance.
37   W-pI.44.3. Today we are going to attempt to reach that light. 2 For this purpose, we 
38   will use a form of exercise which has been suggested before, and which we will utilize 
39   increasingly. 3 It is a particularly difficult form for the undisciplined mind, and represents a 
40   major goal of mind training. 4 It requires precisely what the untrained mind lacks. 5 Yet 
41   this training must be accomplished if you are to see.
42   W-pI.44.4. Have at least three practice periods today, each lasting three to five 
43   minutes. 2 A longer time is highly recommended, but only if you find the time slipping by with
44   little or no sense of strain. 3 The form of practice we will use today is the most 
45   natural and easy one in the world for the trained mind, just as it seems to be the most 
46   unnatural and difficult for the untrained mind.
47   W-pI.44.5. Your mind is no longer wholly untrained. 2 You are quite ready to learn the 
48   form of exercise we will use today, but you may find that you will encounter strong 
49   resistance. 3 The reason is very simple. 4 While you practice in this way, you leave behind 
50   everything that you now believe, and all the thoughts that you have made up. 5 Properly speaking,
0442
 1   this is the release from hell. 6 Yet perceived through the ego's eyes, it is loss of 
 2   identity and a descent into hell.
 3   W-pI.44.6. If you can stand aside from the ego by ever so little, you will have no 
 4   difficulty in recognizing that its opposition and its fears are meaningless. 2 You might find it 
 5   helpful to remind yourself, from time to time, that to reach light is to escape from darkness,
 6   whatever you may believe to the contrary. 3 God is the light in which you see. 4 You 
 7   are attempting to reach Him.
 8   W-pI.44.7. Begin the practice period by repeating today's idea with your eyes open, and
 9   close them slowly, repeating the idea several times more. 2 Then try to sink into your 
10   mind, letting go every kind of interference and intrusion by quietly sinking past them. 3 
11   Your mind cannot be stopped in this unless you choose to stop it. 4 It is merely taking its
12   natural course. 5 Try to observe your passing thoughts without involvement, and slip 
13   quietly by them.
14   W-pI.44.8. While no particular approach is advocated for this form of exercise, what is
15   needful is a sense of the importance of what you are doing; its inestimable value to 
16   you, and an awareness that you are attempting something very holy. 2 Salvation is your 
17   happiest accomplishment. 3 It is also the only one that has any meaning, because it is the only
18   one that has any real use to you at all.
19   W-pI.44.9. If resistance rises in any form, pause long enough to repeat today's idea, 
20   keeping your eyes closed unless you are aware of fear. 2 In that case, you will probably find 
21   it more reassuring to open your eyes briefly. 3 Try, however, to return to the exercises 
22   with eyes closed as soon as possible.
23   W-pI.44.10. If you are doing the exercises correctly, you should experience some sense 
24   of relaxation, and even a feeling that you are approaching, if not actually entering into
25   light. 2 Try to think of light, formless and without limit, as you pass by the thoughts
26   of this world. 3 And do not forget that they cannot hold you to the world unless you 
27   give them the power to do so.
28   W-pI.44.11. Throughout the day repeat the idea often, with eyes open or closed as seems
29   better to you at the time. 2 But do not forget. 3 Above all, be determined not to 
30   forget today.
