34   LESSON 45.
35   
36   God is the Mind with which I think.
37   W-pI.45.1. Today's idea holds the key to what your real thoughts are. 2 They are 
38   nothing that you think you think, just as nothing that you think you see is related to vision 
39   in any way. 3 There is no relationship between what is real and what you think is real. 4
40   Nothing that you think are your real thoughts resemble your real thoughts in any 
41   respect. 5 Nothing that you think you see bears any resemblance to what vision will show you.
42   W-pI.45.2. You think with the Mind of God. 2 Therefore you share your thoughts with Him,
43    as He shares His with you. 3 They are the same thoughts, because they are thought by 
44   the same Mind. 4 To share is to make alike, or to make one. 5 Nor do the thoughts you 
45   think with the Mind of God leave your mind, because thoughts do not leave their source. 6 
46   Therefore, your thoughts are in the Mind of God, as you are. 7 They are in your mind as well, 
47   where He is. 8 As you are part of His Mind, so are your thoughts part of His Mind.
48   W-pI.45.3. Where, then, are your real thoughts? 2 Today we will attempt to reach them. 
49   3 We will have to look for them in your mind, because that is where they are. 4 They 
50   must still be there, because they cannot have left their source. 5 What is thought by the 
0443
 1   Mind of God is eternal, being part of creation.
 2   W-pI.45.4. Our three five-minute practice periods for today will take the same general 
 3   form that we used in applying yesterday's idea. 2 We will attempt to leave the unreal and 
 4   seek for the real. 3 We will deny the world in favor of truth. 4 We will not let the 
 5   thoughts of the world hold us back. 5 We will not let the beliefs of the world tell us that 
 6   what God would have us do is impossible. 6 Instead, we will try to recognize that only what
 7   God would have us do is possible.
 8   W-pI.45.5. We will also try to understand that only what God would have us do is what 
 9   we want to do. 2 And we will also try to remember that we cannot fail in doing what He 
10   would have us do. 3 There is every reason to feel confident that we will succeed today. 4 It
11   is the Will of God.
12   W-pI.45.6. Begin the exercises for today by repeating the idea to yourself, closing 
13   your eyes as you do so. 2 Then spend a fairly short period in thinking a few relevant 
14   thoughts of your own, keeping the idea in mind. 3 After you have added some four or five 
15   thoughts of your own to the idea, repeat it again and tell yourself gently: 
16   
17   4 My real thoughts are in my mind. 5 I would like to find them. 
18   
19   6 Then try to go past all the unreal thoughts that cover the truth in your mind, and 
20   reach to the eternal.
21   W-pI.45.7. Under all the senseless thoughts and mad ideas with which you have cluttered
22   up your mind are the thoughts that you thought with God in the beginning. 2 They are 
23   there in your mind now, completely unchanged. 3 They will always be in your mind, exactly as
24   they always were. 4 Everything you have thought since then will change, but the 
25   Foundation on which it rests is wholly changeless.
26   W-pI.45.8. It is this Foundation toward which the exercises for today are directed. 2 
27   Here is your mind joined with the Mind of God. 3 Here are your thoughts one with His. 4 For
28   this kind of practice only one thing is necessary; approach it as you would an altar 
29   dedicated in Heaven to God the Father and to God the Son. 5 For such is the place you are trying
30   to reach. 6 You will probably be unable as yet to realize how high you are trying to go.
31    7 Yet even with the little understanding you have already gained, you should be able 
32   to remind yourself that this is no idle game, but an exercise in holiness and an attempt 
33   to reach the Kingdom of Heaven.
34   W-pI.45.9. In the shorter exercise periods for today, try to remember how important it 
35   is to you to understand the holiness of the mind that thinks with God. 2 Take a minute or
36   two, as you repeat the idea throughout the day, to appreciate your mind's holiness. 3 
37   Stand aside, however briefly, from all thoughts that are unworthy of Him Whose host you are.
38   4 And thank Him for the Thoughts He is thinking with you.
39   
40   
41   
42   LESSON 46.
43   
44   God is the Love in which I forgive.
45   W-pI.46.1. God does not forgive because He has never condemned. 2 And there must be 
46   condemnation before forgiveness is necessary. 3 Forgiveness is the great need of this world, but 
47   that is because it is a world of illusions. 4 Those who forgive are thus releasing 
48   themselves from illusions, while those who withhold forgiveness are binding themselves to them. 5
49   As you condemn only yourself, so do you forgive only yourself.
50   W-pI.46.2. Yet although God does not forgive, His Love is nevertheless the basis of 
0444
 1   forgiveness. 2 Fear condemns and love forgives. 3 Forgiveness thus undoes what fear has produced, 
 2   returning the mind to the awareness of God. 4 For this reason, forgiveness can truly be called 
 3   salvation. 5 It is the means by which illusions disappear.
 4   W-pI.46.3. Today's exercises require at least three full five-minute practice periods, 
 5   and as many shorter ones as possible. 2 Begin the longer practice periods by repeating 
 6   today's idea to yourself, as usual. 3 Close your eyes as you do so, and spend a minute or two 
 7   in searching your mind for those whom you have not forgiven. 4 It does not matter "how 
 8   much" you have not forgiven them. 5 You have forgiven them entirely or not at all.
 9   W-pI.46.4. If you are doing the exercises well you should have no difficulty in finding
10   a number of people you have not forgiven. 2 It is a safe rule that anyone you do not 
11   like is a suitable subject. 3 Mention each one by name, and say: 
12   
13   4 God is the Love in which I forgive you, [name].
14   
15   W-pI.46.5. The purpose of the first phase of today's practice periods is to put you in 
16   a position to forgive yourself. 2 After you have applied the idea to all those who have 
17   come to mind, tell yourself: 
18   
19   3 God is the Love in which I forgive myself. 
20   
21   4 Then devote the remainder of the practice period to adding related ideas such as: 
22   
23   5 God is the Love with which I love myself
24   6 God is the Love in which I am blessed.
25   
26   W-pI.46.6. The form of the application may vary considerably, but the central idea 
27   should not be lost sight of. 2 You might say, for example: 
28   
29   3 I cannot be guilty because I am a Son of God. 
30   4 I have already been forgiven. 
31   5 No fear is possible in a mind beloved of God. 
32   6 There is no need to attack because love has forgiven me. 
33   
34   7 The practice period should end, however, with a repetition of today's idea as 
35   originally stated.
36   W-pI.46.7. The shorter practice periods may consist either of a repetition of the idea 
37   for today in the original or in a related form, as you prefer. 2 Be sure, however, to make
38   more specific applications if they are needed. 3 They will be needed at any time during
39   the day when you become aware of any kind of negative reaction to anyone, present or 
40   not. 4 In that event, tell him silently: 
41   
42   5 God is the Love in which I forgive you.
43   
44   
45   
46   LESSON 47.
47   
48   God is the strength in which I trust.
49   W-pI.47.1. If you are trusting in your own strength, you have every reason to be 
50   apprehensive, anxious and fearful. 2 What can you predict or control? 3 What is there in you that 
0445
 1   can be counted on? 4 What would give you the ability to be aware of all the facets of any 
 2   problem, and to resolve them in such a way that only good can come of it? 5 What is there in 
 3   you that gives you the recognition of the right solution, and the guarantee that it will 
 4   be accomplished?
 5   W-pI.47.2. Of yourself you can do none of these things. 2 To believe that you can is to
 6   put your trust where trust is unwarranted, and to justify fear, anxiety, depression, 
 7   anger and sorrow. 3 Who can put his faith in weakness and feel safe? 4 Yet who can put his 
 8   faith in strength and feel weak?
 9   W-pI.47.3. God is your safety in every circumstance. 2 His Voice speaks for Him in all 
10   situations and in every aspect of all situations, telling you exactly what to do to call upon His
11   strength and His protection. 3 There are no exceptions because God has no exceptions. 4
12   And the Voice which speaks for Him thinks as He does.
13   W-pI.47.4. Today we will try to reach past your own weakness to the Source of real 
14   strength. 2 Four five-minute practice periods are necessary today, and longer and more frequent
15   ones are urged. 3 Close your eyes and begin, as usual, by repeating the idea for the 
16   day. 4 Then spend a minute or two in searching for situations in your life which you have 
17   invested with fear, dismissing each one by telling yourself: 
18   
19   5 God is the strength in which I trust.
20   
21   W-pI.47.5. Now try to slip past all concerns related to your own sense of inadequacy. 2
22   It is obvious that any situation that causes you concern is associated with feelings of
23   inadequacy, for otherwise you would believe that you could deal with the situation 
24   successfully. 3 It is not by trusting yourself that you will gain confidence. 4 But the strength of
25   God in you is successful in all things.
26   W-pI.47.6. The recognition of your own frailty is a necessary step in the correction of
27   your errors, but it is hardly a sufficient one in giving you the confidence which you 
28   need, and to which you are entitled. 2 You must also gain an awareness that confidence in 
29   your real strength is fully justified in every respect and in all circumstances.
30   W-pI.47.7. In the latter phase of the practice period, try to reach down into your mind
31   to a place of real safety. 2 You will recognize that you have reached it if you feel a 
32   sense of deep peace, however briefly. 3 Let go all the trivial things that churn and bubble 
33   on the surface of your mind, and reach down and below them to the Kingdom of Heaven. 4 
34   There is a place in you where there is perfect peace. 5 There is a place in you where 
35   nothing is impossible. 6 There is a place in you where the strength of God abides.
36   W-pI.47.8. During the day, repeat the idea often. 2 Use it as your answer to any 
37   disturbance. 3 Remember that peace is your right, because you are giving your trust to the 
38   strength of God.
39   
40   
41   
42   LESSON 48.
43   
44   There is nothing to fear.
45   W-pI.48.1. The idea for today simply states a fact. 2 It is not a fact to those who 
46   believe in illusions, but illusions are not facts. 3 In truth there is nothing to fear. 4 It 
47   is very easy to recognize this. 5 But it is very difficult to recognize it for those who 
48   want illusions to be true.
49   W-pI.48.2. Today's practice periods will be very short, very simple and very frequent. 
50   2 Merely repeat the idea as often as possible. 3 You can use it with your eyes open at 
0446
 1   any time and in any situation. 4 It is strongly recommended, however, that you take a 
 2   minute or so whenever possible to close your eyes and repeat the idea slowly to yourself 
 3   several times. 5 It is particularly important that you use the idea immediately, should 
 4   anything disturb your peace of mind.
 5   W-pI.48.3. The presence of fear is a sure sign that you are trusting in your own 
 6   strength. 2 The awareness that there is nothing to fear shows that somewhere in your mind, 
 7   though not necessarily in a place you recognize as yet, you have remembered God, and let His 
 8   strength take the place of your weakness. 3 The instant you are willing to do this there is 
 9   indeed nothing to fear.
10   
11   
12   
13   LESSON 49.
14   
15   God's Voice speaks to me all through the day.
16   W-pI.49.1. It is quite possible to listen to God's Voice all through the day without 
17   interrupting your regular activities in any way. 2 The part of your mind in which truth abides is 
18   in constant communication with God, whether you are aware of it or not. 3 It is the other
19   part of your mind that functions in the world and obeys the world's laws. 4 It is this 
20   part that is constantly distracted, disorganized and highly uncertain.
21   W-pI.49.2. The part that is listening to the Voice for God is calm, always at rest and 
22   wholly certain. 2 It is really the only part there is. 3 The other part is a wild illusion, 
23   frantic and distraught, but without reality of any kind. 4 Try today not to listen to it. 5 
24   Try to identify with the part of your mind where stillness and peace reign forever. 6 Try 
25   to hear God's Voice call to you lovingly, reminding you that your Creator has not 
26   forgotten His Son.
27   W-pI.49.3. We will need at least four five-minute practice periods today, and more if 
28   possible. 2 We will try actually to hear God's Voice reminding you of Him and of your Self. 3 
29   We will approach this happiest and holiest of thoughts with confidence, knowing that in 
30   doing so we are joining our will with the Will of God. 4 He wants you to hear His Voice. 5 
31   He gave It to you to be heard.
32   W-pI.49.4. Listen in deep silence. 2 Be very still and open your mind. 3 Go past all 
33   the raucous shrieks and sick imaginings that cover your real thoughts and obscure your 
34   eternal link with God. 4 Sink deep into the peace that waits for you beyond the frantic, 
35   riotous thoughts and sights and sounds of this insane world. 5 You do not live here. 6 We are 
36   trying to reach your real home. 7 We are trying to reach the place where you are truly 
37   welcome. 8 We are trying to reach God.
38   W-pI.49.5. Do not forget to repeat today's idea very frequently. 2 Do so with your eyes
39   open when necessary, but closed when possible. 3 And be sure to sit quietly and repeat 
40   the idea for today whenever you can, closing your eyes on the world, and realizing that 
41   you are inviting God's Voice to speak to you.
42   
