 9   LESSON 56.
10   
11   Our review for today covers the following:
12   W-pI.56.1. (26) My attack thoughts are attacking my invulnerability. 
13   2 How can I know who I am when I see myself as under constant attack? 3 Pain, illness, 
14   loss, age and death seem to threaten me. 4 All my hopes and wishes and plans appear to be 
15   at the mercy of a world I cannot control. 5 Yet perfect security and complete fulfillment
16   are my inheritance. 6 I have tried to give my inheritance away in exchange for the 
17   world I see. 7 But God has kept my inheritance safe for me. 8 My own real thoughts will 
18   teach me what it is.
19   
20   W-pI.56.2. (27) Above all else I want to see. 
21   2 Recognizing that what I see reflects what I think I am, I realize that vision is my 
22   greatest need. 3 The world I see attests to the fearful nature of the self-image I have made. 4
23   If I would remember who I am, it is essential that I let this image of myself go. 5 As 
24   it is replaced by truth, vision will surely be given me. 6 And with this vision, I will 
25   look upon the world and on myself with charity and love.
26   
27   W-pI.56.3. (28) Above all else I want to see differently. 
28   2 The world I see holds my fearful self-image in place, and guarantees its continuance.
29   3 While I see the world as I see it now, truth cannot enter my awareness. 4 I would let
30   the door behind this world be opened for me, that I may look past it to the world that 
31   reflects the Love of God.
32   
33   W-pI.56.4. (29) God is in everything I see. 
34   2 Behind every image I have made, the truth remains unchanged. 3 Behind every veil I 
35   have drawn across the face of love, its light remains undimmed. 4 Beyond all my insane 
36   wishes is my will, united with the Will of my Father. 5 God is still everywhere and in 
37   everything forever. 6 And we who are part of Him will yet look past all appearances, and 
38   recognize the truth beyond them all.
39   
40   W-pI.56.5. (30) God is in everything I see because God is in my mind. 
41   2 In my own mind, behind all my insane thoughts of separation and attack, is the 
42   knowledge that all is one forever. 3 I have not lost the knowledge of Who I am because I have 
43   forgotten it. 4 It has been kept for me in the Mind of God, Who has not left His Thoughts. 5 And
44   I, who am among them, am one with them and one with Him.
45   
