48   see in its light shares in the joy it brings to me. 4 There is nothing that is apart from 
49   this joy, because there is nothing that does not share my holiness. 5 As I recognize my 
50   holiness, so does the holiness of the world shine forth for everyone to see. 
0454
 1   
 2   W-pI.58.3. (38) There is nothing my holiness cannot do. 
 3   2 My holiness is unlimited in its power to heal, because it is unlimited in its power 
 4   to save. 3 What is there to be saved from except illusions? 4 And what are all illusions 
 5   except false ideas about myself? 5 My holiness undoes them all by asserting the truth about 
 6   me. 6 In the presence of my holiness, which I share with God Himself, all idols vanish.
 7   
 8   W-pI.58.4. (39) My holiness is my salvation. 2 Since my holiness saves me from all 
 9   guilt, recognizing my holiness is recognizing my salvation. 3 It is also recognizing the 
10   salvation of the world. 4 Once I have accepted my holiness, nothing can make me afraid. 5 And 
11   because I am unafraid, everyone must share in my understanding, which is the gift of God to me
12   and to the world.
13   
14   W-pI.58.5. (40) I am blessed as a Son of God. 
15   2 Herein lies my claim to all good and only good. 3 I am blessed as a Son of God. 4 All
16   good things are mine, because God intended them for me. 5 I cannot suffer any loss or 
17   deprivation or pain because of Who I am. 6 My Father supports me, protects me, and directs me in 
18   all things. 7 His care for me is infinite, and is with me forever. 8 I am eternally 
19   blessed as His Son.
