24   
25   The following ideas are for review today:
26   W-pI.59.1. (41) God goes with me wherever I go. 
27   2 How can I be alone when God always goes with me? 3 How can I be doubtful and unsure 
28   of myself when perfect certainty abides in Him? 4 How can I be disturbed by anything when
29   He rests in me in absolute peace? 5 How can I suffer when love and joy surround me 
30   through Him? 6 Let me not cherish illusions about myself. 7 I am perfect because God goes with
31   me wherever I go.
32   
33   W-pI.59.2. (42) God is my strength. 2 Vision is His gift. 
34   3 Let me not look to my own eyes to see today. 4 Let me be willing to exchange my 
35   pitiful illusion of seeing for the vision that is given by God. 5 Christ's vision is His gift,
36   and He has given it to me. 6 Let me call upon this gift today, so that this day may 
37   help me to understand eternity.
38   
39   W-pI.59.3. (43) God is my Source. 2 I cannot see apart from Him. 
40   3 I can see what God wants me to see. 4 I cannot see anything else. 5 Beyond His Will 
41   lie only illusions. 6 It is these I choose when I think I can see apart from Him. 7 It is 
42   these I choose when I try to see through the body's eyes. 8 Yet the vision of Christ has 
43   been given me to replace them. 9 It is through this vision that I choose to see.
44   
45   W-pI.59.4. (44) God is the light in which I see. 
46   2 I cannot see in darkness. 3 God is the only light. 4 Therefore, if I am to see, it 
47   must be through Him. 5 I have tried to define what seeing is, and I have been wrong. 6 Now 
48   it is given me to understand that God is the light in which I see. 7 Let me welcome 
49   vision and the happy world it will show me.
50   
0455
 1   W-pI.59.5. (45) God is the Mind with which I think. 
 2   2 I have no thoughts I do not share with God. 3 I have no thoughts apart from Him, 
 3   because I have no mind apart from His. 4 As part of His Mind, my thoughts are His and His 
 4   Thoughts are mine.
