10   These ideas are for today's review:
11   W-pI.60.1. (46) God is the Love in which I forgive. 
12   2 God does not forgive because He has never condemned. 3 The blameless cannot blame, 
13   and those who have accepted their innocence see nothing to forgive. 4 Yet forgiveness is 
14   the means by which I will recognize my innocence. 5 It is the reflection of God's Love on 
15   earth. 6 It will bring me near enough to Heaven that the Love of God can reach down to me 
16   and raise me up to Him.
17   
18   W-pI.60.2. (47) God is the strength in which I trust. 
19   2 It is not my own strength through which I forgive. 3 It is through the strength of 
20   God in me, which I am remembering as I forgive. 4 As I begin to see, I recognize His 
21   reflection on earth. 5 I forgive all things because I feel the stirring of His strength in me. 6 
22   And I begin to remember the Love I chose to forget, but which has not forgotten me.
23   
24   W-pI.60.3. (48) There is nothing to fear. 
25   2 How safe the world will look to me when I can see it! 3 It will not look anything 
26   like what I imagine I see now. 4 Everyone and everything I see will lean toward me to bless
27   me. 5 I will recognize in everyone my dearest Friend. 6 What could there be to fear in 
28   a world that I have forgiven, and that has forgiven me?
29   
30   W-pI.60.4. (49) God's Voice speaks to me all through the day. 
31   2 There is not a moment in which God's Voice ceases to call on my forgiveness to save 
32   me. 3 There is not a moment in which His Voice fails to direct my thoughts, guide my 
33   actions and lead my feet. 4 I am walking steadily on toward truth. 5 There is nowhere else I 
34   can go, because God's Voice is the only Voice and the only Guide that has been given to 
35   His Son.
36   
37   W-pI.60.5. (50) I am sustained by the Love of God. 
38   2 As I listen to God's Voice, I am sustained by His Love. 3 As I open my eyes, His Love
39   lights up the world for me to see. 4 As I forgive, His Love reminds me that His Son is 
40   sinless. 5 And as I look upon the world with the vision He has given me, I remember that I am 
41   His Son.
