24   LESSON 63.
25   
26   The light of the world brings peace to every mind through my forgiveness.
27   W-pI.63.1. How holy are you who have the power to bring peace to every mind! 2 How 
28   blessed are you who can learn to recognize the means for letting this be done through you! 3 
29   What purpose could you have that would bring you greater happiness?
30   W-pI.63.2. You are indeed the light of the world with such a function. 2 The Son of God
31   looks to you for his redemption. 3 It is yours to give him, for it belongs to you. 4 
32   Accept no trivial purpose or meaningless desire in its place, or you will forget your 
33   function and leave the Son of God in hell. 5 This is no idle request that is being asked of you.
34    6 You are being asked to accept salvation that it may be yours to give.
35   W-pI.63.3. Recognizing the importance of this function, we will be happy to remember it
36   very often today. 2 We will begin the day by acknowledging it, and close the day with 
37   the thought of it in our awareness. 3 And throughout the day we will repeat this as often 
38   as we can: 
39   
40   4 The light of the world brings peace to every mind through my forgiveness. 5 I am the 
41   means God has appointed for the salvation of the world.
42   
43   W-pI.63.4. If you close your eyes, you will probably find it easier to let the related 
44   thoughts come to you in the minute or two that you should devote to considering this. 2 Do not,
45   however, wait for such an opportunity. 3 No chance should be lost for reinforcing 
46   today's idea. 4 Remember that God's Son looks to you for his salvation. 5 And Who but your 
47   Self must be His Son?
