0458
 1   LESSON 64.
 2   
 3   Let me not forget my function.
 4   W-pI.64.1. Today's idea is merely another way of saying "Let me not wander into 
 5   temptation." 2 The purpose of the world you see is to obscure your function of forgiveness, and 
 6   provide you with a justification for forgetting it. 3 It is the temptation to abandon God and 
 7   His Son by taking on a physical appearance. 4 It is this the body's eyes look upon.
 8   W-pI.64.2. Nothing the body's eyes seem to see can be anything but a form of temptation,
 9    since this was the purpose of the body itself. 2 Yet we have learned that the Holy 
10   Spirit has another use for all the illusions you have made, and therefore He sees another 
11   purpose in them. 3 To the Holy Spirit, the world is a place where you learn to forgive 
12   yourself what you think of as your sins. 4 In this perception, the physical appearance of 
13   temptation becomes the spiritual recognition of salvation.
14   W-pI.64.3. To review our last few lessons, your function here is to be the light of the
15   world, a function given you by God. 2 It is only the arrogance of the ego that leads 
16   you to question this, and only the fear of the ego that induces you to regard yourself as 
17   unworthy of the task assigned to you by God Himself. 3 The world's salvation awaits your 
18   forgiveness, because through it does the Son of God escape from all illusions, and thus from all 
19   temptation. 4 The Son of God is you.
20   W-pI.64.4. Only by fulfilling the function given you by God will you be happy. 2 That 
21   is because your function is to be happy by using the means by which happiness becomes 
22   inevitable. 3 There is no other way. 4 Therefore, every time you choose whether or not to fulfill
23   your function, you are really choosing whether or not to be happy.
24   W-pI.64.5. Let us remember this today. 2 Let us remind ourselves of it in the morning 
25   and again at night, and all through the day as well. 3 Prepare yourself in advance for all
26   the decisions you will make today by remembering they are all really very simple. 4 
27   Each one will lead to happiness or unhappiness. 5 Can such a simple decision really be 
28   difficult to make? 6 Let not the form of the decision deceive you. 7 Complexity of form does not
29   imply complexity of content. 8 It is impossible that any decision on earth can have a 
30   content different from just this one simple choice. 9 That is the only choice the Holy Spirit 
31   sees. 10 Therefore it is the only choice there is.
32   W-pI.64.6. Today, then, let us practice with these thoughts: 
33   
34   2 Let me not forget my function. 
35   3 Let me not try to substitute mine for God's. 
36   4 Let me forgive and be happy. 
37   
38   5 At least once devote ten or fifteen minutes today to reflecting on this with closed 
39   eyes. 6 Related thoughts will come to help you, if you remember the crucial importance of 
40   your function to you and to the world.
41   W-pI.64.7. In the frequent applications of today's idea throughout the day, devote 
42   several minutes to reviewing these thoughts, and then thinking about them and about nothing 
43   else. 2 This will be difficult, at first particularly, since you are not proficient in the 
44   mind discipline that it requires. 3 You may need to repeat "Let me not forget my function" 
45   quite often to help you concentrate.
46   W-pI.64.8. Two forms of shorter practice periods are required. 2 At times, do the 
47   exercises with your eyes closed, trying to concentrate on the thoughts you are using. 3 At other
48   times, keep your eyes open after reviewing the thoughts, and then look slowly and 
49   unselectively around you, telling yourself: 
50   
0459
 1   4 This is the world it is my function to save.
 2   
 3   
 4   
 5   LESSON 65.
 6   
 7   My only function is the one God gave me.
 8   W-pI.65.1. The idea for today reaffirms your commitment to salvation. 2 It also reminds
 9   you that you have no function other than that. 3 Both these thoughts are obviously 
10   necessary for a total commitment. 4 Salvation cannot be the only purpose you hold while you 
11   still cherish others. 5 The full acceptance of salvation as your only function necessarily 
12   entails two phases; the recognition of salvation as your function, and the relinquishment of 
13   all the other goals you have invented for yourself.
14   W-pI.65.2. This is the only way in which you can take your rightful place among the 
15   saviors of the world. 2 This is the only way in which you can say and mean, "My only function 
16   is the one God gave me." 3 This is the only way in which you can find peace of mind.
17   W-pI.65.3. Today, and for a number of days to follow, set aside ten to fifteen minutes 
18   for a more sustained practice period, in which you try to understand and accept what the 
19   idea for the day really means. 2 Today's idea offers you escape from all your perceived 
20   difficulties. 3 It places the key to the door of peace, which you have closed upon yourself, in 
21   your own hands. 4 It gives you the answer to all the searching you have done since time 
22   began.
23   W-pI.65.4. Try, if possible, to undertake the daily extended practice periods at 
24   approximately the same time each day. 2 Try, also, to determine this time in advance, and then 
25   adhere to it as closely as possible. 3 The purpose of this is to arrange your day so that you
26   have set apart the time for God, as well as for all the trivial purposes and goals you 
27   will pursue. 4 This is part of the long-range disciplinary training your mind needs, so 
28   that the Holy Spirit can use it consistently for the purpose He shares with you.
29   W-pI.65.5. For the longer practice period, begin by reviewing the idea for the day. 2 
30   Then close your eyes, repeat the idea to yourself once again, and watch your mind carefully
31   to catch whatever thoughts cross it. 3 At first, make no attempt to concentrate only on
32   thoughts related to the idea for the day. 4 Rather, try to uncover each thought that 
33   arises to interfere with it. 5 Note each one as it comes to you, with as little involvement 
34   or concern as possible, dismissing each one by telling yourself: 
35   
36   6 This thought reflects a goal that is preventing me from accepting my only function.
37   
38   W-pI.65.6. After a while, interfering thoughts will become harder to find. 2 Try, 
39   however, to continue a minute or so longer, attempting to catch a few of the idle thoughts 
40   that escaped your attention before, but do not strain or make undue effort in doing this. 3
41   Then tell yourself: 
42   
43   4 On this clean slate let my true function be written for me. 
44   
45   5 You need not use these exact words, but try to get the sense of being willing to have
46   your illusions of purpose be replaced by truth.
47   W-pI.65.7. Finally, repeat the idea for today once more, and devote the rest of the 
48   practice period to trying to focus on its importance to you, the relief its acceptance will 
49   bring you by resolving your conflicts once and for all, and the extent to which you really 
50   want salvation in spite of your own foolish ideas to the contrary.
0460
 1   W-pI.65.8. In the shorter practice periods, which should be undertaken at least once an
 2   hour, use this form in applying today's idea: 
 3   
 4   2 My only function is the one God gave me. 3 I want no other and I have no other. 
 5   
 6   4 Sometimes close your eyes as you practice this, and sometimes keep them open and look
 7   about you. 5 It is what you see now that will be totally changed when you accept 
 8   today's idea completely.
