37   LESSON 69.
38   
39   My grievances hide the light of the world in me.
40   W-pI.69.1. No one can look upon what your grievances conceal. 2 Because your grievances
41   are hiding the light of the world in you, everyone stands in darkness, and you beside 
42   him. 3 But as the veil of your grievances is lifted, you are released with him. 4 Share 
43   your salvation now with him who stood beside you when you were in hell. 5 He is your 
44   brother in the light of the world that saves you both.
45   W-pI.69.2. Today let us make another real attempt to reach the light in you. 2 Before 
46   we undertake this in our more extended practice period, let us devote several minutes to 
47   thinking about what we are trying to do. 3 We are literally attempting to get in touch with the
48   salvation of the world. 4 We are trying to see past the veil of darkness that keeps it 
49   concealed. 5 We are trying to let the veil be lifted, and to see the tears of God's Son 
50   disappear in the sunlight.
0464
 1   W-pI.69.3. Let us begin our longer practice period today with the full realization that
 2   this is so, and with real determination to reach what is dearer to us than all else. 2 
 3   Salvation is our only need. 3 There is no other purpose here, and no other function to fulfill. 
 4   4 Learning salvation is our only goal. 5 Let us end the ancient search today by finding 
 5   the light in us, and holding it up for everyone who searches with us to look upon and 
 6   rejoice.
 7   W-pI.69.4. Very quietly now, with your eyes closed, try to let go of all the content 
 8   that generally occupies your consciousness. 2 Think of your mind as a vast circle, 
 9   surrounded by a layer of heavy, dark clouds. 3 You can see only the clouds because you seem to be
10   standing outside the circle and quite apart from it.
11   W-pI.69.5. From where you stand, you can see no reason to believe there is a brilliant 
12   light hidden by the clouds. 2 The clouds seem to be the only reality. 3 They seem to be all 
13   there is to see. 4 Therefore, you do not attempt to go through them and past them, which is 
14   the only way in which you would be really convinced of their lack of substance. 5 We will 
15   make this attempt today.
16   W-pI.69.6. After you have thought about the importance of what you are trying to do for
17   yourself and the world, try to settle down in perfect stillness, remembering only how 
18   much you want to reach the light in you today,--now! 2 Determine to go past the clouds. 3 
19   Reach out and touch them in your mind. 4 Brush them aside with your hand; feel them resting 
20   on your cheeks and forehead and eyelids as you go through them. 5 Go on; clouds cannot 
21   stop you.
22   W-pI.69.7. If you are doing the exercises properly, you will begin to feel a sense of 
23   being lifted up and carried ahead. 2 Your little effort and small determination call on the 
24   power of the universe to help you, and God Himself will raise you from darkness into light. 
25   3 You are in accord with His Will. 4 You cannot fail because your will is His.
26   W-pI.69.8. Have confidence in your Father today, and be certain that He has heard you 
27   and answered you. 2 You may not recognize His answer yet, but you can indeed be sure that 
28   it is given you and you will yet receive it. 3 Try, as you attempt to go through the 
29   clouds to the light, to hold this confidence in your mind. 4 Try to remember that you are at 
30   last joining your will to God's. 5 Try to keep the thought clearly in mind that what you 
31   undertake with God must succeed. 6 Then let the power of God work in you and through you, that 
32   His Will and yours be done.
33   W-pI.69.9. In the shorter practice periods, which you will want to do as often as 
34   possible in view of the importance of today's idea to you and your happiness, remind yourself 
35   that your grievances are hiding the light of the world from your awareness. 2 Remind 
36   yourself also that you are not searching for it alone, and that you do know where to look for 
37   it. 3 Say, then: 
38   
39   4 My grievances hide the light of the world in me. 5 I cannot see what I have hidden. 6
40   Yet I want to let it be revealed to me, for my salvation and the salvation of the world.
41   
42   
43   7 Also, be sure to tell yourself: 
44   
45   8 If I hold this grievance the light of the world will be hidden from me, 
46   
47   if you are tempted to hold anything against anyone today.
