11   LESSON 75.
12   
13   The light has come.
14   W-pI.75.1. The light has come. 2 You are healed and you can heal. 3 The light has come.
15   4 You are saved and you can save. 5 You are at peace, and you bring peace with you 
16   wherever you go. 6 Darkness and turmoil and death have disappeared. 7 The light has come.
17   W-pI.75.2. Today we celebrate the happy ending to your long dream of disaster. 2 There 
18   are no dark dreams now. 3 The light has come. 4 Today the time of light begins for you and
19   everyone. 5 It is a new era, in which a new world is born. 6 The old one has left no 
20   trace upon it in its passing. 7 Today we see a different world, because the light has come.
21   W-pI.75.3. Our exercises for today will be happy ones, in which we offer thanks for the
22   passing of the old and the beginning of the new. 2 No shadows from the past remain to 
23   darken our sight and hide the world forgiveness offers us. 3 Today we will accept the new 
24   world as what we want to see. 4 We will be given what we desire. 5 We will to see the light;
25   the light has come.
26   W-pI.75.4. Our longer practice periods will be devoted to looking at the world that our
27   forgiveness shows us. 2 This is what we want to see, and only this. 3 Our single 
28   purpose makes our goal inevitable. 4 Today the real world rises before us in gladness, to be 
29   seen at last. 5 Sight is given us, now that the light has come.
30   W-pI.75.5. We do not want to see the ego's shadow on the world today. 2 We see the 
31   light, and in it we see Heaven's reflection lie across the world. 3 Begin the longer 
32   practice periods by telling yourself the glad tidings of your release: 
33   
34   4 The light has come. 5 I have forgiven the world.
35   
36   W-pI.75.6. Dwell not upon the past today. 2 Keep a completely open mind, washed of all 
37   past ideas and clean of every concept you have made. 3 You have forgiven the world today. 4
38   You can look upon it now as if you never saw it before. 5 You do not know yet what it 
39   looks like. 6 You merely wait to have it shown to you. 7 While you wait, repeat several 
40   times, slowly and in complete patience: 
41   
42   8 The light has come. 9 I have forgiven the world.
43   
44   W-pI.75.7. Realize that your forgiveness entitles you to vision. 2 Understand that the 
45   Holy Spirit never fails to give the gift of sight to the forgiving. 3 Believe He will not 
46   fail you now. 4 You have forgiven the world. 5 He will be with you as you watch and wait. 6
47   He will show you what true vision sees. 7 It is His Will, and you have joined with Him.
48   8 Wait patiently for Him. 9 He will be there. 10 The light has come. 11 You have 
49   forgiven the world.
50   W-pI.75.8. Tell Him you know you cannot fail because you trust in Him. 2 And tell 
0473
 1   yourself you wait in certainty to look upon the world He promised you. 3 From this time forth 
 2   you will see differently. 4 Today the light has come. 5 And you will see the world that 
 3   has been promised you since time began, and in which is the end of time ensured.
 4   W-pI.75.9. The shorter practice periods, too, will be joyful reminders of your release.
 5   2 Remind yourself every quarter of an hour or so that today is a time for special 
 6   celebration. 3 Give thanks for mercy and the Love of God. 4 Rejoice in the power of forgiveness to
 7   heal your sight completely. 5 Be confident that on this day there is a new beginning. 6
 8   Without the darkness of the past upon your eyes, you cannot fail to see today. 7 And 
 9   what you see will be so welcome that you will gladly extend today forever.
10   W-pI.75.10. Say, then: 
11   
12   2 The light has come. 3 I have forgiven the world. 
13   
14   4 Should you be tempted, say to anyone who seems to pull you back into darkness: 
15   
16   5 The light has come. 6 I have forgiven you.
17   
18   W-pI.75.11. We dedicate this day to the serenity in which God would have you be. 2 Keep
19   it in your awareness of yourself and see it everywhere today, as we celebrate the 
20   beginning of your vision and the sight of the real world, which has come to replace the 
21   unforgiven world you thought was real.
