25   LESSON 76.
26   
27   I am under no laws but God's.
28   W-pI.76.1. We have observed before how many senseless things have seemed to you to be 
29   salvation. 2 Each has imprisoned you with laws as senseless as itself. 3 You are not bound by 
30   them. 4 Yet to understand that this is so, you must first realize salvation lies not there.
31   5 While you would seek for it in things that have no meaning, you bind yourself to laws
32   that make no sense. 6 Thus do you seek to prove salvation is where it is not.
33   W-pI.76.2. Today we will be glad you cannot prove it. 2 For if you could, you would 
34   forever seek salvation where it is not, and never find it. 3 The idea for today tells you once
35   again how simple is salvation. 4 Look for it where it waits for you, and there it will 
36   be found. 5 Look nowhere else, for it is nowhere else.
37   W-pI.76.3. Think of the freedom in the recognition that you are not bound by all the 
38   strange and twisted laws you have set up to save you. 2 You really think that you would starve
39   unless you have stacks of green paper strips and piles of metal discs. 3 You really 
40   think a small round pellet or some fluid pushed into your veins through a sharpened needle 
41   will ward off disease and death. 4 You really think you are alone unless another body is 
42   with you.
43   W-pI.76.4. It is insanity that thinks these things. 2 You call them laws, and put them 
44   under different names in a long catalogue of rituals that have no use and serve no purpose. 
45   3 You think you must obey the "laws" of medicine, of economics and of health. 4 Protect 
46   the body, and you will be saved.
47   W-pI.76.5. These are not laws, but madness. 2 The body is endangered by the mind that 
48   hurts itself. 3 The body suffers just in order that the mind will fail to see it is the 
49   victim of itself. 4 The body's suffering is a mask the mind holds up to hide what really 
50   suffers. 5 It would not understand it is its own enemy; that it attacks itself and wants to 
0474
 1   die. 6 It is from this your "laws" would save the body. 7 It is for this you think you are
 2   a body.
 3   W-pI.76.6. There are no laws except the laws of God. 2 This needs repeating, over and 
 4   over, until you realize it applies to everything that you have made in opposition to God's 
 5   Will. 3 Your magic has no meaning. 4 What it is meant to save does not exist. 5 Only what 
 6   it is meant to hide will save you.
 7   W-pI.76.7. The laws of God can never be replaced. 2 We will devote today to rejoicing 
 8   that this is so. 3 It is no longer a truth that we would hide. 4 We realize instead it is a
 9   truth that keeps us free forever. 5 Magic imprisons, but the laws of God make free. 6 
10   The light has come because there are no laws but His.
11   W-pI.76.8. We will begin the longer practice periods today with a short review of the 
12   different kinds of "laws" we have believed we must obey. 2 These would include, for example, the
13   "laws" of nutrition, of immunization, of medication, and of the body's protection in 
14   innumerable ways. 3 Think further; you believe in the "laws" of friendship, of "good" 
15   relationships and reciprocity. 4 Perhaps you even think that there are laws which set forth what is 
16   God's and what is yours. 5 Many "religions" have been based on this. 6 They would not save 
17   but damn in Heaven's name. 7 Yet they are no more strange than other "laws" you hold must 
18   be obeyed to make you safe.
19   W-pI.76.9. There are no laws but God's. 2 Dismiss all foolish magical beliefs today, 
20   and hold your mind in silent readiness to hear the Voice that speaks the truth to you. 3 
21   You will be listening to One Who says there is no loss under the laws of God. 4 Payment is
22   neither given nor received. 5 Exchange cannot be made; there are no substitutes; and 
23   nothing is replaced by something else. 6 God's laws forever give and never take.
24   W-pI.76.10. Hear Him Who tells you this, and realize how foolish are the "laws" you 
25   thought upheld the world you thought you saw. 2 Then listen further. 3 He will tell you more. 
26   4 About the Love your Father has for you. 5 About the endless joy He offers you. 6 About
27   His yearning for His only Son, created as His channel for creation; denied to Him by 
28   his belief in hell.
29   W-pI.76.11. Let us today open God's channels to Him, and let His Will extend through us
30   to Him. 2 Thus is creation endlessly increased. 3 His Voice will speak of this to us, 
31   as well as of the joys of Heaven which His laws keep limitless forever. 4 We will repeat 
32   today's idea until we have listened and understood there are no laws but God's. 5 Then we will
33   tell ourselves, as a dedication with which the practice period concludes: 
34   
35   6 I am under no laws but God's.
36   
37   W-pI.76.12. We will repeat this dedication as often as possible today; at least four or
38   five times an hour, as well as in response to any temptation to experience ourselves as
39   subject to other laws throughout the day. 2 It is our statement of freedom from all 
40   danger and all tyranny. 3 It is our acknowledgment that God is our Father, and that His Son 
41   is saved.
