45   LESSON 77.
46   
47   I am entitled to miracles.
48   W-pI.77.1. You are entitled to miracles because of what you are. 2 You will receive 
49   miracles because of what God is. 3 And you will offer miracles because you are one with God. 4 
50   Again, how simple is salvation! 5 It is merely a statement of your true Identity. 6 It is 
0475
 1   this that we will celebrate today.
 2   W-pI.77.2. Your claim to miracles does not lie in your illusions about yourself. 2 It 
 3   does not depend on any magical powers you have ascribed to yourself, nor on any of the 
 4   rituals you have devised. 3 It is inherent in the truth of what you are. 4 It is implicit in 
 5   what God your Father is. 5 It was ensured in your creation, and guaranteed by the laws of 
 6   God.
 7   W-pI.77.3. Today we will claim the miracles which are your right, since they belong to 
 8   you. 2 You have been promised full release from the world you made. 3 You have been 
 9   assured that the Kingdom of God is within you, and can never be lost. 4 We ask no more than 
10   what belongs to us in truth. 5 Today, however, we will also make sure that we will not 
11   content ourselves with less.
12   W-pI.77.4. Begin the longer practice periods by telling yourself quite confidently that
13   you are entitled to miracles. 2 Closing your eyes, remind yourself that you are asking 
14   only for what is rightfully yours. 3 Remind yourself also that miracles are never taken 
15   from one and given to another, and that in asking for your rights, you are upholding the 
16   rights of everyone. 4 Miracles do not obey the laws of this world. 5 They merely follow from 
17   the laws of God.
18   W-pI.77.5. After this brief introductory phase, wait quietly for the assurance that 
19   your request is granted. 2 You have asked for the salvation of the world, and for your own.
20   3 You have requested that you be given the means by which this is accomplished. 4 You 
21   cannot fail to be assured in this. 5 You are but asking that the Will of God be done.
22   W-pI.77.6. In doing this, you do not really ask for anything. 2 You state a fact that 
23   cannot be denied. 3 The Holy Spirit cannot but assure you that your request is granted. 4 The
24   fact that you accepted must be so. 5 There is no room for doubt and uncertainty today. 
25   6 We are asking a real question at last. 7 The answer is a simple statement of a simple 
26   fact. 8 You will receive the assurance that you seek.
27   W-pI.77.7. Our shorter practice periods will be frequent, and will also be devoted to a
28   reminder of a simple fact. 2 Tell yourself often today: 
29   
30   3 I am entitled to miracles. 
31   
32   4 Ask for them whenever a situation arises in which they are called for. 5 You will 
33   recognize these situations. 6 And since you are not relying on yourself to find the miracle, you
34   are fully entitled to receive it whenever you ask.
35   W-pI.77.8. Remember, too, not to be satisfied with less than the perfect answer. 2 Be 
36   quick to tell yourself, should you be tempted: 
37   
38   3 I will not trade miracles for grievances. 4 I want only what belongs to me. 5 God has
39   established miracles as my right.
