43   LESSON 78.
44   
45   Let miracles replace all grievances.
46   W-pI.78.1. Perhaps it is not yet quite clear to you that each decision that you make is
47   one between a grievance and a miracle. 2 Each grievance stands like a dark shield of 
48   hate before the miracle it would conceal. 3 And as you raise it up before your eyes, you 
49   will not see the miracle beyond. 4 Yet all the while it waits for you in light, but you 
50   behold your grievances instead.
0476
 1   W-pI.78.2. Today we go beyond the grievances, to look upon the miracle instead. 2 We 
 2   will reverse the way you see by not allowing sight to stop before it sees. 3 We will not 
 3   wait before the shield of hate, but lay it down and gently lift our eyes in silence to 
 4   behold the Son of God.
 5   W-pI.78.3. He waits for you behind your grievances, and as you lay them down he will 
 6   appear in shining light where each one stood before. 2 For every grievance is a block to 
 7   sight, and as it lifts you see the Son of God where he has always been. 3 He stands in light,
 8    but you were in the dark. 4 Each grievance made the darkness deeper, and you could not
 9   see.
10   W-pI.78.4. Today we will attempt to see God's Son. 2 We will not let ourselves be blind
11   to him; we will not look upon our grievances. 3 So is the seeing of the world reversed,
12   as we look out toward truth, away from fear. 4 We will select one person you have used 
13   as target for your grievances, and lay the grievances aside and look at him. 5 Someone, 
14   perhaps, you fear and even hate; someone you think you love who angered you; someone you call 
15   a friend, but whom you see as difficult at times or hard to please, demanding, 
16   irritating or untrue to the ideal he should accept as his, according to the role you set for him.
17   W-pI.78.5. You know the one to choose; his name has crossed your mind already. 2 He 
18   will be the one of whom we ask God's Son be shown to you. 3 Through seeing him behind the 
19   grievances that you have held against him, you will learn that what lay hidden while you saw him 
20   not is there in everyone, and can be seen. 4 He who was enemy is more than friend when he 
21   is freed to take the holy role the Holy Spirit has assigned to him. 5 Let him be savior 
22   unto you today. 6 Such is his role in God your Father's plan.
23   W-pI.78.6. Our longer practice periods today will see him in this role. 2 You will 
24   attempt to hold him in your mind, first as you now consider him. 3 You will review his faults,
25   the difficulties you have had with him, the pain he caused you, his neglect, and all 
26   the little and the larger hurts he gave. 4 You will regard his body with its flaws and 
27   better points as well, and you will think of his mistakes and even of his "sins."
28   W-pI.78.7. Then let us ask of Him Who knows this Son of God in his reality and truth, 
29   that we may look on him a different way, and see our savior shining in the light of true 
30   forgiveness, given unto us. 2 We ask Him in the holy Name of God and of His Son, as holy as 
31   Himself: 
32   
33   3 Let me behold my savior in this one You have appointed as the one for me to ask to 
34   lead me to the holy light in which he stands, that I may join with him. 
35   
36   4 The body's eyes are closed, and as you think of him who grieved you, let your mind be
37   shown the light in him beyond your grievances.
38   W-pI.78.8. What you have asked for cannot be denied. 2 Your savior has been waiting 
39   long for this. 3 He would be free, and make his freedom yours. 4 The Holy Spirit leans from
40   him to you, seeing no separation in God's Son. 5 And what you see through Him will free
41   you both. 6 Be very quiet now, and look upon your shining savior. 7 No dark grievances 
42   obscure the sight of him. 8 You have allowed the Holy Spirit to express through him the role 
43   God gave Him that you might be saved.
44   W-pI.78.9. God thanks you for these quiet times today in which you laid your images 
45   aside, and looked upon the miracle of love the Holy Spirit showed you in their place. 2 The 
46   world and Heaven join in thanking you, for not one Thought of God but must rejoice as you 
47   are saved, and all the world with you.
48   W-pI.78.10. We will remember this throughout the day, and take the role assigned to us 
49   as part of God's salvation plan, and not our own. 2 Temptation falls away when we allow 
50   each one we meet to save us, and refuse to hide his light behind our grievances. 3 To 
0477
 1   everyone you meet, and to the ones you think of or remember from the past, allow the role of 
 2   savior to be given, that you may share it with him. 4 For you both, and all the sightless 
 3   ones as well, we pray: 
 4   
 5   5 Let miracles replace all grievances.
 6   
 7   
 8   
 9   LESSON 79.
10   
11   Let me recognize the problem so it can be solved.
12   W-pI.79.1. A problem cannot be solved if you do not know what it is. 2 Even if it is 
13   really solved already you will still have the problem, because you will not recognize that it
14   has been solved. 3 This is the situation of the world. 4 The problem of separation, 
15   which is really the only problem, has already been solved. 5 Yet the solution is not 
16   recognized because the problem is not recognized.
17   W-pI.79.2. Everyone in this world seems to have his own special problems. 2 Yet they 
18   are all the same, and must be recognized as one if the one solution that solves them all 
19   is to be accepted. 3 Who can see that a problem has been solved if he thinks the problem 
20   is something else? 4 Even if he is given the answer, he cannot see its relevance.
21   W-pI.79.3. That is the position in which you find yourself now. 2 You have the answer, 
22   but you are still uncertain about what the problem is. 3 A long series of different 
23   problems seems to confront you, and as one is settled the next one and the next arise. 4 There 
24   seems to be no end to them. 5 There is no time in which you feel completely free of problems
25   and at peace.
26   W-pI.79.4. The temptation to regard problems as many is the temptation to keep the 
27   problem of separation unsolved. 2 The world seems to present you with a vast number of 
28   problems, each requiring a different answer. 3 This perception places you in a position in 
29   which your problem solving must be inadequate, and failure is inevitable.
30   W-pI.79.5. No one could solve all the problems the world appears to hold. 2 They seem 
31   to be on so many levels, in such varying forms and with such varied content, that they 
32   confront you with an impossible situation. 3 Dismay and depression are inevitable as you regard
33   them. 4 Some spring up unexpectedly, just as you think you have resolved the previous 
34   ones. 5 Others remain unsolved under a cloud of denial, and rise to haunt you from time to 
35   time, only to be hidden again but still unsolved.
36   W-pI.79.6. All this complexity is but a desperate attempt not to recognize the problem,
37   and therefore not to let it be resolved. 2 If you could recognize that your only 
38   problem is separation, no matter what form it takes, you could accept the answer because you 
39   would see its relevance. 3 Perceiving the underlying constancy in all the problems that seem
40   to confront you, you would understand that you have the means to solve them all. 4 And 
41   you would use the means, because you recognize the problem.
42   W-pI.79.7. In our longer practice periods today we will ask what the problem is, and 
43   what is the answer to it. 2 We will not assume that we already know. 3 We will try to free 
44   our minds of all the many different kinds of problems we think we have. 4 We will try to 
45   realize that we have only one problem, which we have failed to recognize. 5 We will ask what 
46   it is, and wait for the answer. 6 We will be told. 7 Then we will ask for the solution to
47   it. 8 And we will be told.
48   W-pI.79.8. The exercises for today will be successful to the extent to which you do not
49   insist on defining the problem. 2 Perhaps you will not succeed in letting all your 
50   preconceived notions go, but that is not necessary. 3 All that is necessary is to entertain some 
0478
 1   doubt about the reality of your version of what your problems are. 4 You are trying to 
 2   recognize that you have been given the answer by recognizing the problem, so that the problem 
 3   and the answer can be brought together and you can be at peace.
 4   W-pI.79.9. The shorter practice periods for today will not be set by time, but by need.
 5   2 You will see many problems today, each one calling for an answer. 3 Our efforts will 
 6   be directed toward recognizing that there is only one problem and one answer. 4 In this 
 7   recognition are all problems resolved. 5 In this recognition there is peace.
 8   W-pI.79.10. Be not deceived by the form of problems today. 2 Whenever any difficulty 
 9   seems to rise, tell yourself quickly: 
10   
11   3 Let me recognize this problem so it can be solved. 
12   
13   4 Then try to suspend all judgment about what the problem is. 5 If possible, close your
14   eyes for a moment and ask what it is. 6 You will be heard and you will be answered.
15   
16   
17   
18   LESSON 80.
19   
20   Let me recognize my problems have been solved.
21   W-pI.80.1. If you are willing to recognize your problems, you will recognize that you 
22   have no problems. 2 Your one central problem has been answered, and you have no other. 3 
23   Therefore, you must be at peace. 4 Salvation thus depends on recognizing this one problem, and 
24   understanding that it has been solved. 5 One problem, one solution. 6 Salvation is accomplished. 7 
25   Freedom from conflict has been given you. 8 Accept that fact, and you are ready to take your 
26   rightful place in God's plan for salvation.
27   W-pI.80.2. Your only problem has been solved! 2 Repeat this over and over to yourself 
28   today, with gratitude and conviction. 3 You have recognized your only problem, opening the 
29   way for the Holy Spirit to give you God's answer. 4 You have laid deception aside, and 
30   seen the light of truth. 5 You have accepted salvation for yourself by bringing the problem
31   to the answer. 6 And you can recognize the answer, because the problem has been 
32   identified.
33   W-pI.80.3. You are entitled to peace today. 2 A problem that has been resolved cannot 
34   trouble you. 3 Only be certain you do not forget that all problems are the same. 4 Their many 
35   forms will not deceive you while you remember this. 5 One problem, one solution. 6 Accept 
36   the peace this simple statement brings.
37   W-pI.80.4. In our longer practice periods today, we will claim the peace that must be 
38   ours when the problem and the answer have been brought together. 2 The problem must be gone,
39    because God's answer cannot fail. 3 Having recognized one, you have recognized the 
40   other. 4 The solution is inherent in the problem. 5 You are answered, and have accepted the 
41   answer. 6 You are saved.
42   W-pI.80.5. Now let the peace that your acceptance brings be given you. 2 Close your 
43   eyes, and receive your reward. 3 Recognize that your problems have been solved. 4 Recognize
44   that you are out of conflict; free and at peace. 5 Above all, remember that you have 
45   one problem, and that the problem has one solution. 6 It is in this that the simplicity of
46   salvation lies. 7 It is because of this that it is guaranteed to work.
47   W-pI.80.6. Assure yourself often today that your problems have been solved. 2 Repeat 
48   the idea with deep conviction, as frequently as possible. 3 And be particularly sure to 
49   apply the idea for today to any specific problem that may arise. 4 Say quickly: 
50   
0479
 1   5 Let me recognize this problem has been solved.
 2   
 3   W-pI.80.7. Let us be determined not to collect grievances today. 2 Let us be determined
 4   to be free of problems that do not exist. 3 The means is simple honesty. 4 Do not 
 5   deceive yourself about what the problem is, and you must recognize it has been solved.
 6   
