48   W-pI.83.1. (65) My only function is the one God gave me. 
49   2 I have no function but the one God gave me. 3 This recognition releases me from all 
50   conflict, because it means I cannot have conflicting goals. 4 With one purpose only, I am 
0481
 1   always certain what to do, what to say and what to think. 5 All doubt must disappear as I 
 2   acknowledge that my only function is the one God gave me.
 3   W-pI.83.2. More specific applications of this idea might take these forms: 
 4   
 5   2 My perception of this does not change my function. 
 6   3 This does not give me a function other than the one God gave me. 
 7   4 Let me not use this to justify a function God did not give me.
 8   
 9   
10   W-pI.83.3. (66) My happiness and my function are one. 
11   2 All things that come from God are one. 3 They come from Oneness, and must be received
12   as one. 4 Fulfilling my function is my happiness because both come from the same Source.
13    5 And I must learn to recognize what makes me happy, if I would find happiness.
14   W-pI.83.4. Some useful forms for specific applications of this idea are: 
15   
16   2 This cannot separate my happiness from my function. 
17   3 The oneness of my happiness and my function remains wholly unaffected by this. 
18   4 Nothing, including this, can justify the illusion of happiness apart from my function.
