 3   Today's review will cover these ideas:
 4   W-pI.85.1. (69) My grievances hide the light of the world in me. 
 5   2 My grievances show me what is not there, and hide from me what I would see. 3 
 6   Recognizing this, what do I want my grievances for? 4 They keep me in darkness and hide the light.
 7   5 Grievances and light cannot go together, but light and vision must be joined for me 
 8   to see. 6 To see, I must lay grievances aside. 7 I want to see, and this will be the 
 9   means by which I will succeed.
