45   
46   W-pI.86.3. (72) Holding grievances is an attack on God's plan for salvation. 
47   2 Holding grievances is an attempt to prove that God's plan for salvation will not work.
48    3 Yet only His plan will work. 4 By holding grievances, I am therefore excluding my 
49   only hope of salvation from my awareness. 5 I would no longer defeat my own best interests 
50   in this insane way. 6 I would accept God's plan for salvation, and be happy.
0483
 1   W-pI.86.4. Specific applications for this idea might be in these forms: 
