41   2 In choosing salvation rather than attack, I merely choose to recognize what is 
42   already there. 3 Salvation is a decision made already. 4 Attack and grievances are not there 
43   to choose. 5 That is why I always choose between truth and illusion; between what is 
44   there and what is not. 6 The light has come. 7 I can but choose the light, for it has no 
45   alternative. 8 It has replaced the darkness, and the darkness has gone.
46   W-pI.88.2. These would prove useful forms for specific applications of this idea: 
