26   LESSON 91.
27   
28   Miracles are seen in light.
29   W-pI.91.1. It is important to remember that miracles and vision necessarily go together.
30    2 This needs repeating, and frequent repeating. 3 It is a central idea in your new 
31   thought system, and the perception that it produces. 4 The miracle is always there. 5 Its 
32   presence is not caused by your vision; its absence is not the result of your failure to see. 6 
33   It is only your awareness of miracles that is affected. 7 You will see them in the light;
34   you will not see them in the dark.
35   W-pI.91.2. To you, then, light is crucial. 2 While you remain in darkness, the miracle 
36   remains unseen. 3 Thus you are convinced it is not there. 4 This follows from the premises 
37   from which the darkness comes. 5 Denial of light leads to failure to perceive it. 6 Failure
38   to perceive light is to perceive darkness. 7 The light is useless to you then, even 
39   though it is there. 8 You cannot use it because its presence is unknown to you. 9 And the 
40   seeming reality of the darkness makes the idea of light meaningless.
41   W-pI.91.3. To be told that what you do not see is there sounds like insanity. 2 It is 
42   very difficult to become convinced that it is insanity not to see what is there, and to see
43   what is not there instead. 3 You do not doubt that the body's eyes can see. 4 You do 
44   not doubt the images they show you are reality. 5 Your faith lies in the darkness, not the
45   light. 6 How can this be reversed? 7 For you it is impossible, but you are not alone in
46   this.
47   W-pI.91.4. Your efforts, however little they may be, have strong support. 2 Did you but
48   realize how great this strength, your doubts would vanish. 3 Today we will devote 
49   ourselves to the attempt to let you feel this strength. 4 When you have felt the strength in you,
50    which makes all miracles within your easy reach, you will not doubt. 5 The miracles 
0486
 1   your sense of weakness hides will leap into awareness as you feel the strength in you.
 2   W-pI.91.5. Three times today, set aside about ten minutes for a quiet time in which you
 3   try to leave your weakness behind. 2 This is accomplished very simply, as you instruct 
 4   yourself that you are not a body. 3 Faith goes to what you want, and you instruct your mind 
 5   accordingly. 4 Your will remains your teacher, and your will has all the strength to do what it 
 6   desires. 5 You can escape the body if you choose. 6 You can experience the strength in you.
 7   W-pI.91.6. Begin the longer practice periods with this statement of true cause and 
 8   effect relationships: 
 9   
10   2 Miracles are seen in light. 
11   3 The body's eyes do not perceive the light. 
12   4 But I am not a body. 5 What am I? 
13   
14   6 The question with which this statement ends is needed for our exercises today. 7 What
15   you think you are is a belief to be undone. 8 But what you really are must be revealed 
16   to you. 9 The belief you are a body calls for correction, being a mistake. 10 The truth 
17   of what you are calls on the strength in you to bring to your awareness what the mistake 
18   conceals.
19   W-pI.91.7. If you are not a body, what are you? 2 You need to be aware of what the Holy
20   Spirit uses to replace the image of a body in your mind. 3 You need to feel something 
21   to put your faith in, as you lift it from the body. 4 You need a real experience of 
22   something else, something more solid and more sure; more worthy of your faith, and really there.
23   W-pI.91.8. If you are not a body, what are you? 2 Ask this in honesty, and then devote 
24   several minutes to allowing your mistaken thoughts about your attributes to be corrected, and 
25   their opposites to take their place. 3 Say, for example: 
26   
27   4 I am not weak, but strong. 
28   5 I am not helpless, but all powerful. 
29   6 I am not limited, but unlimited. 
30   7 I am not doubtful, but certain. 
31   8 I am not an illusion, but a reality. 
32   9 I cannot see in darkness, but in light.
33   
34   W-pI.91.9. In the second phase of the exercise period, try to experience these truths 
35   about yourself. 2 Concentrate particularly on the experience of strength. 3 Remember that 
36   all sense of weakness is associated with the belief you are a body, a belief that is 
37   mistaken and deserves no faith. 4 Try to remove your faith from it, if only for a moment. 5 You
38   will be accustomed to keeping faith with the more worthy in you as we go along.
39   W-pI.91.10. Relax for the rest of the practice period, confident that your efforts, 
40   however meager, are fully supported by the strength of God and all His Thoughts. 2 It is from 
41   Them that your strength will come. 3 It is through Their strong support that you will feel 
42   the strength in you. 4 They are united with you in this practice period, in which you 
43   share a purpose like Their Own. 5 Theirs is the light in which you will see miracles, 
44   because Their strength is yours. 6 Their strength becomes your eyes, that you may see.
45   W-pI.91.11. Five or six times an hour, at reasonably regular intervals, remind yourself
46   that miracles are seen in light. 2 Also, be sure to meet temptation with today's idea. 
47   3 This form would be helpful for this special purpose: 
48   
49   4 Miracles are seen in light. 5 Let me not close my eyes because of this.
