 3   LESSON 92.
 4   
 5   Miracles are seen in light, and light and strength are one.
 6   W-pI.92.1. The idea for today is an extension of the previous one. 2 You do not think 
 7   of light in terms of strength, and darkness in terms of weakness. 3 That is because your 
 8   idea of what seeing means is tied up with the body and its eyes and brain. 4 Thus you 
 9   believe that you can change what you see by putting little bits of glass before your eyes. 5 
10   This is among the many magical beliefs that come from the conviction you are a body, and 
11   the body's eyes can see.
12   W-pI.92.2. You also believe the body's brain can think. 2 If you but understood the 
13   nature of thought, you could but laugh at this insane idea. 3 It is as if you thought you 
14   held the match that lights the sun and gives it all its warmth; or that you held the world 
15   within your hand, securely bound until you let it go. 4 Yet this is no more foolish than to 
16   believe the body's eyes can see; the brain can think.
17   W-pI.92.3. It is God's strength in you that is the light in which you see, as it is His
18   Mind with which you think. 2 His strength denies your weakness. 3 It is your weakness 
19   that sees through the body's eyes, peering about in darkness to behold the likeness of 
20   itself; the small, the weak, the sickly and the dying, those in need, the helpless and afraid,
21    the sad, the poor, the starving and the joyless. 4 These are seen through eyes that 
22   cannot see and cannot bless.
23   W-pI.92.4. Strength overlooks these things by seeing past appearances. 2 It keeps its 
24   steady gaze upon the light that lies beyond them. 3 It unites with light, of which it is a 
25   part. 4 It sees itself. 5 It brings the light in which your Self appears. 6 In darkness you
26   perceive a self that is not there. 7 Strength is the truth about you; weakness is an 
27   idol falsely worshipped and adored that strength may be dispelled, and darkness rule where 
28   God appointed that there should be light.
29   W-pI.92.5. Strength comes from truth, and shines with light its Source has given it; 
30   weakness reflects the darkness of its maker. 2 It is sick and looks on sickness, which is like 
31   itself. 3 Truth is a savior and can only will for happiness and peace for everyone. 4 It 
32   gives its strength to everyone who asks, in limitless supply. 5 It sees that lack in anyone 
33   would be a lack in all. 6 And so it gives its light that all may see and benefit as one. 7 
34   Its strength is shared, that it may bring to all the miracle in which they will unite in 
35   purpose and forgiveness and in love.
36   W-pI.92.6. Weakness, which looks in darkness, cannot see a purpose in forgiveness and 
37   in love. 2 It sees all others different from itself, and nothing in the world that it 
38   would share. 3 It judges and condemns, but does not love. 4 In darkness it remains to hide 
39   itself, and dreams that it is strong and conquering, a victor over limitations that but grow 
40   in darkness to enormous size.
41   W-pI.92.7. It fears and it attacks and hates itself, and darkness covers everything it 
42   sees, leaving its dreams as fearful as itself. 2 No miracles are here, but only hate. 3 It 
43   separates itself from what it sees, while light and strength perceive themselves as one. 4 The 
44   light of strength is not the light you see. 5 It does not change and flicker and go out. 6 
45   It does not shift from night to day, and back to darkness till the morning comes again.
46   W-pI.92.8. The light of strength is constant, sure as love, forever glad to give itself
47   away, because it cannot give but to itself. 2 No one can ask in vain to share its sight,
48    and none who enters its abode can leave without a miracle before his eyes, and 
49   strength and light abiding in his heart.
50   W-pI.92.9. The strength in you will offer you the light, and guide your seeing so you 
0488
 1   do not dwell on idle shadows that the body's eyes provide for self-deception. 2 Strength 
 2   and light unite in you, and where they meet, your Self stands ready to embrace you as Its 
 3   Own. 3 Such is the meeting place we try today to find and rest in, for the peace of God is
 4   where your Self, His Son, is waiting now to meet Itself again, and be as One.
 5   W-pI.92.10. Let us give twenty minutes twice today to join this meeting. 2 Let yourself
 6   be brought unto your Self. 3 Its strength will be the light in which the gift of sight 
 7   is given you. 4 Leave, then, the dark a little while today, and we will practice seeing 
 8   in the light, closing the body's eyes and asking truth to show us how to find the meeting
 9   place of self and Self, where light and strength are one.
10   W-pI.92.11. Morning and evening we will practice thus. 2 After the morning meeting, we 
11   will use the day in preparation for the time at night when we will meet again in trust. 3 
12   Let us repeat as often as we can the idea for today, and recognize that we are being 
13   introduced to sight, and led away from darkness to the light where only miracles can be perceived.
