18   LESSON 93.
19   
20   Light and joy and peace abide in me.
21   W-pI.93.1. You think you are the home of evil, darkness and sin. 2 You think if anyone 
22   could see the truth about you he would be repelled, recoiling from you as if from a 
23   poisonous snake. 3 You think if what is true about you were revealed to you, you would be struck
24   with horror so intense that you would rush to death by your own hand, living on after 
25   seeing this being impossible.
26   W-pI.93.2. These are beliefs so firmly fixed that it is difficult to help you see that 
27   they are based on nothing. 2 That you have made mistakes is obvious. 3 That you have sought
28   salvation in strange ways; have been deceived, deceiving and afraid of foolish 
29   fantasies and savage dreams; and have bowed down to idols made of dust,--all this is true by 
30   what you now believe.
31   W-pI.93.3. Today we question this, not from the point of view of what you think, but 
32   from a very different reference point, from which such idle thoughts are meaningless. 2 
33   These thoughts are not according to God's Will. 3 These weird beliefs He does not share with
34   you. 4 This is enough to prove that they are wrong, but you do not perceive that this 
35   is so.
36   W-pI.93.4. Why would you not be overjoyed to be assured that all the evil that you 
37   think you did was never done, that all your sins are nothing, that you are as pure and holy 
38   as you were created, and that light and joy and peace abide in you? 2 Your image of 
39   yourself cannot withstand the Will of God. 3 You think that this is death, but it is life. 4 
40   You think you are destroyed, but you are saved.
41   W-pI.93.5. The self you made is not the Son of God. 2 Therefore, this self does not 
42   exist at all. 3 And anything it seems to do and think means nothing. 4 It is neither bad nor
43   good. 5 It is unreal, and nothing more than that. 6 It does not battle with the Son of 
44   God. 7 It does not hurt him, nor attack his peace. 8 It has not changed creation, nor 
45   reduced eternal sinlessness to sin, and love to hate. 9 What power can this self you made 
46   possess, when it would contradict the Will of God?
47   W-pI.93.6. Your sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 2 Over and over this must be repeated,
48    until it is accepted. 3 It is true. 4 Your sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 5 Nothing
49   can touch it, or change what God created as eternal. 6 The self you made, evil and full
50   of sin, is meaningless. 7 Your sinlessness is guaranteed by God, and light and joy and 
0489
 1   peace abide in you.
 2   W-pI.93.7. Salvation requires the acceptance of but one thought;--you are as God 
 3   created you, not what you made of yourself. 2 Whatever evil you may think you did, you are as 
 4   God created you. 3 Whatever mistakes you made, the truth about you is unchanged. 4 
 5   Creation is eternal and unalterable. 5 Your sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 6 You are and 
 6   will forever be exactly as you were created. 7 Light and joy and peace abide in you because
 7   God put them there.
 8   W-pI.93.8. In our longer exercise periods today, which would be most profitable if done
 9   for the first five minutes of every waking hour, begin by stating the truth about your 
10   creation: 
11   
12   2 Light and joy and peace abide in me. 
13   3 My sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 
14   
15   4 Then put away your foolish self-images, and spend the rest of the practice period in 
16   trying to experience what God has given you, in place of what you have decreed for yourself.
17   W-pI.93.9. You are what God created or what you made. 2 One Self is true; the other is 
18   not there. 3 Try to experience the unity of your one Self. 4 Try to appreciate Its 
19   Holiness and the love from which It was created. 5 Try not to interfere with the Self which God
20   created as you, by hiding Its majesty behind the tiny idols of evil and sinfulness you 
21   have made to replace It. 6 Let It come into Its Own. 7 Here you are; This is You. 8 And 
22   light and joy and peace abide in you because this is so.
23   W-pI.93.10. You may not be willing or even able to use the first five minutes of each 
24   hour for these exercises. 2 Try, however, to do so when you can. 3 At least remember to 
25   repeat these thoughts each hour: 
26   
27   4 Light and joy and peace abide in me. 
28   5 My sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 
29   
30   6 Then try to devote at least a minute or so to closing your eyes and realizing that 
31   this is a statement of the truth about you.
32   W-pI.93.11. If a situation arises that seems to be disturbing, quickly dispel the 
33   illusion of fear by repeating these thoughts again. 2 Should you be tempted to become angry 
34   with someone, tell him silently: 
35   
36   3 Light and joy and peace abide in you. 
37   4 Your sinlessness is guaranteed by God. 
38   
39   5 You can do much for the world's salvation today. 6 You can do much today to bring you
40   closer to the part in salvation that God has assigned to you. 7 And you can do much 
41   today to bring the conviction to your mind that the idea for the day is true indeed.
