46   
47   I am as God created me.
48   W-pI.94.1. Today we continue with the one idea which brings complete salvation; the one
49   statement which makes all forms of temptation powerless; the one thought which renders 
50   the ego silent and entirely undone. 2 You are as God created you. 3 The sounds of this 
0490
 1   world are still, the sights of this world disappear, and all the thoughts that this world 
 2   ever held are wiped away forever by this one idea. 4 Here is salvation accomplished. 5 Here
 3   is sanity restored.
 4   W-pI.94.2. True light is strength, and strength is sinlessness. 2 If you remain as God 
 5   created you, you must be strong and light must be in you. 3 He Who ensured your sinlessness 
 6   must be the guarantee of strength and light as well. 4 You are as God created you. 5 
 7   Darkness cannot obscure the glory of God's Son. 6 You stand in light, strong in the sinlessness
 8   in which you were created, and in which you will remain throughout eternity.
 9   W-pI.94.3. Today we will again devote the first five minutes of each waking hour to the
10   attempt to feel the truth in you. 2 Begin these times of searching with these words: 
11   
12   3 I am as God created me. 
13   4 I am His Son eternally. 
14   
15   5 Now try to reach the Son of God in you. 6 This is the Self that never sinned, nor 
16   made an image to replace reality. 7 This is the Self that never left Its home in God to 
17   walk the world uncertainly. 8 This is the Self that knows no fear, nor could conceive of 
18   loss or suffering or death.
19   W-pI.94.4. Nothing is required of you to reach this goal except to lay all idols and 
20   self-images aside; go past the list of attributes, both good and bad, you have ascribed to 
21   yourself; and wait in silent expectancy for the truth. 2 God has Himself promised that it will 
22   be revealed to all who ask for it. 3 You are asking now. 4 You cannot fail because He 
23   cannot fail.
24   W-pI.94.5. If you do not meet the requirement of practicing for the first five minutes 
25   of every hour, at least remind yourself hourly: 
