39   LESSON 96.
40   
41   Salvation comes from my one Self.
42   W-pI.96.1. Although you are one Self, you experience yourself as two; as both good and 
43   evil, loving and hating, mind and body. 2 This sense of being split into opposites induces 
44   feelings of acute and constant conflict, and leads to frantic attempts to reconcile the 
45   contradictory aspects of this self-perception. 3 You have sought many such solutions, and none of 
46   them has worked. 4 The opposites you see in you will never be compatible. 5 But one exists.
47   W-pI.96.2. The fact that truth and illusion cannot be reconciled, no matter how you try,
48    what means you use and where you see the problem, must be accepted if you would be 
49   saved. 2 Until you have accepted this, you will attempt an endless list of goals you cannot 
50   reach; a senseless series of expenditures of time and effort, hopefulness and doubt, each 
0493
 1   one as futile as the one before, and failing as the next one surely will.
 2   W-pI.96.3. Problems that have no meaning cannot be resolved within the framework they 
 3   are set. 2 Two selves in conflict could not be resolved, and good and evil have no meeting
 4   place. 3 The self you made can never be your Self, nor can your Self be split in two, 
 5   and still be what It is and must forever be. 4 A mind and body cannot both exist. 5 Make 
 6   no attempt to reconcile the two, for one denies the other can be real. 6 If you are 
 7   physical, your mind is gone from your self-concept, for it has no place in which it could be 
 8   really part of you. 7 If you are spirit, then the body must be meaningless to your reality.
 9   W-pI.96.4. Spirit makes use of mind as means to find its Self expression. 2 And the 
10   mind which serves the spirit is at peace and filled with joy. 3 Its power comes from spirit,
11    and it is fulfilling happily its function here. 4 Yet mind can also see itself 
12   divorced from spirit, and perceive itself within a body it confuses with itself. 5 Without its 
13   function then it has no peace, and happiness is alien to its thoughts.
14   W-pI.96.5. Yet mind apart from spirit cannot think. 2 It has denied its Source of 
15   strength, and sees itself as helpless, limited and weak. 3 Dissociated from its function now, 
16   it thinks it is alone and separate, attacked by armies massed against itself and hiding 
17   in the body's frail support. 4 Now must it reconcile unlike with like, for this is what 
18   it thinks that it is for.
19   W-pI.96.6. Waste no more time on this. 2 Who can resolve the senseless conflicts which 
20   a dream presents? 3 What could the resolution mean in truth? 4 What purpose could it 
21   serve? 5 What is it for? 6 Salvation cannot make illusions real, nor solve a problem that 
22   does not exist. 7 Perhaps you hope it can. 8 Yet would you have God's plan for the release 
23   of His dear Son bring pain to him, and fail to set him free?
24   W-pI.96.7. Your Self retains Its Thoughts, and they remain within your mind and in the 
25   Mind of God. 2 The Holy Spirit holds salvation in your mind, and offers it the way to peace.
26    3 Salvation is a thought you share with God, because His Voice accepted it for you and
27   answered in your name that it was done. 4 Thus is salvation kept among the Thoughts 
28   your Self holds dear and cherishes for you.
29   W-pI.96.8. We will attempt today to find this thought, whose presence in your mind is 
30   guaranteed by Him Who speaks to you from your one Self. 2 Our hourly five-minute practicing will 
31   be a search for Him within your mind. 3 Salvation comes from this one Self through Him 
32   Who is the Bridge between your mind and It. 4 Wait patiently, and let Him speak to you 
33   about your Self, and what your mind can do, restored to It and free to serve Its Will.
34   W-pI.96.9. Begin with saying this: 
35   
36   2 Salvation comes from my one Self. 3 Its Thoughts are mine to use. 
37   
38   4 Then seek Its Thoughts, and claim them as your own. 5 These are your own real 
39   thoughts you have denied, and let your mind go wandering in a world of dreams, to find 
40   illusions in their place. 6 Here are your thoughts, the only ones you have. 7 Salvation is among
41   them; find it there.
42   W-pI.96.10. If you succeed, the thoughts that come to you will tell you you are saved, 
43   and that your mind has found the function that it sought to lose. 2 Your Self will welcome
44   it and give it peace. 3 Restored in strength, it will again flow out from spirit to the
45   spirit in all things created by the Spirit as Itself. 4 Your mind will bless all things.
46    5 Confusion done, you are restored, for you have found your Self.
47   W-pI.96.11. Your Self knows that you cannot fail today. 2 Perhaps your mind remains 
48   uncertain yet a little while. 3 Be not dismayed by this. 4 The joy your Self experiences It will
49   save for you, and it will yet be yours in full awareness. 5 Every time you spend five 
50   minutes of the hour seeking Him Who joins your mind and Self, you offer Him another treasure 
0494
 1   to be kept for you.
 2   W-pI.96.12. Each time today you tell your frantic mind salvation comes from your one 
 3   Self, you lay another treasure in your growing store. 2 And all of it is given everyone who
 4   asks for it, and will accept the gift. 3 Think, then, how much is given unto you to 
 5   give this day, that it be given you!
