 9   LESSON 97.
10   
11   I am spirit.
12   W-pI.97.1. Today's idea identifies you with your one Self. 2 It accepts no split 
13   identity, nor tries to weave opposing factors into unity. 3 It simply states the truth. 4 
14   Practice this truth today as often as you can, for it will bring your mind from conflict to the
15   quiet fields of peace. 5 No chill of fear can enter, for your mind has been absolved 
16   from madness, letting go illusions of a split identity.
17   W-pI.97.2. We state again the truth about your Self, the holy Son of God Who rests in 
18   you; whose mind has been restored to sanity. 2 You are the spirit lovingly endowed with 
19   all your Father's Love and peace and joy. 3 You are the spirit which completes Himself, 
20   and shares His function as Creator. 4 He is with you always, as you are with Him.
21   W-pI.97.3. Today we try to bring reality still closer to your mind. 2 Each time you 
22   practice, awareness is brought a little nearer at least; sometimes a thousand years or more are
23   saved. 3 The minutes which you give are multiplied over and over, for the miracle makes
24   use of time, but is not ruled by it. 4 Salvation is a miracle, the first and last; the 
25   first that is the last, for it is one.
26   W-pI.97.4. You are the spirit in whose mind abides the miracle in which all time stands
27   still; the miracle in which a minute spent in using these ideas becomes a time that has
28   no limit and that has no end. 2 Give, then, these minutes willingly, and count on Him 
29   Who promised to lay timelessness beside them. 3 He will offer all His strength to every 
30   little effort that you make. 4 Give Him the minutes which He needs today, to help you 
31   understand with Him you are the spirit that abides in Him, and that calls through His Voice to 
32   every living thing; offers His sight to everyone who asks; replaces error with the simple 
33   truth.
34   W-pI.97.5. The Holy Spirit will be glad to take five minutes of each hour from your 
35   hands, and carry them around this aching world where pain and misery appear to rule. 2 He 
36   will not overlook one open mind that will accept the healing gifts they bring, and He will 
37   lay them everywhere He knows they will be welcome. 3 And they will increase in healing 
38   power each time someone accepts them as his thoughts, and uses them to heal.
39   W-pI.97.6. Thus will each gift to Him be multiplied a thousandfold and tens of 
40   thousands more. 2 And when it is returned to you, it will surpass in might the little gift you 
41   gave as much as does the radiance of the sun outshine the tiny gleam a firefly makes an 
42   uncertain moment and goes out. 3 The steady brilliance of this light remains and leads you out 
43   of darkness, nor will you be able to forget the way again.
44   W-pI.97.7. Begin these happy exercises with the words the Holy Spirit speaks to you, 
45   and let them echo round the world through Him: 
46   
47   2 Spirit am I, a holy Son of God, free of all limits, safe and healed and whole, free 
48   to forgive, and free to save the world. 
