12   
13   I will accept my part in God's plan for salvation.
14   W-pI.98.1. Today is a day of special dedication. 2 We take a stand on but one side 
15   today. 3 We side with truth and let illusions go. 4 We will not vacillate between the two, 
16   but take a firm position with the One. 5 We dedicate ourselves to truth today, and to 
17   salvation as God planned it be. 6 We will not argue it is something else. 7 We will not seek for
18   it where it is not. 8 In gladness we accept it as it is, and take the part assigned to 
19   us by God.
20   W-pI.98.2. How happy to be certain! 2 All our doubts we lay aside today, and take our 
21   stand with certainty of purpose, and with thanks that doubt is gone and surety has come. 3 
22   We have a mighty purpose to fulfill, and have been given everything we need with which to
23   reach the goal. 4 Not one mistake stands in our way. 5 For we have been absolved from 
24   errors. 6 All our sins are washed away by realizing they were but mistakes.
25   W-pI.98.3. The guiltless have no fear, for they are safe and recognize their safety. 2 
26   They do not appeal to magic, nor invent escapes from fancied threats without reality. 3 
27   They rest in quiet certainty that they will do what it is given them to do. 4 They do not 
28   doubt their own ability because they know their function will be filled completely in the 
29   perfect time and place. 5 They took the stand which we will take today, that we may share 
30   their certainty and thus increase it by accepting it ourselves.
31   W-pI.98.4. They will be with us; all who took the stand we take today will gladly offer
32   us all that they learned and every gain they made. 2 Those still uncertain, too, will 
33   join with us, and, borrowing our certainty, will make it stronger still. 3 While those as 
34   yet unborn will hear the call we heard, and answer it when they have come to make their 
35   choice again. 4 We do not choose but for ourselves today.
36   W-pI.98.5. Is it not worth five minutes of your time each hour to be able to accept the
37   happiness that God has given you? 2 Is it not worth five minutes hourly to recognize 
38   your special function here? 3 Is not five minutes but a small request to make in terms of 
39   gaining a reward so great it has no measure? 4 You have made a thousand losing bargains at the
40   least.
41   W-pI.98.6. Here is an offer guaranteeing you your full release from pain of every kind,
42   and joy the world does not contain. 2 You can exchange a little of your time for peace 
43   of mind and certainty of purpose, with the promise of complete success. 3 And since time 
44   has no meaning, you are being asked for nothing in return for everything. 4 Here is a 
45   bargain that you cannot lose. 5 And what you gain is limitless indeed!
