11   LESSON 100.
12   
13   My part is essential to God's plan for salvation.
14   W-pI.100.1. Just as God's Son completes his Father, so your part in it completes your 
15   Father's plan. 2 Salvation must reverse the mad belief in separate thoughts and separate bodies,
16    which lead separate lives and go their separate ways. 3 One function shared by 
17   separate minds unites them in one purpose, for each one of them is equally essential to them 
18   all.
19   W-pI.100.2. God's Will for you is perfect happiness. 2 Why should you choose to go 
20   against His Will? 3 The part that He has saved for you to take in working out His plan is 
21   given you that you might be restored to what He wills. 4 This part is as essential to His 
22   plan as to your happiness. 5 Your joy must be complete to let His plan be understood by 
23   those to whom He sends you. 6 They will see their function in your shining face, and hear 
24   God calling to them in your happy laugh.
25   W-pI.100.3. You are indeed essential to God's plan. 2 Without your joy, His joy is 
26   incomplete. 3 Without your smile, the world cannot be saved. 4 While you are sad, the light that 
27   God Himself appointed as the means to save the world is dim and lusterless, and no one 
28   laughs because all laughter can but echo yours.
29   W-pI.100.4. You are indeed essential to God's plan. 2 Just as your light increases 
30   every light that shines in Heaven, so your joy on earth calls to all minds to let their 
31   sorrows go, and take their place beside you in God's plan. 3 God's messengers are joyous, and 
32   their joy heals sorrow and despair. 4 They are the proof that God wills perfect happiness 
33   for all who will accept their Father's gifts as theirs.
34   W-pI.100.5. We will not let ourselves be sad today. 2 For if we do, we fail to take the
35   part that is essential to God's plan, as well as to our vision. 3 Sadness is the sign 
36   that you would play another part, instead of what has been assigned to you by God. 4 Thus 
37   do you fail to show the world how great the happiness He wills for you. 5 And so you do 
38   not recognize that it is yours.
39   W-pI.100.6. Today we will attempt to understand joy is our function here. 2 If you are 
40   sad, your part is unfulfilled, and all the world is thus deprived of joy, along with you. 
41   3 God asks you to be happy, so the world can see how much He loves His Son, and wills no
42   sorrow rises to abate his joy; no fear besets him to disturb his peace. 4 You are God's
43   messenger today. 5 You bring His happiness to all you look upon; His peace to everyone 
44   who looks on you and sees His message in your happy face.
45   W-pI.100.7. We will prepare ourselves for this today, in our five-minute practice 
46   periods, by feeling happiness arise in us according to our Father's Will and ours. 2 Begin the
47   exercises with the thought today's idea contains. 3 Then realize your part is to be 
48   happy. 4 Only this is asked of you or anyone who wants to take his place among God's 
49   messengers. 5 Think what this means. 6 You have indeed been wrong in your belief that sacrifice 
50   is asked. 7 You but receive according to God's plan, and never lose or sacrifice or die.
0499
 1   W-pI.100.8. Now let us try to find that joy that proves to us and all the world God's 
