18   LESSON 101.
19   
20   God's Will for me is perfect happiness.
21   W-pI.101.1. Today we will continue with the theme of happiness. 2 This is a key idea in
22   understanding what salvation means. 3 You still believe it asks for suffering as 
23   penance for your "sins." 4 This is not so. 5 Yet you must think it so while you believe that 
24   sin is real, and that God's Son can sin.
25   W-pI.101.2. If sin is real, then punishment is just and cannot be escaped. 2 Salvation 
26   thus cannot be purchased but through suffering. 3 If sin is real, then happiness must be 
27   illusion, for they cannot both be true. 4 The sinful warrant only death and pain, and it is 
28   this they ask for. 5 For they know it waits for them, and it will seek them out and find 
29   them somewhere, sometime, in some form that evens the account they owe to God. 6 They would
30   escape Him in their fear. 7 And yet He will pursue, and they can not escape.
31   W-pI.101.3. If sin is real, salvation must be pain. 2 Pain is the cost of sin, and 
32   suffering can never be escaped, if sin is real. 3 Salvation must be feared, for it will kill, 
33   but slowly, taking everything away before it grants the welcome boon of death to victims 
34   who are little more than bones before salvation is appeased. 4 Its wrath is boundless, 
35   merciless, but wholly just.
36   W-pI.101.4. Who would seek out such savage punishment? 2 Who would not flee salvation, 
37   and attempt in every way he can to drown the Voice which offers it to him? 3 Why would he 
38   try to listen and accept Its offering? 4 If sin is real, its offering is death, and meted 
39   out in cruel form to match the vicious wishes in which sin is born. 5 If sin is real, 
40   salvation has become your bitter enemy, the curse of God upon you who have crucified His Son.
41   W-pI.101.5. You need the practice periods today. 2 The exercises teach sin is not real,
42   and all that you believe must come from sin will never happen, for it has no cause. 3 
43   Accept Atonement with an open mind, which cherishes no lingering belief that you have made a 
44   devil of God's Son. 4 There is no sin. 5 We practice with this thought as often as we can 
45   today, because it is the basis for today's idea.
46   W-pI.101.6. God's Will for you is perfect happiness because there is no sin, and 
47   suffering is causeless. 2 Joy is just, and pain is but the sign you have misunderstood yourself.
48   3 Fear not the Will of God. 4 But turn to it in confidence that it will set you free 
49   from all the consequences sin has wrought in feverish imagination. 5 Say: 
50   
0500
 1   6 God's Will for me is perfect happiness. 
 2   7 There is no sin; it has no consequence. 
 3   
 4   8 So should you start your practice periods, and then attempt again to find the joy 
 5   these thoughts will introduce into your mind.
 6   W-pI.101.7. Give these five minutes gladly, to remove the heavy load you lay upon 
 7   yourself with the insane belief that sin is real. 2 Today escape from madness. 3 You are set on
 8   freedom's road, and now today's idea brings wings to speed you on, and hope to go still
