50   LESSON 103.
0501
 1   
 2   God, being Love, is also happiness.
 3   W-pI.103.1. Happiness is an attribute of love. 2 It cannot be apart from it. 3 Nor can 
 4   it be experienced where love is not. 4 Love has no limits, being everywhere. 5 And 
 5   therefore joy is everywhere as well. 6 Yet can the mind deny that this is so, believing there 
 6   are gaps in love where sin can enter, bringing pain instead of joy. 7 This strange belief 
 7   would limit happiness by redefining love as limited, and introducing opposition in what has 
 8   no limit and no opposite.
 9   W-pI.103.2. Fear is associated then with love, and its results become the heritage of 
10   minds that think what they have made is real. 2 These images, with no reality in truth, bear
11   witness to the fear of God, forgetting being Love, He must be joy. 3 This basic error 
12   we will try again to bring to truth today, and teach ourselves: 
13   
14   4 God, being Love, is also happiness. 
15   5 To fear Him is to be afraid of joy. 
16   
17   6 Begin your periods of practicing today with this association, which corrects the 
18   false belief that God is fear. 7 It also emphasizes happiness belongs to you, because of 
19   what He is.
20   W-pI.103.3. Allow this one correction to be placed within your mind each waking hour 
21   today. 2 Then welcome all the happiness it brings as truth replaces fear, and joy becomes 
22   what you expect to take the place of pain. 3 God, being Love, it will be given you. 4 
23   Bolster this expectation frequently throughout the day, and quiet all your fears with this 
24   assurance, kind and wholly true: 
25   
26   5 God, being Love, is also happiness. 
27   6 And it is happiness I seek today. 
28   7 I cannot fail, because I seek the truth.
