32   LESSON 104.
33   
34   I seek but what belongs to me in truth.
35   W-pI.104.1. Today's idea continues with the thought that joy and peace are not but idle
36   dreams. 2 They are your right, because of what you are. 3 They come to you from God, 
37   Who cannot fail to give you what He wills. 4 Yet must there be a place made ready to 
38   receive His gifts. 5 They are not welcomed gladly by a mind that has instead received the 
39   gifts it made where His belong, as substitutes for them.
40   W-pI.104.2. Today we would remove all meaningless and self-made gifts which we have 
41   placed upon the holy altar where God's gifts belong. 2 His are the gifts that are our own in 
42   truth. 3 His are the gifts that we inherited before time was, and that will still be ours 
43   when time has passed into eternity. 4 His are the gifts that are within us now, for they 
44   are timeless. 5 And we need not wait to have them. 6 They belong to us today.
45   W-pI.104.3. Therefore, we choose to have them now, and know, in choosing them in place 
46   of what we made, we but unite our will with what God wills, and recognize the same as 
47   being one. 2 Our longer practice periods today, the hourly five minutes given truth for your
48   salvation, should begin with this: 
49   
50   3 I seek but what belongs to me in truth, And joy and peace are my inheritance. 
0502
 1   
 2   4 Then lay aside the conflicts of the world that offer other gifts and other goals made
 3   of illusions, witnessed to by them, and sought for only in a world of dreams.
 4   W-pI.104.4. All this we lay aside, and seek instead that which is truly ours, as we ask
 5   to recognize what God has given us. 2 We clear a holy place within our minds before His
 6   altar, where His gifts of peace and joy are welcome, and to which we come to find what 
 7   has been given us by Him. 3 We come in confidence today, aware that what belongs to us in 
 8   truth is what He gives. 4 And we would wish for nothing else, for nothing else belongs to us
 9   in truth.
10   W-pI.104.5. So do we clear the way for Him today by simply recognizing that His Will is
11   done already, and that joy and peace belong to us as His eternal gifts. 2 We will not 
12   let ourselves lose sight of them between the times we come to seek for them where He has 
13   laid them. 3 This reminder will we bring to mind as often as we can: 
