20   LESSON 105.
21   
22   God's peace and joy are mine.
23   W-pI.105.1. God's peace and joy are yours. 2 Today we will accept them, knowing they 
24   belong to us. 3 And we will try to understand these gifts increase as we receive them. 4 They
25   are not like to the gifts the world can give, in which the giver loses as he gives the 
26   gift; the taker is the richer by his loss. 5 Such are not gifts, but bargains made with 
27   guilt. 6 The truly given gift entails no loss. 7 It is impossible that one can gain because 
28   another loses. 8 This implies a limit and an insufficiency.
29   W-pI.105.2. No gift is given thus. 2 Such "gifts" are but a bid for a more valuable 
30   return; a loan with interest to be paid in full; a temporary lending, meant to be a pledge of
31   debt to be repaid with more than was received by him who took the gift. 3 This strange 
32   distortion of what giving means pervades all levels of the world you see. 4 It strips all meaning
33   from the gifts you give, and leaves you nothing in the ones you take.
34   W-pI.105.3. A major learning goal this course has set is to reverse your view of giving,
35    so you can receive. 2 For giving has become a source of fear, and so you would avoid 
36   the only means by which you can receive. 3 Accept God's peace and joy, and you will learn 
37   a different way of looking at a gift. 4 God's gifts will never lessen when they are 
38   given away. 5 They but increase thereby.
39   W-pI.105.4. As Heaven's peace and joy intensify when you accept them as God's gift to 
40   you, so does the joy of your Creator grow when you accept His joy and peace as yours. 2 
41   True giving is creation. 3 It extends the limitless to the unlimited, eternity to 
42   timelessness, and love unto itself. 4 It adds to all that is complete already, not in simple terms 
43   of adding more, for that implies that it was less before. 5 It adds by letting what 
44   cannot contain itself fulfill its aim of giving everything it has away, securing it forever 
45   for itself.
46   W-pI.105.5. Today accept God's peace and joy as yours. 2 Let Him complete Himself as He
47   defines completion. 3 You will understand that what completes Him must complete His Son
48   as well. 4 He cannot give through loss. 5 No more can you. 6 Receive His gift of joy 
49   and peace today, and He will thank you for your gift to Him.
50   W-pI.105.6. Today our practice periods will start a little differently. 2 Begin today 
0503
 1   by thinking of those brothers who have been denied by you the peace and joy that are 
 2   their right under the equal laws of God. 3 Here you denied them to yourself. 4 And here you 
 3   must return to claim them as your own.
 4   W-pI.105.7. Think of your "enemies" a little while, and tell each one, as he occurs to 
 5   you: 
 6   
 7   2 My brother, peace and joy I offer you, That I may have God's peace and joy as mine. 
 8   
 9   3 Thus you prepare yourself to recognize God's gifts to you, and let your mind be free 
10   of all that would prevent success today. 4 Now are you ready to accept the gift of peace 
11   and joy that God has given you. 5 Now are you ready to experience the joy and peace you 
12   have denied yourself. 6 Now you can say, "God's peace and joy are mine," for you have given
13   what you would receive.
14   W-pI.105.8. You must succeed today, if you prepare your mind as we suggest. 2 For you 
15   have let all bars to peace and joy be lifted up, and what is yours can come to you at last.
16   3 So tell yourself, "God's peace and joy are mine," and close your eyes a while, and 
17   let His Voice assure you that the words you speak are true.
18   W-pI.105.9. Spend your five minutes thus with Him each time you can today, but do not 
19   think that less is worthless when you cannot give Him more. 2 At least remember hourly to 
20   say the words which call to Him to give you what He wills to give, and wills you to 
21   receive. 3 Determine not to interfere today with what He wills. 4 And if a brother seems to 
22   tempt you to deny God's gift to him, see it as but another chance to let yourself receive 
23   the gifts of God as yours. 5 Then bless your brother thankfully, and say: 
24   
25   6 My brother, peace and joy I offer you, That I may have God's peace and joy as mine.
26   
27   
28   
29   LESSON 106.
30   
31   Let me be still and listen to the truth.
32   W-pI.106.1. If you will lay aside the ego's voice, however loudly it may seem to call, 
33   if you will not accept its petty gifts that give you nothing that you really want; if you
34   will listen with an open mind, that has not told you what salvation is; then you will 
35   hear the mighty Voice of truth, quiet in power, strong in stillness, and completely certain
36   in Its messages.
37   W-pI.106.2. Listen, and hear your Father speak to you through His appointed Voice, 
38   which silences the thunder of the meaningless, and shows the way to peace to those who 
39   cannot see. 2 Be still today and listen to the truth. 3 Be not deceived by voices of the dead,
40    which tell you they have found the source of life and offer it to you for your belief.
41   4 Attend them not, but listen to the truth.
42   W-pI.106.3. Be not afraid today to circumvent the voices of the world. 2 Walk lightly 
43   past their meaningless persuasion. 3 Hear them not. 4 Be still today and listen to the 
44   truth. 5 Go past all things which do not speak of Him Who holds your happiness within His 
45   Hand, held out to you in welcome and in love. 6 Hear only Him today, and do not wait to 
46   reach Him longer. 7 Hear one Voice today.
47   W-pI.106.4. Today the promise of God's Word is kept. 2 Hear and be silent. 3 He would 
48   speak to you. 4 He comes with miracles a thousand times as happy and as wonderful as those 
49   you ever dreamed or wished for in your dreams. 5 His miracles are true. 6 They will not 
50   fade when dreaming ends. 7 They end the dream instead; and last forever, for they come from
0504
 1   God to His dear Son, whose other name is you. 8 Prepare yourself for miracles today. 9 
 2   Today allow your Father's ancient pledge to you and all your brothers to be kept.
 3   W-pI.106.5. Hear Him today, and listen to the Word which lifts the veil that lies upon 
 4   the earth, and wakes all those who sleep and cannot see. 2 God calls to them through you. 
 5   3 He needs your voice to speak to them, for who could reach God's Son except his Father,
 6   calling through your Self? 4 Hear Him today, and offer Him your voice to speak to all 
 7   the multitude who wait to hear the Word that He will speak today.
 8   W-pI.106.6. Be ready for salvation. 2 It is here, and will today be given unto you. 3 
 9   And you will learn your function from the One Who chose it in your Father's Name for you. 
10   4 Listen today, and you will hear a Voice which will resound throughout the world 
11   through you. 5 The bringer of all miracles has need that you receive them first, and thus 
12   become the joyous giver of what you received.
13   W-pI.106.7. Thus does salvation start and thus it ends; when everything is yours and 
14   everything is given away, it will remain with you forever. 2 And the lesson has been learned. 3 
15   Today we practice giving, not the way you understand it now, but as it is. 4 Each hour's 
16   exercises should begin with this request for your enlightenment: 
17   
18   5 I will be still and listen to the truth. 
19   6 What does it mean to give and to receive?
20   
21   W-pI.106.8. Ask and expect an answer. 2 Your request is one whose answer has been 
22   waiting long to be received by you. 3 It will begin the ministry for which you came, and which
23   will free the world from thinking giving is a way to lose. 4 And so the world becomes 
24   ready to understand and to receive.
25   W-pI.106.9. Be still and listen to the truth today. 2 For each five minutes spent in 
26   listening, a thousand minds are opened to the truth and they will hear the holy Word you hear. 3
27   And when the hour is past, you will again release a thousand more who pause to ask that
28   truth be given them, along with you.
29   W-pI.106.10. Today the holy Word of God is kept through your receiving it to give away,
30   so you can teach the world what giving means by listening and learning it of Him. 2 Do 
31   not forget today to reinforce your choice to hear and to receive the Word by this reminder,
32    given to yourself as often as is possible today: 
33   
34   3 Let me be still and listen to the truth. 
35   4 I am the messenger of God today, My voice is His, to give what I receive.
36   
37   
38   
39   LESSON 107.
40   
41   Truth will correct all errors in my mind.
42   W-pI.107.1. What can correct illusions but the truth? 2 And what are errors but 
43   illusions that remain unrecognized for what they are? 3 Where truth has entered errors disappear.
44    4 They merely vanish, leaving not a trace by which to be remembered. 5 They are gone 
45   because, without belief, they have no life. 6 And so they disappear to nothingness, returning 
46   whence they came. 7 From dust to dust they come and go, for only truth remains.
47   W-pI.107.2. Can you imagine what a state of mind without illusions is? 2 How it would 
48   feel? 3 Try to remember when there was a time,--perhaps a minute, maybe even less--when 
49   nothing came to interrupt your peace; when you were certain you were loved and safe. 4 Then 
50   try to picture what it would be like to have that moment be extended to the end of time 
0505
 1   and to eternity. 5 Then let the sense of quiet that you felt be multiplied a hundred times,
 2    and then be multiplied another hundred more.
 3   W-pI.107.3. And now you have a hint, not more than just the faintest intimation of the 
 4   state your mind will rest in when the truth has come. 2 Without illusions there could be no 
 5   fear, no doubt and no attack. 3 When truth has come all pain is over, for there is no room 
 6   for transitory thoughts and dead ideas to linger in your mind. 4 Truth occupies your mind 
 7   completely, liberating you from all beliefs in the ephemeral. 5 They have no place because the 
 8   truth has come, and they are nowhere. 6 They can not be found, for truth is everywhere 
 9   forever, now.
10   W-pI.107.4. When truth has come it does not stay a while, to disappear or change to 
11   something else. 2 It does not shift and alter in its form, nor come and go and go and come again.
12    3 It stays exactly as it always was, to be depended on in every need, and trusted with
13   a perfect trust in all the seeming difficulties and the doubts that the appearances the
14   world presents engender. 4 They will merely blow away, when truth corrects the errors 
15   in your mind.
16   W-pI.107.5. When truth has come it harbors in its wings the gift of perfect constancy, 
17   and love which does not falter in the face of pain, but looks beyond it, steadily and sure.
18    2 Here is the gift of healing, for the truth needs no defense, and therefore no attack
19   is possible. 3 Illusions can be brought to truth to be corrected. 4 But the truth 
20   stands far beyond illusions, and can not be brought to them to turn them into truth.
21   W-pI.107.6. Truth does not come and go nor shift nor change, in this appearance now and
22   then in that, evading capture and escaping grasp. 2 It does not hide. 3 It stands in 
23   open light, in obvious accessibility. 4 It is impossible that anyone could seek it truly, 
24   and would not succeed. 5 Today belongs to truth. 6 Give truth its due, and it will give 
25   you yours. 7 You were not meant to suffer and to die. 8 Your Father wills these dreams be 
26   gone. 9 Let truth correct them all.
27   W-pI.107.7. We do not ask for what we do not have. 2 We merely ask for what belongs to 
28   us, that we may recognize it as our own. 3 Today we practice on the happy note of 
29   certainty that has been born of truth. 4 The shaky and unsteady footsteps of illusion are not 
30   our approach today. 5 We are as certain of success as we are sure we live and hope and 
31   breathe and think. 6 We do not doubt we walk with truth today, and count on it to enter into 
32   all the exercises that we do this day.
33   W-pI.107.8. Begin by asking Him Who goes with you upon this undertaking that He be in 
34   your awareness as you go with Him. 2 You are not made of flesh and blood and bone, but were
35   created by the selfsame Thought which gave the gift of life to Him as well. 3 He is 
36   your Brother, and so like to you your Father knows that You are Both the same. 4 It is your
37   Self you ask to go with you, and how could He be absent where you are?
38   W-pI.107.9. Truth will correct all errors in your mind which tell you you could be 
39   apart from Him. 2 You speak to Him today, and make your pledge to let His function be 
40   fulfilled through you. 3 To share His function is to share His joy. 4 His confidence is with you,
41    as you say: 
42   
43   5 Truth will correct all errors in my mind, And I will rest in Him Who is my Self. 
44   
45   6 Then let Him lead you gently to the truth, which will envelop you and give you peace 
46   so deep and tranquil that you will return to the familiar world reluctantly.
47   W-pI.107.10. And yet you will be glad to look again upon this world. 2 For you will 
48   bring with you the promise of the changes which the truth that goes with you will carry to 
49   the world. 3 They will increase with every gift you give of five small minutes, and the 
50   errors that surround the world will be corrected as you let them be corrected in your mind.
0506
 1   W-pI.107.11. Do not forget your function for today. 2 Each time you tell yourself with 
 2   confidence, "Truth will correct all errors in my mind," you speak for all the world and Him Who 
 3   would release the world, as He would set you free.
 4   
 5   
 6   
 7   LESSON 108.
 8   
 9   To give and to receive are one in truth.
10   W-pI.108.1. Vision depends upon today's idea. 2 The light is in it, for it reconciles 
11   all seeming opposites. 3 And what is light except the resolution, born of peace, of all 
12   your conflicts and mistaken thoughts into one concept which is wholly true? 4 Even that one
13   will disappear, because the Thought behind it will appear instead to take its place. 5 
14   And now you are at peace forever, for the dream is over then.
15   W-pI.108.2. True light that makes true vision possible is not the light the body's eyes
16   behold. 2 It is a state of mind that has become so unified that darkness cannot be 
17   perceived at all. 3 And thus what is the same is seen as one, while what is not the same remains
18   unnoticed, for it is not there.
19   W-pI.108.3. This is the light that shows no opposites, and vision, being healed, has 
20   power to heal. 2 This is the light that brings your peace of mind to other minds, to share 
21   it and be glad that they are one with you and with themselves. 3 This is the light that 
22   heals because it brings single perception, based upon one frame of reference, from which one
23   meaning comes.
24   W-pI.108.4. Here are both giving and receiving seen as different aspects of one Thought
25   whose truth does not depend on which is seen as first, nor which appears to be in 
26   second place. 2 Here it is understood that both occur together, that the Thought remain 
27   complete. 3 And in this understanding is the base on which all opposites are reconciled, 
28   because they are perceived from the same frame of reference which unifies this Thought.
29   W-pI.108.5. One thought, completely unified, will serve to unify all thought. 2 This is
30   the same as saying one correction will suffice for all correction, or that to forgive 
31   one brother wholly is enough to bring salvation to all minds. 3 For these are but some 
32   special cases of one law which holds for every kind of learning, if it be directed by the One 
33   Who knows the truth.
34   W-pI.108.6. To learn that giving and receiving are the same has special usefulness, 
35   because it can be tried so easily and seen as true. 2 And when this special case has proved it
36   always works, in every circumstance where it is tried, the thought behind it can be 
37   generalized to other areas of doubt and double vision. 3 And from there it will extend, and 
38   finally arrive at the one Thought which underlies them all.
39   W-pI.108.7. Today we practice with the special case of giving and receiving. 2 We will 
40   use this simple lesson in the obvious because it has results we cannot miss. 3 To give is 
41   to receive. 4 Today we will attempt to offer peace to everyone, and see how quickly peace
42   returns to us. 5 Light is tranquility, and in that peace is vision given us, and we can
43   see.
44   W-pI.108.8. So we begin the practice periods with the instruction for today, and say: 
45   
46   2 To give and to receive are one in truth. 
47   3 I will receive what I am giving now. 
48   
49   4 Then close your eyes, and for five minutes think of what you would hold out to 
50   everyone, to have it yours. 5 You might, for instance, say: 
0507
 1   
 2   6 To everyone I offer quietness. 
 3   7 To everyone I offer peace of mind. 
 4   8 To everyone I offer gentleness.
 5   
 6   W-pI.108.9. Say each one slowly and then pause a while, expecting to receive the gift 
 7   you gave. 2 And it will come to you in the amount in which you gave it. 3 You will find 
 8   you have exact return, for that is what you asked. 4 It might be helpful, too, to think of
 9   one to whom to give your gifts. 5 He represents the others, and through him you give to
10   all.
11   W-pI.108.10. Our very simple lesson for today will teach you much. 2 Effect and cause 
12   will be far better understood from this time on, and we will make much faster progress now.
13   3 Think of the exercises for today as quick advances in your learning, made still 
14   faster and more sure each time you say, "To give and to receive are one in truth."
15   
16   
17   
18   LESSON 109.
19   
20   I rest in God.
21   W-pI.109.1. We ask for rest today, and quietness unshaken by the world's appearances. 2
22   We ask for peace and stillness, in the midst of all the turmoil born of clashing dreams.
23    3 We ask for safety and for happiness, although we seem to look on danger and on 
24   sorrow. 4 And we have the thought that will answer our asking with what we request.
25   W-pI.109.2. "I rest in God." 2 This thought will bring to you the rest and quiet, peace
26   and stillness, and the safety and the happiness you seek. 3 "I rest in God." 4 This 
27   thought has power to wake the sleeping truth in you, whose vision sees beyond appearances to 
28   that same truth in everyone and everything there is. 5 Here is the end of suffering for all
29   the world, and everyone who ever came and yet will come to linger for a while. 6 Here 
30   is the thought in which the Son of God is born again, to recognize himself.
31   W-pI.109.3. "I rest in God." 2 Completely undismayed, this thought will carry you 
32   through storms and strife, past misery and pain, past loss and death, and onward to the 
33   certainty of God. 3 There is no suffering it cannot heal. 4 There is no problem that it cannot 
34   solve. 5 And no appearance but will turn to truth before the eyes of you who rest in God.
35   W-pI.109.4. This is the day of peace. 2 You rest in God, and while the world is torn by
36   winds of hate your rest remains completely undisturbed. 3 Yours is the rest of truth. 4
37   Appearances cannot intrude on you. 5 You call to all to join you in your rest, and they
38   will hear and come to you because you rest in God. 6 They will not hear another voice 
39   than yours because you gave your voice to God, and now you rest in Him and let Him speak 
40   through you.
41   W-pI.109.5. In Him you have no cares and no concerns, no burdens, no anxiety, no pain, 
42   no fear of future and no past regrets. 2 In timelessness you rest, while time goes by 
43   without its touch upon you, for your rest can never change in any way at all. 3 You rest today.
44    4 And as you close your eyes, sink into stillness. 5 Let these periods of rest and 
45   respite reassure your mind that all its frantic fantasies were but the dreams of fever that 
46   has passed away. 6 Let it be still and thankfully accept its healing. 7 No more fearful 
47   dreams will come, now that you rest in God. 8 Take time today to slip away from dreams and 
48   into peace.
49   W-pI.109.6. Each hour that you take your rest today, a tired mind is suddenly made glad,
50    a bird with broken wings begins to sing, a stream long dry begins to flow again. 2 The
0508
 1   world is born again each time you rest, and hourly remember that you came to bring the 
 2   peace of God into the world, that it might take its rest along with you.
 3   W-pI.109.7. With each five minutes that you rest today, the world is nearer waking. 2 
 4   And the time when rest will be the only thing there is comes closer to all worn and tired 
 5   minds, too weary now to go their way alone. 3 And they will hear the bird begin to sing and 
 6   see the stream begin to flow again, with hope reborn and energy restored to walk with 
 7   lightened steps along the road that suddenly seems easy as they go.
 8   W-pI.109.8. You rest within the peace of God today, and call upon your brothers from 
 9   your rest to draw them to their rest, along with you. 2 You will be faithful to your trust 
10   today, forgetting no one, bringing everyone into the boundless circle of your peace, the 
11   holy sanctuary where you rest. 3 Open the temple doors and let them come from far across 
12   the world, and near as well; your distant brothers and your closest friends; bid them all 
13   enter here and rest with you.
14   W-pI.109.9. You rest within the peace of God today, quiet and unafraid. 2 Each brother 
15   comes to take his rest, and offer it to you. 3 We rest together here, for thus our rest is 
16   made complete, and what we give today we have received already. 4 Time is not the guardian 
17   of what we give today. 5 We give to those unborn and those passed by, to every Thought of
18   God, and to the Mind in which these Thoughts were born and where they rest. 6 And we 
19   remind them of their resting place each time we tell ourselves, "I rest in God."
20   
21   
22   
23   LESSON 110.
24   
25   I am as God created me.
26   W-pI.110.1. We will repeat today's idea from time to time. 2 For this one thought would
27   be enough to save you and the world, if you believed that it is true. 3 Its truth would
28   mean that you have made no changes in yourself that have reality, nor changed the 
29   universe so that what God created was replaced by fear and evil, misery and death. 4 If you 
30   remain as God created you fear has no meaning, evil is not real, and misery and death do not 
31   exist.
32   W-pI.110.2. Today's idea is therefore all you need to let complete correction heal your
33   mind, and give you perfect vision that will heal all the mistakes that any mind has 
34   made at any time or place. 2 It is enough to heal the past and make the future free. 3 It 
35   is enough to let the present be accepted as it is. 4 It is enough to let time be the 
36   means for all the world to learn escape from time, and every change that time appears to 
37   bring in passing by.
38   W-pI.110.3. If you remain as God created you, appearances cannot replace the truth, 
39   health cannot turn to sickness, nor can death be substitute for life, or fear for love. 2 All
40   this has not occurred, if you remain as God created you. 3 You need no thought but just
41   this one, to let redemption come to light the world and free it from the past.
42   W-pI.110.4. In this one thought is all the past undone; the present saved to quietly 
43   extend into a timeless future. 2 If you are as God created you, then there has been no 
44   separation of your mind from His, no split between your mind and other minds, and only unity 
45   within your own.
46   W-pI.110.5. The healing power of today's idea is limitless. 2 It is the birthplace of 
47   all miracles, the great restorer of the truth to the awareness of the world. 3 Practice 
48   today's idea with gratitude. 4 This is the truth that comes to set you free. 5 This is the 
49   truth that God has promised you. 6 This is the Word in which all sorrow ends.
50   W-pI.110.6. For your five-minute practice periods, begin with this quotation from the 
0509
 1   text: 
 2   
 3   2 I am as God created me. 3 His Son can suffer nothing. 
 4   4 And I am His Son.
 5   
 6   W-pI.110.7. Then, with this statement firmly in your mind, try to discover in your mind
 7   the Self Who is the holy Son of God Himself.
 8   W-pI.110.8. Seek Him within you Who is Christ in you, the Son of God and brother to the
 9   world; the Savior Who has been forever saved, with power to save whoever touches Him, 
10   however lightly, asking for the Word that tells him he is brother unto Him.
11   W-pI.110.9. You are as God created you. 2 Today honor your Self. 3 Let graven images 
12   you made to be the Son of God instead of what he is be worshipped not today. 4 Deep in 
13   your mind the holy Christ in you is waiting your acknowledgment as you. 5 And you are lost 
14   and do not know yourself while He is unacknowledged and unknown.
15   W-pI.110.10. Seek Him today, and find Him. 2 He will be your Savior from all idols you 
16   have made. 3 For when you find Him, you will understand how worthless are your idols, and 
17   how false the images which you believed were you. 4 Today we make a great advance to truth
18   by letting idols go, and opening our hands and hearts and minds to God today.
19   W-pI.110.11. We will remember Him throughout the day with thankful hearts and loving 
20   thoughts for all who meet with us today. 2 For it is thus that we remember Him. 3 And we will 
21   say, that we may be reminded of His Son, our holy Self, the Christ in each of us: 
22   
23   4 I am as God created me. 
24   
25   5 Let us declare this truth as often as we can. 6 This is the Word of God that sets you
26   free. 7 This is the key that opens up the gate of Heaven, and that lets you enter in 
27   the peace of God and His eternity.
28   
