 6   LESSON 121.
 7   
 8   Forgiveness is the key to happiness.
 9   W-pI.121.1. Here is the answer to your search for peace. 2 Here is the key to meaning 
10   in a world that seems to make no sense. 3 Here is the way to safety in apparent dangers 
11   that appear to threaten you at every turn, and bring uncertainty to all your hopes of ever 
12   finding quietness and peace. 4 Here are all questions answered; here the end of all 
13   uncertainty ensured at last.
14   W-pI.121.2. The unforgiving mind is full of fear, and offers love no room to be itself;
15   no place where it can spread its wings in peace and soar above the turmoil of the world.
16    2 The unforgiving mind is sad, without the hope of respite and release from pain. 3 It
17   suffers and abides in misery, peering about in darkness, seeing not, yet certain of the
18   danger lurking there.
19   W-pI.121.3. The unforgiving mind is torn with doubt, confused about itself and all it 
20   sees; afraid and angry, weak and blustering, afraid to go ahead, afraid to stay, afraid to 
21   waken or to go to sleep, afraid of every sound, yet more afraid of stillness; terrified of 
22   darkness, yet more terrified at the approach of light. 2 What can the unforgiving mind perceive
23   but its damnation? 3 What can it behold except the proof that all its sins are real?
24   W-pI.121.4. The unforgiving mind sees no mistakes, but only sins. 2 It looks upon the 
25   world with sightless eyes, and shrieks as it beholds its own projections rising to attack 
26   its miserable parody of life. 3 It wants to live, yet wishes it were dead. 4 It wants 
27   forgiveness, yet it sees no hope. 5 It wants escape, yet can conceive of none because it sees the 
28   sinful everywhere.
29   W-pI.121.5. The unforgiving mind is in despair, without the prospect of a future which 
30   can offer anything but more despair. 2 Yet it regards its judgment of the world as 
31   irreversible, and does not see it has condemned itself to this despair. 3 It thinks it cannot 
32   change, for what it sees bears witness that its judgment is correct. 4 It does not ask, 
33   because it thinks it knows. 5 It does not question, certain it is right.
34   W-pI.121.6. Forgiveness is acquired. 2 It is not inherent in the mind, which cannot sin.
35    3 As sin is an idea you taught yourself, forgiveness must be learned by you as well, 
36   but from a Teacher other than yourself, Who represents the other Self in you. 4 Through 
37   Him you learn how to forgive the self you think you made, and let it disappear. 5 Thus you
38   return your mind as one to Him Who is your Self, and Who can never sin.
39   W-pI.121.7. Each unforgiving mind presents you with an opportunity to teach your own 
40   how to forgive itself. 2 Each one awaits release from hell through you, and turns to you 
41   imploringly for Heaven here and now. 3 It has no hope, but you become its hope. 4 And as its hope,
42   do you become your own. 5 The unforgiving mind must learn through your forgiveness that
43   it has been saved from hell. 6 And as you teach salvation, you will learn. 7 Yet all 
44   your teaching and your learning will be not of you, but of the Teacher Who was given you to
45   show the way to you.
46   W-pI.121.8. Today we practice learning to forgive. 2 If you are willing, you can learn 
47   today to take the key to happiness, and use it on your own behalf. 3 We will devote ten 
48   minutes in the morning, and at night another ten, to learning how to give forgiveness and 
49   receive forgiveness, too.
50   W-pI.121.9. The unforgiving mind does not believe that giving and receiving are the 
0516
 1   same. 2 Yet we will try to learn today that they are one through practicing forgiveness 
 2   toward one whom you think of as an enemy, and one whom you consider as a friend. 3 And as you
 3   learn to see them both as one, we will extend the lesson to yourself, and see that 
 4   their escape included yours.
 5   W-pI.121.10. Begin the longer practice periods by thinking of someone you do not like, 
 6   who seems to irritate you, or to cause regret in you if you should meet him; one you 
 7   actively despise, or merely try to overlook. 2 It does not matter what the form your anger 
 8   takes. 3 You probably have chosen him already. 4 He will do.
 9   W-pI.121.11. Now close your eyes and see him in your mind, and look at him a while. 2 
10   Try to perceive some light in him somewhere; a little gleam which you had never noticed. 3
11   Try to find some little spark of brightness shining through the ugly picture that you 
12   hold of him. 4 Look at this picture till you see a light somewhere within it, and then try 
13   to let this light extend until it covers him, and makes the picture beautiful and good.
14   W-pI.121.12. Look at this changed perception for a while, and turn your mind to one you
15   call a friend. 2 Try to transfer the light you learned to see around your former "enemy
16   " to him. 3 Perceive him now as more than friend to you, for in that light his holiness 
17   shows you your savior, saved and saving, healed and whole.
18   W-pI.121.13. Then let him offer you the light you see in him, and let your "enemy" and 
19   friend unite in blessing you with what you gave. 2 Now are you one with them, and they with 
20   you. 3 Now have you been forgiven by yourself. 4 Do not forget, throughout the day, the 
21   role forgiveness plays in bringing happiness to every unforgiving mind, with yours among 
22   them. 5 Every hour tell yourself: 
23   
24   6 Forgiveness is the key to happiness. 7 I will awaken from the dream that I am mortal,
25   fallible and full of sin, and know I am the perfect Son of God.
26   
27   
28   
29   LESSON 122.
30   
31   Forgiveness offers everything I want.
32   W-pI.122.1. What could you want forgiveness cannot give? 2 Do you want peace? 3 
33   Forgiveness offers it. 4 Do you want happiness, a quiet mind, a certainty of purpose, and a sense 
34   of worth and beauty that transcends the world? 5 Do you want care and safety, and the 
35   warmth of sure protection always? 6 Do you want a quietness that cannot be disturbed, a 
36   gentleness that never can be hurt, a deep, abiding comfort, and a rest so perfect it can never be
37   upset?
38   W-pI.122.2. All this forgiveness offers you, and more. 2 It sparkles on your eyes as 
39   you awake, and gives you joy with which to meet the day. 3 It soothes your forehead while 
40   you sleep, and rests upon your eyelids so you see no dreams of fear and evil, malice and 
41   attack. 4 And when you wake again, it offers you another day of happiness and peace. 5 All 
42   this forgiveness offers you, and more.
43   W-pI.122.3. Forgiveness lets the veil be lifted up that hides the face of Christ from 
44   those who look with unforgiving eyes upon the world. 2 It lets you recognize the Son of God,
45   and clears your memory of all dead thoughts so that remembrance of your Father can 
46   arise across the threshold of your mind. 3 What would you want forgiveness cannot give? 4 
47   What gifts but these are worthy to be sought? 5 What fancied value, trivial effect or 
48   transient promise, never to be kept, can hold more hope than what forgiveness brings?
49   W-pI.122.4. Why would you seek an answer other than the answer that will answer 
50   everything? 2 Here is the perfect answer, given to imperfect questions, meaningless requests, 
0517
 1   halfhearted willingness to hear, and less than halfway diligence and partial trust. 3 Here is the 
 2   answer! 4 Seek for it no more. 5 You will not find another one instead.
 3   W-pI.122.5. God's plan for your salvation cannot change, nor can it fail. 2 Be thankful
 4   it remains exactly as He planned it. 3 Changelessly it stands before you like an open 
 5   door, with warmth and welcome calling from beyond the doorway, bidding you to enter in and 
 6   make yourself at home, where you belong.
 7   W-pI.122.6. Here is the answer! 2 Would you stand outside while all of Heaven waits for
 8   you within? 3 Forgive and be forgiven. 4 As you give you will receive. 5 There is no 
 9   plan but this for the salvation of the Son of God. 6 Let us today rejoice that this is so, 
10   for here we have an answer, clear and plain, beyond deceit in its simplicity. 7 All the 
11   complexities the world has spun of fragile cobwebs disappear before the power and the majesty of 
12   this extremely simple statement of the truth.
13   W-pI.122.7. Here is the answer! 2 Do not turn away in aimless wandering again. 3 Accept
14   salvation now. 4 It is the gift of God, and not the world. 5 The world can give no 
15   gifts of any value to a mind that has received what God has given as its own. 6 God wills 
16   salvation be received today, and that the intricacies of your dreams no longer hide their 
17   nothingness from you.
18   W-pI.122.8. Open your eyes today and look upon a happy world of safety and of peace. 2 
19   Forgiveness is the means by which it comes to take the place of hell. 3 In quietness it rises up 
20   to greet your open eyes, and fill your heart with deep tranquility as ancient truths, 
21   forever newly born, arise in your awareness. 4 What you will remember then can never be 
22   described. 5 Yet your forgiveness offers it to you.
23   W-pI.122.9. Remembering the gifts forgiveness gives, we undertake our practicing today 
24   with hope and faith that this will be the day salvation will be ours. 2 Earnestly and 
25   gladly will we seek for it today, aware we hold the key within our hands, accepting Heaven's 
26   answer to the hell we made, but where we would remain no more.
27   W-pI.122.10. Morning and evening do we gladly give a quarter of an hour to the search 
28   in which the end of hell is guaranteed. 2 Begin in hopefulness, for we have reached the 
29   turning point at which the road becomes far easier. 3 And now the way is short that yet we 
30   travel. 4 We are close indeed to the appointed ending of the dream.
31   W-pI.122.11. Sink into happiness as you begin these practice periods, for they hold out
32   the sure rewards of questions answered and what your acceptance of the answer brings. 2
33   Today it will be given you to feel the peace forgiveness offers, and the joy the 
34   lifting of the veil holds out to you.
35   W-pI.122.12. Before the light you will receive today the world will fade until it 
36   disappears, and you will see another world arise you have no words to picture. 2 Now we walk 
37   directly into light, and we receive the gifts that have been held in store for us since time 
38   began, kept waiting for today.
39   W-pI.122.13. Forgiveness offers everything you want. 2 Today all things you want are 
40   given you. 3 Let not your gifts recede throughout the day, as you return again to meet a 
41   world of shifting change and bleak appearances. 4 Retain your gifts in clear awareness as 
42   you see the changeless in the heart of change; the light of truth behind appearances.
43   W-pI.122.14. Be tempted not to let your gifts slip by and drift into forgetfulness, but
44   hold them firmly in your mind by your attempts to think of them at least a minute as 
45   each quarter of an hour passes by. 2 Remind yourself how precious are these gifts with this
46   reminder, which has power to hold your gifts in your awareness through the day: 
47   
48   3 Forgiveness offers everything I want. 
49   4 Today I have accepted this as true. 
50   5 Today I have received the gifts of God.
