 4   LESSON 123.
 5   
 6   I thank my Father for His gifts to me.
 7   W-pI.123.1. Today let us be thankful. 2 We have come to gentler pathways and to 
 8   smoother roads. 3 There is no thought of turning back, and no implacable resistance to the 
 9   truth. 4 A bit of wavering remains, some small objections and a little hesitance, but you 
10   can well be grateful for your gains, which are far greater than you realize.
11   W-pI.123.2. A day devoted now to gratitude will add the benefit of some insight into 
12   the real extent of all the gains which you have made; the gifts you have received. 2 Be 
13   glad today, in loving thankfulness, your Father has not left you to yourself, nor let you 
14   wander in the dark alone. 3 Be grateful He has saved you from the self you thought you made 
15   to take the place of Him and His creation. 4 Give Him thanks today.
16   W-pI.123.3. Give thanks that He has not abandoned you, and that His Love forever will 
17   remain shining on you, forever without change. 2 Give thanks as well that you are changeless,
18   for the Son He loves is changeless as Himself. 3 Be grateful you are saved. 4 Be glad 
19   you have a function in salvation to fulfill. 5 Be thankful that your value far transcends 
20   your meager gifts and petty judgments of the one whom God established as His Son.
21   W-pI.123.4. Today in gratitude we lift our hearts above despair, and raise our thankful
22   eyes, no longer looking downward to the dust. 2 We sing the song of thankfulness today,
23   in honor of the Self that God has willed to be our true Identity in Him. 3 Today we 
24   smile on everyone we see, and walk with lightened footsteps as we go to do what is appointed
25   us to do.
26   W-pI.123.5. We do not go alone. 2 And we give thanks that in our solitude a Friend has 
27   come to speak the saving Word of God to us. 3 And thanks to you for listening to Him. 4 His
28   Word is soundless if it be not heard. 5 In thanking Him the thanks are yours as well. 6
29   An unheard message will not save the world, however mighty be the Voice that speaks, 
30   however loving may the message be.
31   W-pI.123.6. Thanks be to you who heard, for you become the messenger who brings His 
32   Voice with you, and lets It echo round and round the world. 2 Receive the thanks of God 
33   today, as you give thanks to Him. 3 For He would offer you the thanks you give, since He 
34   receives your gifts in loving gratitude, and gives them back a thousand and a hundred thousand 
35   more than they were given. 4 He will bless your gifts by sharing them with you. 5 And so 
36   they grow in power and in strength, until they fill the world with gladness and with 
37   gratitude.
38   W-pI.123.7. Receive His thanks and offer yours to Him for fifteen minutes twice today. 
39   2 And you will realize to Whom you offer thanks, and Whom He thanks as you are thanking 
40   Him. 3 This holy half an hour given Him will be returned to you in terms of years for 
41   every second; power to save the world eons more quickly for your thanks to Him.
42   W-pI.123.8. Receive His thanks, and you will understand how lovingly He holds you in 
43   His Mind, how deep and limitless His care for you, how perfect is His gratitude to you. 2 
44   Remember hourly to think of Him, and give Him thanks for everything He gave His Son, that he 
45   might rise above the world, remembering his Father and his Self.
