49   LESSON 124.
50   
0519
 1   Let me remember I am one with God.
 2   W-pI.124.1. Today we will again give thanks for our Identity in God. 2 Our home is safe,
 3    protection guaranteed in all we do, power and strength available to us in all our 
 4   undertakings. 3 We can fail in nothing. 4 Everything we touch takes on a shining light that blesses
 5   and that heals. 5 At one with God and with the universe we go our way rejoicing, with 
 6   the thought that God Himself goes everywhere with us.
 7   W-pI.124.2. How holy are our minds! 2 And everything we see reflects the holiness 
 8   within the mind at one with God and with itself. 3 How easily do errors disappear, and death 
 9   give place to everlasting life. 4 Our shining footprints point the way to truth, for God is
10   our Companion as we walk the world a little while. 5 And those who come to follow us 
11   will recognize the way because the light we carry stays behind, yet still remains with us 
12   as we walk on.
13   W-pI.124.3. What we receive is our eternal gift to those who follow after, and to those
14   who went before or stayed with us a while. 2 And God, Who loves us with the equal love 
15   in which we were created, smiles on us and offers us the happiness we gave.
16   W-pI.124.4. Today we will not doubt His Love for us, nor question His protection and 
17   His care. 2 No meaningless anxieties can come between our faith and our awareness of His 
18   Presence. 3 We are one with Him today in recognition and remembrance. 4 We feel Him in our 
19   hearts. 5 Our minds contain His Thoughts; our eyes behold His loveliness in all we look upon.
20   6 Today we see only the loving and the lovable.
21   W-pI.124.5. We see it in appearances of pain, and pain gives way to peace. 2 We see it 
22   in the frantic, in the sad and the distressed, the lonely and afraid, who are restored to
23   the tranquility and peace of mind in which they were created. 3 And we see it in the 
24   dying and the dead as well, restoring them to life. 4 All this we see because we saw it 
25   first within ourselves.
26   W-pI.124.6. No miracle can ever be denied to those who know that they are one with God.
27   2 No thought of theirs but has the power to heal all forms of suffering in anyone, in 
28   times gone by and times as yet to come, as easily as in the ones who walk beside them now. 3
29   Their thoughts are timeless, and apart from distance as apart from time.
30   W-pI.124.7. We join in this awareness as we say that we are one with God. 2 For in 
31   these words we say as well that we are saved and healed; that we can save and heal 
32   accordingly. 3 We have accepted, and we now would give. 4 For we would keep the gifts our Father 
33   gave. 5 Today we would experience ourselves at one with Him, so that the world may share 
34   our recognition of reality. 6 In our experience the world is freed. 7 As we deny our 
35   separation from our Father, it is healed along with us.
36   W-pI.124.8. Peace be to you today. 2 Secure your peace by practicing awareness you are 
37   one with your Creator, as He is with you. 3 Sometime today, whenever it seems best, devote
38   a half an hour to the thought that you are one with God. 4 This is our first attempt at
39   an extended period for which we give no rules nor special words to guide your 
40   meditation. 5 We will trust God's Voice to speak as He sees fit today, certain He will not fail. 
41   6 Abide with Him this half an hour. 7 He will do the rest.
42   W-pI.124.9. Your benefit will not be less if you believe that nothing happens. 2 You 
43   may not be ready to accept the gain today. 3 Yet sometime, somewhere, it will come to you,
44   nor will you fail to recognize it when it dawns with certainty upon your mind. 4 This 
45   half an hour will be framed in gold, with every minute like a diamond set around the mirror
46   that this exercise will offer you. 5 And you will see Christ's face upon it, in 
47   reflection of your own.
48   W-pI.124.10. Perhaps today, perhaps tomorrow, you will see your own transfiguration in 
49   the glass this holy half an hour will hold out to you, to look upon yourself. 2 When you 
50   are ready you will find it there, within your mind and waiting to be found. 3 You will 
0520
 1   remember then the thought to which you gave this half an hour, thankfully aware no time was 
 2   ever better spent.
 3   W-pI.124.11. Perhaps today, perhaps tomorrow, you will look into this glass, and 
 4   understand the sinless light you see belongs to you; the loveliness you look on is your own. 2 
 5   Count this half hour as your gift to God, in certainty that His return will be a sense of 
 6   love you cannot understand, a joy too deep for you to comprehend, a sight too holy for the 
 7   body's eyes to see. 3 And yet you can be sure someday, perhaps today, perhaps tomorrow, you 
 8   will understand and comprehend and see.
 9   W-pI.124.12. Add further jewels to the golden frame that holds the mirror offered you 
10   today, by hourly repeating to yourself: 
11   
12   2 Let me remember I am one with God, at one with all my brothers and my Self, in 
13   everlasting holiness and peace.
14   
