17   LESSON 125.
18   
19   In quiet I receive God's Word today.
20   W-pI.125.1. Let this day be a day of stillness and of quiet listening. 2 Your Father 
21   wills you hear His Word today. 3 He calls to you from deep within your mind where He abides.
22   4 Hear Him today. 5 No peace is possible until His Word is heard around the world; 
23   until your mind, in quiet listening, accepts the message that the world must hear to usher 
24   in the quiet time of peace.
25   W-pI.125.2. This world will change through you. 2 No other means can save it, for God's
26   plan is simply this: The Son of God is free to save himself, given the Word of God to 
27   be his Guide, forever in his mind and at his side to lead him surely to his Father's 
28   house by his own will, forever free as God's. 3 He is not led by force, but only love. 4 He 
29   is not judged, but only sanctified.
30   W-pI.125.3. In stillness we will hear God's Voice today without intrusion of our petty 
31   thoughts, without our personal desires, and without all judgment of His holy Word. 2 We will 
32   not judge ourselves today, for what we are can not be judged. 3 We stand apart from all 
33   the judgments which the world has laid upon the Son of God. 4 It knows him not. 5 Today we
34   will not listen to the world, but wait in silence for the Word of God.
35   W-pI.125.4. Hear, holy Son of God, your Father speak. 2 His Voice would give to you His
36   holy Word, to spread across the world the tidings of salvation and the holy time of 
37   peace. 3 We gather at the throne of God today, the quiet place within the mind where He 
38   abides forever, in the holiness that He created and will never leave.
39   W-pI.125.5. He has not waited until you return your mind to Him to give His Word to you.
40    2 He has not hid Himself from you, while you have wandered off a little while from Him.
41    3 He does not cherish the illusions which you hold about yourself. 4 He knows His Son,
42   and wills that he remain as part of Him regardless of his dreams; regardless of his 
43   madness that his will is not his own.
44   W-pI.125.6. Today He speaks to you. 2 His Voice awaits your silence, for His Word can 
45   not be heard until your mind is quiet for a while, and meaningless desires have been 
46   stilled. 3 Await His Word in quiet. 4 There is peace within you to be called upon today, to 
47   help make ready your most holy mind to hear the Voice for its Creator speak.
48   W-pI.125.7. Three times today, at times most suitable for silence, give ten minutes set
49   apart from listening to the world, and choose instead a gentle listening to the Word of
50   God. 2 He speaks from nearer than your heart to you. 3 His Voice is closer than your 
0521
 1   hand. 4 His Love is everything you are and that He is; the same as you, and you the same as
 2   He.
 3   W-pI.125.8. It is your voice to which you listen as He speaks to you. 2 It is your word
 4   He speaks. 3 It is the Word of freedom and of peace, of unity of will and purpose, with
 5   no separation nor division in the single Mind of Father and of Son. 4 In quiet listen 
 6   to your Self today, and let Him tell you God has never left His Son, and you have never 
 7   left your Self.
 8   W-pI.125.9. Only be quiet. 2 You will need no rule but this, to let your practicing 
 9   today lift you above the thinking of the world, and free your vision from the body's eyes. 3
10   Only be still and listen. 4 You will hear the Word in which the Will of God the Son 
11   joins in his Father's Will, at one with it, with no illusions interposed between the wholly 
12   indivisible and true. 5 As every hour passes by today, be still a moment and remind yourself you 
13   have a special purpose for this day; in quiet to receive the Word of God.
