45   
46   LESSON 136.
47   
48   Sickness is a defense against the truth.
49   W-pI.136.1. No one can heal unless he understands what purpose sickness seems to serve.
50   2 For then he understands as well its purpose has no meaning. 3 Being causeless and 
0538
 1   without a meaningful intent of any kind, it cannot be at all. 4 When this is seen, healing is 
 2   automatic. 5 It dispels this meaningless illusion by the same approach that carries all of them 
 3   to truth, and merely leaves them there to disappear.
 4   W-pI.136.2. Sickness is not an accident. 2 Like all defenses, it is an insane device 
 5   for self-deception. 3 And like all the rest, its purpose is to hide reality, attack it, 
 6   change it, render it inept, distort it, twist it, or reduce it to a little pile of 
 7   unassembled parts. 4 The aim of all defenses is to keep the truth from being whole. 5 The parts 
 8   are seen as if each one were whole within itself.
 9   W-pI.136.3. Defenses are not unintentional, nor are they made without awareness. 2 They
10   are secret, magic wands you wave when truth appears to threaten what you would believe.
11   3 They seem to be unconscious but because of the rapidity with which you choose to use 
12   them. 4 In that second, even less, in which the choice is made, you recognize exactly what 
13   you would attempt to do, and then proceed to think that it is done.
14   W-pI.136.4. Who but yourself evaluates a threat, decides escape is necessary, and sets 
15   up a series of defenses to reduce the threat that has been judged as real? 2 All this 
16   cannot be done unconsciously. 3 But afterwards, your plan requires that you must forget you 
17   made it, so it seems to be external to your own intent; a happening beyond your state of 
18   mind, an outcome with a real effect on you, instead of one effected by yourself.
19   W-pI.136.5. It is this quick forgetting of the part you play in making your "reality" 
20   that makes defenses seem to be beyond your own control. 2 But what you have forgot can be 
21   remembered, given willingness to reconsider the decision which is doubly shielded by oblivion. 3 
22   Your not remembering is but the sign that this decision still remains in force, as far as 
23   your desires are concerned. 4 Mistake not this for fact. 5 Defenses must make facts 
24   unrecognizable. 6 They aim at doing this, and it is this they do.
25   W-pI.136.6. Every defense takes fragments of the whole, assembles them without regard 
26   to all their true relationships, and thus constructs illusions of a whole that is not 
27   there. 2 It is this process that imposes threat, and not whatever outcome may result. 3 When
28   parts are wrested from the whole and seen as separate and wholes within themselves, 
29   they become symbols standing for attack upon the whole; successful in effect, and never to 
30   be seen as whole again. 4 And yet you have forgotten that they stand but for your own 
31   decision of what should be real, to take the place of what is real.
32   W-pI.136.7. Sickness is a decision. 2 It is not a thing that happens to you, quite 
33   unsought, which makes you weak and brings you suffering. 3 It is a choice you make, a plan you 
34   lay, when for an instant truth arises in your own deluded mind, and all your world appears
35   to totter and prepare to fall. 4 Now are you sick, that truth may go away and threaten 
36   your establishments no more.
37   W-pI.136.8. How do you think that sickness can succeed in shielding you from truth? 2 
38   Because it proves the body is not separate from you, and so you must be separate from the 
39   truth. 3 You suffer pain because the body does, and in this pain are you made one with it. 4
40   Thus is your "true" identity preserved, and the strange, haunting thought that you 
41   might be something beyond this little pile of dust silenced and stilled. 5 For see, this 
42   dust can make you suffer, twist your limbs and stop your heart, commanding you to die and 
43   cease to be.
44   W-pI.136.9. Thus is the body stronger than the truth, which asks you live, but cannot 
45   overcome your choice to die. 2 And so the body is more powerful than everlasting life, Heaven 
46   more frail than hell, and God's design for the salvation of His Son opposed by a decision 
47   stronger than His Will. 3 His Son is dust, the Father incomplete, and chaos sits in triumph on 
48   His throne.
49   W-pI.136.10. Such is your planning for your own defense. 2 And you believe that Heaven 
50   quails before such mad attacks as these, with God made blind by your illusions, truth turned 
0539
 1   into lies, and all the universe made slave to laws which your defenses would impose on it. 
 2   3 Yet who believes illusions but the one who made them up? 4 Who else can see them and 
 3   react to them as if they were the truth?
 4   W-pI.136.11. God knows not of your plans to change His Will. 2 The universe remains 
 5   unheeding of the laws by which you thought to govern it. 3 And Heaven has not bowed to hell, nor
 6   life to death. 4 You can but choose to think you die, or suffer sickness or distort the
 7   truth in any way. 5 What is created is apart from all of this. 6 Defenses are plans to 
 8   defeat what cannot be attacked. 7 What is unalterable cannot change. 8 And what is wholly 
 9   sinless cannot sin.
10   W-pI.136.12. Such is the simple truth. 2 It does not make appeal to might nor triumph. 
11   3 It does not command obedience, nor seek to prove how pitiful and futile your attempts 
12   to plan defenses that would alter it. 4 Truth merely wants to give you happiness, for 
13   such its purpose is. 5 Perhaps it sighs a little when you throw away its gifts, and yet it 
14   knows, with perfect certainty, that what God wills for you must be received.
15   W-pI.136.13. It is this fact that demonstrates that time is an illusion. 2 For time 
16   lets you think what God has given you is not the truth right now, as it must be. 3 The 
17   Thoughts of God are quite apart from time. 4 For time is but another meaningless defense you 
18   made against the truth. 5 Yet what He wills is here, and you remain as He created you.
19   W-pI.136.14. Truth has a power far beyond defense, for no illusions can remain where 
20   truth has been allowed to enter. 2 And it comes to any mind that would lay down its arms, 
21   and cease to play with folly. 3 It is found at any time; today, if you will choose to 
22   practice giving welcome to the truth.
23   W-pI.136.15. This is our aim today. 2 And we will give a quarter of an hour twice to 
24   ask the truth to come to us and set us free. 3 And truth will come, for it has never been 
25   apart from us. 4 It merely waits for just this invitation which we give today. 5 We 
26   introduce it with a healing prayer, to help us rise above defensiveness, and let truth be as it 
27   has always been: 
28   
29   6 Sickness is a defense against the truth. 7 I will accept the truth of what I am, and 
30   let my mind be wholly healed today.
31   
32   W-pI.136.16. Healing will flash across your open mind, as peace and truth arise to take
33   the place of war and vain imaginings. 2 There will be no dark corners sickness can 
34   conceal, and keep defended from the light of truth. 3 There will be no dim figures from your 
35   dreams, nor their obscure and meaningless pursuits with double purposes insanely sought, 
36   remaining in your mind. 4 It will be healed of all the sickly wishes that it tried to authorize 
37   the body to obey.
38   W-pI.136.17. Now is the body healed, because the source of sickness has been opened to 
39   relief. 2 And you will recognize you practiced well by this: The body should not feel at all.
40   3 If you have been successful, there will be no sense of feeling ill or feeling well, 
41   of pain or pleasure. 4 No response at all is in the mind to what the body does. 5 Its 
42   usefulness remains and nothing more.
43   W-pI.136.18. Perhaps you do not realize that this removes the limits you had placed 
44   upon the body by the purposes you gave to it. 2 As these are laid aside, the strength the 
45   body has will always be enough to serve all truly useful purposes. 3 The body's health is 
46   fully guaranteed, because it is not limited by time, by weather or fatigue, by food and 
47   drink, or any laws you made it serve before. 4 You need do nothing now to make it well, for 
48   sickness has become impossible.
49   W-pI.136.19. Yet this protection needs to be preserved by careful watching. 2 If you 
50   let your mind harbor attack thoughts, yield to judgment or make plans against 
0540
 1   uncertainties to come, you have again misplaced yourself, and made a bodily identity which will 
 2   attack the body, for the mind is sick.
 3   W-pI.136.20. Give instant remedy, should this occur, by not allowing your defensiveness
 4   to hurt you longer. 2 Do not be confused about what must be healed, but tell yourself: 
 5   
 6   3 I have forgotten what I really am, for I mistook my body for myself. 4 Sickness is a 
 7   defense against the truth. 5 But I am not a body. 6 And my mind cannot attack. 7 So I can not 
 8   be sick.
