12   LESSON 137.
13   
14   When I am healed I am not healed alone.
15   W-pI.137.1. Today's idea remains the central thought on which salvation rests. 2 For 
16   healing is the opposite of all the world's ideas which dwell on sickness and on separate 
17   states. 3 Sickness is a retreat from others, and a shutting off of joining. 4 It becomes a 
18   door that closes on a separate self, and keeps it isolated and alone.
19   W-pI.137.2. Sickness is isolation. 2 For it seems to keep one self apart from all the 
20   rest, to suffer what the others do not feel. 3 It gives the body final power to make the 
21   separation real, and keep the mind in solitary prison, split apart and held in pieces by a solid 
22   wall of sickened flesh, which it can not surmount.
23   W-pI.137.3. The world obeys the laws that sickness serves, but healing operates apart 
24   from them. 2 It is impossible that anyone be healed alone. 3 In sickness must he be apart 
25   and separate. 4 But healing is his own decision to be one again, and to accept his Self 
26   with all Its parts intact and unassailed. 5 In sickness does his Self appear to be 
27   dismembered, and without the unity that gives It life. 6 But healing is accomplished as he sees 
28   the body has no power to attack the universal Oneness of God's Son.
29   W-pI.137.4. Sickness would prove that lies must be the truth. 2 But healing 
30   demonstrates that truth is true. 3 The separation sickness would impose has never really happened. 
31   4 To be healed is merely to accept what always was the simple truth, and always will 
32   remain exactly as it has forever been. 5 Yet eyes accustomed to illusions must be shown that 
33   what they look upon is false. 6 So healing, never needed by the truth, must demonstrate 
34   that sickness is not real.
35   W-pI.137.5. Healing might thus be called a counter-dream, which cancels out the dream 
36   of sickness in the name of truth, but not in truth itself. 2 Just as forgiveness 
37   overlooks all sins that never were accomplished, healing but removes illusions that have not 
38   occurred. 3 Just as the real world will arise to take the place of what has never been at all, 
39   healing but offers restitution for imagined states and false ideas which dreams embroider into
40   pictures of the truth.
41   W-pI.137.6. Yet think not healing is unworthy of your function here. 2 For anti-Christ 
42   becomes more powerful than Christ to those who dream the world is real. 3 The body seems to be
43   more solid and more stable than the mind. 4 And love becomes a dream, while fear 
44   remains the one reality that can be seen and justified and fully understood.
45   W-pI.137.7. Just as forgiveness shines away all sin and the real world will occupy the 
46   place of what you made, so healing must replace the fantasies of sickness which you hold 
47   before the simple truth. 2 When sickness has been seen to disappear in spite of all the laws 
48   that hold it cannot but be real, then questions have been answered. 3 And the laws can be 
49   no longer cherished nor obeyed.
50   W-pI.137.8. Healing is freedom. 2 For it demonstrates that dreams will not prevail 
0541
 1   against the truth. 3 Healing is shared. 4 And by this attribute it proves that laws unlike the
 2   ones which hold that sickness is inevitable are more potent than their sickly opposites.
 3    5 Healing is strength. 6 For by its gentle hand is weakness overcome, and minds that 
 4   were walled off within a body free to join with other minds, to be forever strong.
 5   W-pI.137.9. Healing, forgiveness, and the glad exchange of all the world of sorrow for 
 6   a world where sadness cannot enter, are the means by which the Holy Spirit urges you to 
 7   follow Him. 2 His gentle lessons teach how easily salvation can be yours; how little practice
 8   you need undertake to let His laws replace the ones you made to hold yourself a 
 9   prisoner to death. 3 His life becomes your own, as you extend the little help He asks in 
10   freeing you from everything that ever caused you pain.
11   W-pI.137.10. And as you let yourself be healed, you see all those around you, or who 
12   cross your mind, or whom you touch or those who seem to have no contact with you, healed 
13   along with you. 2 Perhaps you will not recognize them all, nor realize how great your 
14   offering to all the world, when you let healing come to you. 3 But you are never healed alone. 
15   4 And legions upon legions will receive the gift that you receive when you are healed.
16   W-pI.137.11. Those who are healed become the instruments of healing. 2 Nor does time 
17   elapse between the instant they are healed, and all the grace of healing it is given them to 
18   give. 3 What is opposed to God does not exist, and who accepts it not within his mind 
19   becomes a haven where the weary can remain to rest. 4 For here is truth bestowed, and here are
20   all illusions brought to truth.
21   W-pI.137.12. Would you not offer shelter to God's Will? 2 You but invite your Self to 
22   be at home. 3 And can this invitation be refused? 4 Ask the inevitable to occur, and you 
23   will never fail. 5 The other choice is but to ask what cannot be to be, and this can not 
24   succeed. 6 Today we ask that only truth will occupy our minds; that thoughts of healing will 
25   this day go forth from what is healed to what must yet be healed, aware that they will both
26   occur as one.
27   W-pI.137.13. We will remember, as the hour strikes, our function is to let our minds be
28   healed, that we may carry healing to the world, exchanging curse for blessing, pain for
29   joy, and separation for the peace of God. 2 Is not a minute of the hour worth the 
30   giving to receive a gift like this? 3 Is not a little time a small expense to offer for the 
31   gift of everything?
32   W-pI.137.14. Yet must we be prepared for such a gift. 2 And so we will begin the day 
33   with this, and give ten minutes to these thoughts with which we will conclude today at 
34   night as well: 
35   
36   3 When I am healed I am not healed alone. 4 And I would share my healing with the world,
37    that sickness may be banished from the mind of God's one Son, Who is my only Self.
38   
39   W-pI.137.15. Let healing be through you this very day. 2 And as you rest in quiet, be 
40   prepared to give as you receive, to hold but what you give, and to receive the Word of God to 
41   take the place of all the foolish thoughts that ever were imagined. 3 Now we come together 
42   to make well all that was sick, and offer blessing where there was attack. 4 Nor will we 
43   let this function be forgot as every hour of the day slips by, remembering our purpose 
44   with this thought: 
45   
46   5 When I am healed I am not healed alone. 6 And I would bless my brothers, for I would 
47   be healed with them, as they are healed with me.
