18   LESSON 154.
19   
20   I am among the ministers of God.
21   W-pI.154.1. Let us today be neither arrogant nor falsely humble. 2 We have gone beyond 
22   such foolishness. 3 We cannot judge ourselves, nor need we do so. 4 These are but attempts 
23   to hold decision off, and to delay commitment to our function. 5 It is not our part to 
24   judge our worth, nor can we know what role is best for us; what we can do within a larger 
25   plan we cannot see in its entirety. 6 Our part is cast in Heaven, not in hell. 7 And what 
26   we think is weakness can be strength; what we believe to be our strength is often 
27   arrogance.
28   W-pI.154.2. Whatever your appointed role may be, it was selected by the Voice for God, 
29   Whose function is to speak for you as well. 2 Seeing your strengths exactly as they are, and
30   equally aware of where they can be best applied, for what, to whom and when, He chooses
31   and accepts your part for you. 3 He does not work without your own consent. 4 But He is
32   not deceived in what you are, and listens only to His Voice in you.
33   W-pI.154.3. It is through His ability to hear one Voice which is His Own that you 
34   become aware at last there is one Voice in you. 2 And that one Voice appoints your function, 
35   and relays it to you, giving you the strength to understand it, do what it entails, and to
36   succeed in everything you do that is related to it. 3 God has joined His Son in this, 
37   and thus His Son becomes His messenger of unity with Him.
38   W-pI.154.4. It is this joining, through the Voice for God, of Father and of Son, that 
39   sets apart salvation from the world. 2 It is this Voice which speaks of laws the world does
40   not obey; which promises salvation from all sin, with guilt abolished in the mind that 
41   God created sinless. 3 Now this mind becomes aware again of Who created it, and of His 
42   lasting union with itself. 4 So is its Self the one reality in which its will and that of God 
43   are joined.
44   W-pI.154.5. A messenger is not the one who writes the message he delivers. 2 Nor does 
45   he question the right of him who does, nor ask why he has chosen those who will receive 
46   the message that he brings. 3 It is enough that he accept it, give it to the ones for whom
47   it is intended, and fulfill his role in its delivery. 4 If he determines what the 
48   messages should be, or what their purpose is, or where they should be carried, he is failing to
49   perform his proper part as bringer of the Word.
50   W-pI.154.6. There is one major difference in the role of Heaven's messengers, which 
0556
 1   sets them off from those the world appoints. 2 The messages that they deliver are intended 
 2   first for them. 3 And it is only as they can accept them for themselves that they become 
 3   able to bring them further, and to give them everywhere that they were meant to be. 4 Like 
 4   earthly messengers, they did not write the messages they bear, but they become their first 
 5   receivers in the truest sense, receiving to prepare themselves to give.
 6   W-pI.154.7. An earthly messenger fulfills his role by giving all his messages away. 2 
 7   The messengers of God perform their part by their acceptance of His messages as for 
 8   themselves, and show they understand the messages by giving them away. 3 They choose no roles 
 9   that are not given them by His authority. 4 And so they gain by every message that they 
10   give away.
11   W-pI.154.8. Would you receive the messages of God? 2 For thus do you become His 
12   messenger. 3 You are appointed now. 4 And yet you wait to give the messages you have received. 5
13   And so you do not know that they are yours, and do not recognize them. 6 No one can 
14   receive and understand he has received until he gives. 7 For in the giving is his own 
15   acceptance of what he received.
16   W-pI.154.9. You who are now the messenger of God, receive His messages. 2 For that is 
17   part of your appointed role. 3 God has not failed to offer what you need, nor has it been 
18   left unaccepted. 4 Yet another part of your appointed task is yet to be accomplished. 5 He 
19   Who has received for you the messages of God would have them be received by you as well. 6
20   For thus do you identify with Him and claim your own.
21   W-pI.154.10. It is this joining that we undertake to recognize today. 2 We will not 
22   seek to keep our minds apart from Him Who speaks for us, for it is but our voice we hear as
23   we attend Him. 3 He alone can speak to us and for us, joining in one Voice the getting 
24   and the giving of God's Word; the giving and receiving of His Will.
25   W-pI.154.11. We practice giving Him what He would have, that we may recognize His gifts
26   to us. 2 He needs our voice that He may speak through us. 3 He needs our hands to hold 
27   His messages, and carry them to those whom He appoints. 4 He needs our feet to bring us 
28   where He wills, that those who wait in misery may be at last delivered. 5 And He needs our 
29   will united with His Own, that we may be the true receivers of the gifts He gives.
30   W-pI.154.12. Let us but learn this lesson for today: We will not recognize what we 
31   receive until we give it. 2 You have heard this said a hundred ways, a hundred times, and yet 
32   belief is lacking still. 3 But this is sure; until belief is given it, you will receive a 
33   thousand miracles and then receive a thousand more, but will not know that God Himself has left
34   no gift beyond what you already have; nor has denied the tiniest of blessings to His 
35   Son. 4 What can this mean to you, until you have identified with Him and with His Own?
36   W-pI.154.13. Our lesson for today is stated thus: 
37   
38   2 I am among the ministers of God, and I am grateful that I have the means by which to 
39   recognize that I am free.
40   
41   W-pI.154.14. The world recedes as we light up our minds, and realize these holy words 
42   are true. 2 They are the message sent to us today from our Creator. 3 Now we demonstrate 
43   how they have changed our minds about ourselves, and what our function is. 4 For as we 
44   prove that we accept no will we do not share, our many gifts from our Creator will spring to
45   our sight and leap into our hands, and we will recognize what we received.
