28   
29   LESSON 156.
30   
31   I walk with God in perfect holiness.
32   W-pI.156.1. Today's idea but states the simple truth that makes the thought of sin 
33   impossible. 2 It promises there is no cause for guilt, and being causeless it does not exist. 3 
34   It follows surely from the basic thought so often mentioned in the text; ideas leave not 
35   their source. 4 If this be true, how can you be apart from God? 5 How could you walk the 
36   world alone and separate from your Source?
37   W-pI.156.2. We are not inconsistent in the thoughts that we present in our curriculum. 
38   2 Truth must be true throughout, if it be true. 3 It cannot contradict itself, nor be in
39   parts uncertain and in others sure. 4 You cannot walk the world apart from God, because
40   you could not be without Him. 5 He is what your life is. 6 Where you are He is. 7 There
41   is one life. 8 That life you share with Him. 9 Nothing can be apart from Him and live.
42   W-pI.156.3. Yet where He is, there must be holiness as well as life. 2 No attribute of 
43   His remains unshared by everything that lives. 3 What lives is holy as Himself, because 
44   what shares His life is part of Holiness, and could no more be sinful than the sun could 
45   choose to be of ice; the sea elect to be apart from water, or the grass to grow with roots 
46   suspended in the air.
47   W-pI.156.4. There is a light in you which cannot die; whose presence is so holy that 
48   the world is sanctified because of you. 2 All things that live bring gifts to you, and 
49   offer them in gratitude and gladness at your feet. 3 The scent of flowers is their gift to 
50   you. 4 The waves bow down before you, and the trees extend their arms to shield you from 
0559
 1   the heat, and lay their leaves before you on the ground that you may walk in softness, 
 2   while the wind sinks to a whisper round your holy head.
 3   W-pI.156.5. The light in you is what the universe longs to behold. 2 All living things 
 4   are still before you, for they recognize Who walks with you. 3 The light you carry is 
 5   their own. 4 And thus they see in you their holiness, saluting you as savior and as God. 5 
 6   Accept their reverence, for it is due to Holiness Itself, which walks with you, transforming 
 7   in Its gentle light all things unto Its likeness and Its purity.
 8   W-pI.156.6. This is the way salvation works. 2 As you step back, the light in you steps
 9   forward and encompasses the world. 3 It heralds not the end of sin in punishment and 
10   death. 4 In lightness and in laughter is sin gone, because its quaint absurdity is seen. 5 
11   It is a foolish thought, a silly dream, not frightening, ridiculous perhaps, but who 
12   would waste an instant in approach to God Himself for such a senseless whim?
13   W-pI.156.7. Yet you have wasted many, many years on just this foolish thought. 2 The 
14   past is gone, with all its fantasies. 3 They keep you bound no longer. 4 The approach to 
15   God is near. 5 And in the little interval of doubt that still remains, you may perhaps 
16   lose sight of your Companion, and mistake Him for the senseless, ancient dream that now is 
17   past.
18   W-pI.156.8. "Who walks with me?" 2 This question should be asked a thousand times a day,
19    till certainty has ended doubting and established peace. 3 Today let doubting cease. 4
20   God speaks for you in answering your question with these words: 
21   
22   5 I walk with God in perfect holiness. 6 I light the world, I light my mind and all the
23   minds which God created one with me.
