27   LESSON 157.
28   
29   Into His Presence would I enter now.
30   W-pI.157.1. This is a day of silence and of trust. 2 It is a special time of promise in
31   your calendar of days. 3 It is a time Heaven has set apart to shine upon, and cast a 
32   timeless light upon this day, when echoes of eternity are heard. 4 This day is holy, for it 
33   ushers in a new experience; a different kind of feeling and awareness. 5 You have spent long 
34   days and nights in celebrating death. 6 Today you learn to feel the joy of life.
35   W-pI.157.2. This is another crucial turning point in the curriculum. 2 We add a new 
36   dimension now; a fresh experience that sheds a light on all that we have learned already, and 
37   prepares us for what we have yet to learn. 3 It brings us to the door where learning ceases, 
38   and we catch a glimpse of what lies past the highest reaches it can possibly attain. 4 It 
39   leaves us here an instant, and we go beyond it, sure of our direction and our only goal.
40   W-pI.157.3. Today it will be given you to feel a touch of Heaven, though you will 
41   return to paths of learning. 2 Yet you have come far enough along the way to alter time 
42   sufficiently to rise above its laws, and walk into eternity a while. 3 This you will learn to do 
43   increasingly, as every lesson, faithfully rehearsed, brings you more swiftly to this holy place and
44   leaves you, for a moment, to your Self.
45   W-pI.157.4. He will direct your practicing today, for what you ask for now is what He 
46   wills. 2 And having joined your will with His this day, what you are asking must be given 
47   you. 3 Nothing is needed but today's idea to light your mind, and let it rest in still 
48   anticipation and in quiet joy, wherein you quickly leave the world behind.
49   W-pI.157.5. From this day forth, your ministry takes on a genuine devotion, and a glow 
50   that travels from your fingertips to those you touch, and blesses those you look upon. 2 A 
0560
 1   vision reaches everyone you meet, and everyone you think of, or who thinks of you. 3 For your
 2   experience today will so transform your mind that it becomes the touchstone for the 
 3   holy Thoughts of God.
 4   W-pI.157.6. Your body will be sanctified today, its only purpose being now to bring the
 5   vision of what you experience this day to light the world. 2 We cannot give experience 
 6   like this directly. 3 Yet it leaves a vision in our eyes which we can offer everyone, that 
 7   he may come the sooner to the same experience in which the world is quietly forgot, and 
 8   Heaven is remembered for a while.
 9   W-pI.157.7. As this experience increases and all goals but this become of little worth,
10   the world to which you will return becomes a little closer to the end of time; a little
11   more like Heaven in its ways; a little nearer its deliverance. 2 And you who bring it 
12   light will come to see the light more sure; the vision more distinct. 3 The time will come 
13   when you will not return in the same form in which you now appear, for you will have no 
14   need of it. 4 Yet now it has a purpose, and will serve it well.
15   W-pI.157.8. Today we will embark upon a course you have not dreamed of. 2 But the Holy 
16   One, the Giver of the happy dreams of life, Translator of perception into truth, the holy 
17   Guide to Heaven given you, has dreamed for you this journey which you make and start today, 
18   with the experience this day holds out to you to be your own.
19   W-pI.157.9. Into Christ's Presence will we enter now, serenely unaware of everything 
20   except His shining face and perfect Love. 2 The vision of His face will stay with you, but 
21   there will be an instant which transcends all vision, even this, the holiest. 3 This you 
22   will never teach, for you attained it not through learning. 4 Yet the vision speaks of your
23   rememberance of what you knew that instant, and will surely know again.
