40   LESSON 159.
41   
42   I give the miracles I have received.
43   W-pI.159.1. No one can give what he has not received. 2 To give a thing requires first 
44   you have it in your own possession. 3 Here the laws of Heaven and the world agree. 4 But 
45   here they also separate. 5 The world believes that to possess a thing, it must be kept. 6 
46   Salvation teaches otherwise. 7 To give is how to recognize you have received. 8 It is the proof 
47   that what you have is yours.
48   W-pI.159.2. You understand that you are healed when you give healing. 2 You accept 
49   forgiveness as accomplished in yourself when you forgive. 3 You recognize your brother as yourself,
50    and thus do you perceive that you are whole. 4 There is no miracle you cannot give, 
0562
 1   for all are given you. 5 Receive them now by opening the storehouse of your mind where 
 2   they are laid, and giving them away.
 3   W-pI.159.3. Christ's vision is a miracle. 2 It comes from far beyond itself, for it 
 4   reflects eternal love and the rebirth of love which never dies, but has been kept obscure. 3 
 5   Christ's vision pictures Heaven, for it sees a world so like to Heaven that what God created 
 6   perfect can be mirrored there. 4 The darkened glass the world presents can show but twisted 
 7   images in broken parts. 5 The real world pictures Heaven's innocence.
 8   W-pI.159.4. Christ's vision is the miracle in which all miracles are born. 2 It is 
 9   their source, remaining with each miracle you give, and yet remaining yours. 3 It is the 
10   bond by which the giver and receiver are united in extension here on earth, as they are one
11   in Heaven. 4 Christ beholds no sin in anyone. 5 And in His sight the sinless are as one.
12    6 Their holiness was given by His Father and Himself.
13   W-pI.159.5. Christ's vision is the bridge between the worlds. 2 And in its power can 
14   you safely trust to carry you from this world into one made holy by forgiveness. 3 Things 
15   which seem quite solid here are merely shadows there; transparent, faintly seen, at times 
16   forgot, and never able to obscure the light that shines beyond them. 4 Holiness has been 
17   restored to vision, and the blind can see.
18   W-pI.159.6. This is the Holy Spirit's single gift; the treasure house to which you can 
19   appeal with perfect certainty for all the things that can contribute to your happiness. 2 All
20   are laid here already. 3 All can be received but for the asking. 4 Here the door is 
21   never locked, and no one is denied his least request or his most urgent need. 5 There is no 
22   sickness not already healed, no lack unsatisfied, no need unmet within this golden treasury of 
23   Christ.
24   W-pI.159.7. Here does the world remember what was lost when it was made. 2 For here it 
25   is repaired, made new again, but in a different light. 3 What was to be the home of sin 
26   becomes the center of redemption and the hearth of mercy, where the suffering are healed and 
27   welcome. 4 No one will be turned away from this new home, where his salvation waits. 5 No one 
28   is stranger to him. 6 No one asks for anything of him except the gift of his acceptance 
29   of his welcoming.
30   W-pI.159.8. Christ's vision is the holy ground in which the lilies of forgiveness set 
31   their roots. 2 This is their home. 3 They can be brought from here back to the world, but 
32   they can never grow in its unnourishing and shallow soil. 4 They need the light and warmth 
33   and kindly care Christ's charity provides. 5 They need the love with which He looks on 
34   them. 6 And they become His messengers, who give as they received.
35   W-pI.159.9. Take from His storehouse, that its treasures may increase. 2 His lilies do 
36   not leave their home when they are carried back into the world. 3 Their roots remain. 4 
37   They do not leave their source, but carry its beneficence with them, and turn the world 
38   into a garden like the one they came from, and to which they go again with added fragrance.
39   5 Now are they twice blessed. 6 The messages they brought from Christ have been 
40   delivered, and returned to them. 7 And they return them gladly unto Him.
41   W-pI.159.10. Behold the store of miracles set out for you to give. 2 Are you not worth 
42   the gift, when God appointed it be given you? 3 Judge not God's Son, but follow in the way
43   He has established. 4 Christ has dreamed the dream of a forgiven world. 5 It is His 
44   gift, whereby a sweet transition can be made from death to life; from hopelessness to hope.
45   6 Let us an instant dream with Him. 7 His dream awakens us to truth. 8 His vision gives
46   the means for a return to our unlost and everlasting sanctity in God.
