36   LESSON 165.
37   
38   Let not my mind deny the Thought of God.
39   W-pI.165.1. What makes this world seem real except your own denial of the truth that 
40   lies beyond? 2 What but your thoughts of misery and death obscure the perfect happiness and
41   the eternal life your Father wills for you? 3 And what could hide what cannot be 
42   concealed except illusion? 4 What could keep from you what you already have except your choice 
43   to see it not, denying it is there?
44   W-pI.165.2. The Thought of God created you. 2 It left you not, nor have you ever been 
45   apart from it an instant. 3 It belongs to you. 4 By it you live. 5 It is your Source of life,
46    holding you one with it, and everything is one with you because it left you not. 6 The
47   Thought of God protects you, cares for you, makes soft your resting place and smooth 
48   your way, lighting your mind with happiness and love. 7 Eternity and everlasting life shine
49   in your mind, because the Thought of God has left you not, and still abides with you.
50   W-pI.165.3. Who would deny his safety and his peace, his joy, his healing and his peace
0569
 1   of mind, his quiet rest, his calm awakening, if he but recognized where they abide? 2 
 2   Would he not instantly prepare to go where they are found, abandoning all else as worthless 
 3   in comparison with them? 3 And having found them, would he not make sure they stay with 
 4   him, and he remain with them?
 5   W-pI.165.4. Deny not Heaven. 2 It is yours today, but for the asking. 3 Nor need you 
 6   perceive how great the gift, how changed your mind will be before it comes to you. 4 Ask to 
 7   receive, and it is given you. 5 Conviction lies within it. 6 Till you welcome it as yours, 
 8   uncertainty remains. 7 Yet God is fair. 8 Sureness is not required to receive what only your 
 9   acceptance can bestow.
10   W-pI.165.5. Ask with desire. 2 You need not be sure that you request the only thing you
11   want. 3 But when you have received, you will be sure you have the treasure you have 
12   always sought. 4 What would you then exchange for it? 5 What would induce you now to let it 
13   fade away from your ecstatic vision? 6 For this sight proves that you have exchanged your 
14   blindness for the seeing eyes of Christ; your mind has come to lay aside denial, and accept the 
15   Thought of God as your inheritance.
16   W-pI.165.6. Now is all doubting past, the journey's end made certain, and salvation 
17   given you. 2 Now is Christ's power in your mind, to heal as you were healed. 3 For now you 
18   are among the saviors of the world. 4 Your destiny lies there and nowhere else. 5 Would 
19   God consent to let His Son remain forever starved by his denial of the nourishment he 
20   needs to live? 6 Abundance dwells in him, and deprivation cannot cut him off from God's 
21   sustaining Love and from his home.
22   W-pI.165.7. Practice today in hope. 2 For hope indeed is justified. 3 Your doubts are 
23   meaningless, for God is certain. 4 And the Thought of Him is never absent. 5 Sureness must abide 
24   within you who are host to Him. 6 This course removes all doubts which you have interposed 
25   between Him and your certainty of Him.
26   W-pI.165.8. We count on God, and not upon ourselves, to give us certainty. 2 And in His
27   Name we practice as His Word directs we do. 3 His sureness lies beyond our every doubt.
28   4 His Love remains beyond our every fear. 5 The Thought of Him is still beyond all 
29   dreams and in our minds, according to His Will.
