21   LESSON 182.
22   
23   I will be still an instant and go home.
24   W-pI.182.1. This world you seem to live in is not home to you. 2 And somewhere in your 
25   mind you know that this is true. 3 A memory of home keeps haunting you, as if there were a 
26   place that called you to return, although you do not recognize the voice, nor what it is the
27   voice reminds you of. 4 Yet still you feel an alien here, from somewhere all unknown. 5
28   Nothing so definite that you could say with certainty you are an exile here. 6 Just a 
29   persistent feeling, sometimes not more than a tiny throb, at other times hardly remembered, 
30   actively dismissed, but surely to return to mind again.
31   W-pI.182.2. No one but knows whereof we speak. 2 Yet some try to put by their suffering
32   in games they play to occupy their time, and keep their sadness from them. 3 Others 
33   will deny that they are sad, and do not recognize their tears at all. 4 Still others will 
34   maintain that what we speak of is illusion, not to be considered more than but a dream. 5 Yet 
35   who, in simple honesty, without defensiveness and self-deception, would deny he 
36   understands the words we speak?
37   W-pI.182.3. We speak today for everyone who walks this world, for he is not at home. 2 
38   He goes uncertainly about in endless search, seeking in darkness what he cannot find; not
39   recognizing what it is he seeks. 3 A thousand homes he makes, yet none contents his 
40   restless mind. 4 He does not understand he builds in vain. 5 The home he seeks can not be made 
41   by him. 6 There is no substitute for Heaven. 7 All he ever made was hell.
42   W-pI.182.4. Perhaps you think it is your childhood home that you would find again. 2 
43   The childhood of your body, and its place of shelter, are a memory now so distorted that 
44   you merely hold a picture of a past that never happened. 3 Yet there is a Child in you Who
45   seeks His Father's house, and knows that He is alien here. 4 This childhood is eternal,
46   with an innocence that will endure forever. 5 Where this Child shall go is holy ground.
47   6 It is His Holiness that lights up Heaven, and that brings to earth the pure 
48   reflection of the light above, wherein are earth and Heaven joined as one.
49   W-pI.182.5. It is this Child in you your Father knows as His Own Son. 2 It is this 
50   Child Who knows His Father. 3 He desires to go home so deeply, so unceasingly, His voice 
0583
 1   cries unto you to let Him rest a while. 4 He does not ask for more than just a few instants 
 2   of respite; just an interval in which He can return to breathe again the holy air that 
 3   fills His Father's house. 5 You are His home as well. 6 He will return. 7 But give Him just 
 4   a little time to be Himself, within the peace that is His home, resting in silence and 
 5   in peace and love.
 6   W-pI.182.6. This Child needs your protection. 2 He is far from home. 3 He is so little 
 7   that He seems so easily shut out, His tiny voice so readily obscured, His call for help 
 8   almost unheard amid the grating sounds and harsh and rasping noises of the world. 4 Yet does 
 9   He know that in you still abides His sure protection. 5 You will fail Him not. 6 He will 
10   go home, and you along with Him.
11   W-pI.182.7. This Child is your defenselessness; your strength. 2 He trusts in you. 3 He
12   came because He knew you would not fail. 4 He whispers of His home unceasingly to you. 
13   5 For He would bring you back with Him, that He Himself might stay, and not return again
14   where He does not belong, and where He lives an outcast in a world of alien thoughts. 6
15   His patience has no limits. 7 He will wait until you hear His gentle Voice within you, 
16   calling you to let Him go in peace, along with you, to where He is at home and you with Him.
17   W-pI.182.8. When you are still an instant, when the world recedes from you, when 
18   valueless ideas cease to have value in your restless mind, then will you hear His Voice. 2 So 
19   poignantly He calls to you that you will not resist Him longer. 3 In that instant He will take 
20   you to His home, and you will stay with Him in perfect stillness, silent and at peace, 
21   beyond all words, untouched by fear and doubt, sublimely certain that you are at home.
22   W-pI.182.9. Rest with Him frequently today. 2 For He was willing to become a little 
23   Child that you might learn of Him how strong is he who comes without defenses, offering only
24   love's messages to those who think he is their enemy. 3 He holds the might of Heaven in
25   His hand and calls them friend, and gives His strength to them, that they may see He 
26   would be Friend to them. 4 He asks that they protect Him, for His home is far away, and He 
27   will not return to it alone.
28   W-pI.182.10. Christ is reborn as but a little Child each time a wanderer would leave 
29   his home. 2 For he must learn that what he would protect is but this Child, Who comes 
30   defenseless and Who is protected by defenselessness. 3 Go home with Him from time to time today. 4
31   You are as much an alien here as He.
32   W-pI.182.11. Take time today to lay aside your shield which profits nothing, and lay 
33   down the spear and sword you raised against an enemy without existence. 2 Christ has called
34   you friend and brother. 3 He has even come to ask your help in letting Him go home 
35   today, completed and completely. 4 He has come as does a little child, who must beseech his 
36   father for protection and for love. 5 He rules the universe, and yet He asks unceasingly that
37   you return with Him, and take illusions as your gods no more.
38   W-pI.182.12. You have not lost your innocence. 2 It is for this you yearn. 3 This is 
39   your heart's desire. 4 This is the voice you hear, and this the call which cannot be denied.
40    5 The holy Child remains with you. 6 His home is yours. 7 Today He gives you His 
41   defenselessness, and you accept it in exchange for all the toys of battle you have made. 8 And now the
42   way is open, and the journey has an end in sight at last. 9 Be still an instant and go 
43   home with Him, and be at peace a while.
