41   LESSON 186.
42   
43   Salvation of the world depends on me.
44   W-pI.186.1. Here is the statement that will one day take all arrogance away from every 
45   mind. 2 Here is the thought of true humility, which holds no function as your own but that 
46   which has been given you. 3 It offers your acceptance of a part assigned to you, without 
47   insisting on another role. 4 It does not judge your proper role. 5 It but acknowledges the Will 
48   of God is done on earth as well as Heaven. 6 It unites all wills on earth in Heaven's 
49   plan to save the world, restoring it to Heaven's peace.
50   W-pI.186.2. Let us not fight our function. 2 We did not establish it. 3 It is not our 
0589
 1   idea. 4 The means are given us by which it will be perfectly accomplished. 5 All that we 
 2   are asked to do is to accept our part in genuine humility, and not deny with 
 3   self-deceiving arrogance that we are worthy. 6 What is given us to do, we have the strength to do. 7 
 4   Our minds are suited perfectly to take the part assigned to us by One Who knows us well.
 5   W-pI.186.3. Today's idea may seem quite sobering, until you see its meaning. 2 All it 
 6   says is that your Father still remembers you, and offers you the perfect trust He holds in 
 7   you who are His Son. 3 It does not ask that you be different in any way from what you are.
 8   4 What could humility request but this? 5 And what could arrogance deny but this? 6 
 9   Today we will not shrink from our assignment on the specious grounds that modesty is 
10   outraged. 7 It is pride that would deny the Call for God Himself.
11   W-pI.186.4. All false humility we lay aside today, that we may listen to God's Voice 
12   reveal to us what He would have us do. 2 We do not doubt our adequacy for the function He 
13   will offer us. 3 We will be certain only that He knows our strengths, our wisdom and our 
14   holiness. 4 And if He deems us worthy, so we are. 5 It is but arrogance that judges otherwise.
15   W-pI.186.5. There is one way, and only one, to be released from the imprisonment your 
16   plan to prove the false is true has brought to you. 2 Accept the plan you did not make 
17   instead. 3 Judge not your value to it. 4 If God's Voice assures you that salvation needs your 
18   part, and that the whole depends on you, be sure that it is so. 5 The arrogant must cling 
19   to words, afraid to go beyond them to experience which might affront their stance. 6 Yet 
20   are the humble free to hear the Voice which tells them what they are, and what to do.
21   W-pI.186.6. Arrogance makes an image of yourself that is not real. 2 It is this image 
22   which quails and retreats in terror, as the Voice for God assures you that you have the 
23   strength, the wisdom and the holiness to go beyond all images. 3 You are not weak, as is the 
24   image of yourself. 4 You are not ignorant and helpless. 5 Sin can not tarnish the truth in 
25   you, and misery can come not near the holy home of God.
26   W-pI.186.7. All this the Voice for God relates to you. 2 And as He speaks, the image 
27   trembles and seeks to attack the threat it does not know, sensing its basis crumble. 3 Let it 
28   go. 4 Salvation of the world depends on you, and not upon this little pile of dust. 5 
29   What can it tell the holy Son of God? 6 Why need he be concerned with it at all?
30   W-pI.186.8. And so we find our peace. 2 We will accept the function God has given us, 
31   for all illusions rest upon the weird belief that we can make another for ourselves. 3 Our
32   self-made roles are shifting, and they seem to change from mourner to ecstatic bliss of
33   love and loving. 4 We can laugh or weep, and greet the day with welcome or with tears. 
34   5 Our very being seems to change as we experience a thousand shifts in mood, and our 
35   emotions raise us high indeed, or dash us to the ground in hopelessness.
36   W-pI.186.9. Is this the Son of God? 2 Could He create such instability and call it Son?
37   3 He Who is changeless shares His attributes with His creation. 4 All the images His 
38   Son appears to make have no effect on what he is. 5 They blow across his mind like 
39   wind-swept leaves that form a patterning an instant, break apart to group again, and scamper off.
40   6 Or like mirages seen above a desert, rising from the dust.
41   W-pI.186.10. These unsubstantial images will go, and leave your mind unclouded and 
42   serene, when you accept the function given you. 2 The images you make give rise to but 
43   conflicting goals, impermanent and vague, uncertain and ambiguous. 3 Who could be constant in his 
44   efforts, or direct his energies and concentrated drive toward goals like these? 4 The 
45   functions which the world esteems are so uncertain that they change ten times an hour at their 
46   most secure. 5 What hope of gain can rest on goals like this?
47   W-pI.186.11. In lovely contrast, certain as the sun's return each morning to dispel the
48   night, your truly given function stands out clear and wholly unambiguous. 2 There is no
49   doubt of its validity. 3 It comes from One Who knows no error, and His Voice is certain
50   of Its messages. 4 They will not change, nor be in conflict. 5 All of them point to one
0590
 1   goal, and one you can attain. 6 Your plan may be impossible, but God's can never fail 
 2   because He is its Source.
 3   W-pI.186.12. Do as God's Voice directs. 2 And if It asks a thing of you which seems 
 4   impossible, remember Who it is that asks, and who would make denial. 3 Then consider this; which 
 5   is more likely to be right? 4 The Voice that speaks for the Creator of all things, Who 
 6   knows all things exactly as they are, or a distorted image of yourself, confused, bewildered,
 7    inconsistent and unsure of everything? 5 Let not its voice direct you. 6 Hear instead 
 8   a certain Voice, which tells you of a function given you by your Creator Who remembers 
 9   you, and urges that you now remember Him.
10   W-pI.186.13. His gentle Voice is calling from the known to the unknowing. 2 He would 
11   comfort you, although He knows no sorrow. 3 He would make a restitution, though He is complete;
12    a gift to you, although He knows that you have everything already. 4 He has Thoughts 
13   which answer every need His Son perceives, although He sees them not. 5 For Love must give, 
14   and what is given in His Name takes on the form most useful in a world of form.
15   W-pI.186.14. These are the forms which never can deceive, because they come from 
16   Formlessness Itself. 2 Forgiveness is an earthly form of love, which as it is in Heaven has no form.
17    3 Yet what is needed here is given here as it is needed. 4 In this form you can 
18   fulfill your function even here, although what love will mean to you when formlessness has 
19   been restored to you is greater still. 5 Salvation of the world depends on you who can 
20   forgive. 6 Such is your function here.
