23   
24   LESSON 187.
25   
26   I bless the world because I bless myself.
27   W-pI.187.1. No one can give unless he has. 2 In fact, giving is proof of having. 3 We 
28   have made this point before. 4 What seems to make it hard to credit is not this. 5 No one 
29   can doubt that you must first possess what you would give. 6 It is the second phase on 
30   which the world and true perception differ. 7 Having had and given, then the world asserts 
31   that you have lost what you possessed. 8 The truth maintains that giving will increase what
32   you possess.
33   W-pI.187.2. How is this possible? 2 For it is sure that if you give a finite thing away,
34    your body's eyes will not perceive it yours. 3 Yet we have learned that things but 
35   represent the thoughts that make them. 4 And you do not lack for proof that when you give ideas 
36   away, you strengthen them in your own mind. 5 Perhaps the form in which the thought seems 
37   to appear is changed in giving. 6 Yet it must return to him who gives. 7 Nor can the form
38   it takes be less acceptable. 8 It must be more.
39   W-pI.187.3. Ideas must first belong to you, before you give them. 2 If you are to save 
40   the world, you first accept salvation for yourself. 3 But you will not believe that this 
41   is done until you see the miracles it brings to everyone you look upon. 4 Herein is the 
42   idea of giving clarified and given meaning. 5 Now you can perceive that by your giving is 
43   your store increased.
44   W-pI.187.4. Protect all things you value by the act of giving them away, and you are 
45   sure that you will never lose them. 2 What you thought you did not have is thereby proven 
46   yours. 3 Yet value not its form. 4 For this will change and grow unrecognizable in time, 
47   however much you try to keep it safe. 5 No form endures. 6 It is the thought behind the form 
48   of things that lives unchangeable.
49   W-pI.187.5. Give gladly. 2 You can only gain thereby. 3 The thought remains, and grows 
50   in strength as it is reinforced by giving. 4 Thoughts extend as they are shared, for they
0591
 1   can not be lost. 5 There is no giver and receiver in the sense the world conceives of 
 2   them. 6 There is a giver who retains; another who will give as well. 7 And both must gain 
 3   in this exchange, for each will have the thought in form most helpful to him. 8 What he 
 4   seems to lose is always something he will value less than what will surely be returned to 
 5   him.
 6   W-pI.187.6. Never forget you give but to yourself. 2 Who understands what giving means 
 7   must laugh at the idea of sacrifice. 3 Nor can he fail to recognize the many forms which 
 8   sacrifice may take. 4 He laughs as well at pain and loss, at sickness and at grief, at poverty, 
 9   starvation and at death. 5 He recognizes sacrifice remains the one idea that stands behind them 
10   all, and in his gentle laughter are they healed.
11   W-pI.187.7. Illusion recognized must disappear. 2 Accept not suffering, and you remove 
12   the thought of suffering. 3 Your blessing lies on everyone who suffers, when you choose to
13   see all suffering as what it is. 4 The thought of sacrifice gives rise to all the forms
14   that suffering appears to take. 5 And sacrifice is an idea so mad that sanity dismisses
15   it at once.
16   W-pI.187.8. Never believe that you can sacrifice. 2 There is no place for sacrifice in 
17   what has any value. 3 If the thought occurs, its very presence proves that error has arisen
18   and correction must be made. 4 Your blessing will correct it. 5 Given first to you, it 
19   now is yours to give as well. 6 No form of sacrifice and suffering can long endure before 
20   the face of one who has forgiven and has blessed himself.
21   W-pI.187.9. The lilies that your brother offers you are laid upon your altar, with the 
22   ones you offer him beside them. 2 Who could fear to look upon such lovely holiness? 3 The 
23   great illusion of the fear of God diminishes to nothingness before the purity that you will 
24   look on here. 4 Be not afraid to look. 5 The blessedness you will behold will take away all
25   thought of form, and leave instead the perfect gift forever there, forever to increase,
26   forever yours, forever given away.
27   W-pI.187.10. Now are we one in thought, for fear has gone. 2 And here, before the altar
28   to one God, one Father, one Creator and one Thought, we stand together as one Son of 
29   God. 3 Not separate from Him Who is our Source; not distant from one brother who is part 
30   of our one Self Whose innocence has joined us all as one, we stand in blessedness, and 
31   give as we receive. 4 The Name of God is on our lips. 5 And as we look within, we see the 
32   purity of Heaven shine in our reflection of our Father's Love.
33   W-pI.187.11. Now are we blessed, and now we bless the world. 2 What we have looked upon
34   we would extend, for we would see it everywhere. 3 We would behold it shining with the 
35   grace of God in everyone. 4 We would not have it be withheld from anything we look upon. 5 
36   And to ensure this holy sight is ours, we offer it to everything we see. 6 For where we 
37   see it, it will be returned to us in form of lilies we can lay upon our altar, making it a
38   home for Innocence Itself, Who dwells in us and offers us His Holiness as ours.
39   
40   
41   
42   LESSON 188.
43   
44   The peace of God is shining in me now.
45   W-pI.188.1. Why wait for Heaven? 2 Those who seek the light are merely covering their 
46   eyes. 3 The light is in them now. 4 Enlightenment is but a recognition, not a change at all.
47    5 Light is not of the world, yet you who bear the light in you are alien here as well.
48   6 The light came with you from your native home, and stayed with you because it is your
49   own. 7 It is the only thing you bring with you from Him Who is your Source. 8 It shines
50   in you because it lights your home, and leads you back to where it came from and you 
0592
 1   are at home.
 2   W-pI.188.2. This light can not be lost. 2 Why wait to find it in the future, or believe
 3   it has been lost already, or was never there? 3 It can so easily be looked upon that 
 4   arguments which prove it is not there become ridiculous. 4 Who can deny the presence of what he 
 5   beholds in him? 5 It is not difficult to look within, for there all vision starts. 6 There is 
 6   no sight, be it of dreams or from a truer Source, that is not but the shadow of the seen 
 7   through inward vision. 7 There perception starts, and there it ends. 8 It has no source but 
 8   this.
 9   W-pI.188.3. The peace of God is shining in you now, and from your heart extends around 
10   the world. 2 It pauses to caress each living thing, and leaves a blessing with it that 
11   remains forever and forever. 3 What it gives must be eternal. 4 It removes all thoughts of the
12   ephemeral and valueless. 5 It brings renewal to all tired hearts, and lights all vision
13   as it passes by. 6 All of its gifts are given everyone, and everyone unites in giving 
14   thanks to you who give, and you who have received.
15   W-pI.188.4. The shining in your mind reminds the world of what it has forgotten, and 
16   the world restores the memory to you as well. 2 From you salvation radiates with gifts 
17   beyond all measure, given and returned. 3 To you, the giver of the gift, does God Himself 
18   give thanks. 4 And in His blessing does the light in you shine brighter, adding to the 
19   gifts you have to offer to the world.
20   W-pI.188.5. The peace of God can never be contained. 2 Who recognizes it within himself
21   must give it. 3 And the means for giving it are in his understanding. 4 He forgives 
22   because he recognized the truth in him. 5 The peace of God is shining in you now, and in all 
23   living things. 6 In quietness is it acknowledged universally. 7 For what your inward vision 
24   looks upon is your perception of the universe.
25   W-pI.188.6. Sit quietly and close your eyes. 2 The light within you is sufficient. 3 It
26   alone has power to give the gift of sight to you. 4 Exclude the outer world, and let 
27   your thoughts fly to the peace within. 5 They know the way. 6 For honest thoughts, 
28   untainted by the dream of worldly things outside yourself, become the holy messengers of God 
29   Himself.
30   W-pI.188.7. These thoughts you think with Him. 2 They recognize their home. 3 And they 
31   point surely to their Source, Where God the Father and the Son are One. 4 God's peace is 
32   shining on them, but they must remain with you as well, for they were born within your mind, 
33   as yours was born in God's. 5 They lead you back to peace, from where they came but to 
34   remind you how you must return.
35   W-pI.188.8. They heed your Father's Voice when you refuse to listen. 2 And they urge 
36   you gently to accept His Word for what you are, instead of fantasies and shadows. 3 They 
37   remind you that you are the co-creator of all things that live. 4 For as the peace of God is 
38   shining in you, it must shine on them.
39   W-pI.188.9. We practice coming nearer to the light in us today. 2 We take our wandering
40   thoughts, and gently bring them back to where they fall in line with all the thoughts 
41   we share with God. 3 We will not let them stray. 4 We let the light within our minds 
42   direct them to come home. 5 We have betrayed them, ordering that they depart from us. 6 But 
43   now we call them back, and wash them clean of strange desires and disordered wishes. 7 We 
44   restore to them the holiness of their inheritance.
45   W-pI.188.10. Thus are our minds restored with them, and we acknowledge that the peace 
46   of God still shines in us, and from us to all living things that share our life. 2 We 
47   will forgive them all, absolving all the world from what we thought it did to us. 3 For it 
48   is we who make the world as we would have it. 4 Now we choose that it be innocent, devoid
49   of sin and open to salvation. 5 And we lay our saving blessing on it, as we say: 
50   
0593
 1   6 The peace of God is shining in me now. 
 2   7 Let all things shine upon me in that peace, And let me bless them with the light in 
 3   me.
