 7   LESSON 189.
 8   
 9   I feel the Love of God within me now.
10   W-pI.189.1. There is a light in you the world can not perceive. 2 And with its eyes you
11   will not see this light, for you are blinded by the world. 3 Yet you have eyes to see 
12   it. 4 It is there for you to look upon. 5 It was not placed in you to be kept hidden from
13   your sight. 6 This light is a reflection of the thought we practice now. 7 To feel the 
14   Love of God within you is to see the world anew, shining in innocence, alive with hope, and
15   blessed with perfect charity and love.
16   W-pI.189.2. Who could feel fear in such a world as this? 2 It welcomes you, rejoices 
17   that you came, and sings your praises as it keeps you safe from every form of danger and of
18   pain. 3 It offers you a warm and gentle home in which to stay a while. 4 It blesses you
19   throughout the day, and watches through the night as silent guardian of your holy sleep.
20    5 It sees salvation in you, and protects the light in you, in which it sees its own. 6
21   It offers you its flowers and its snow, in thankfulness for your benevolence.
22   W-pI.189.3. This is the world the Love of God reveals. 2 It is so different from the 
23   world you see through darkened eyes of malice and of fear, that one belies the other. 3 Only
24   one can be perceived at all. 4 The other one is wholly meaningless. 5 A world in which 
25   forgiveness shines on everything, and peace offers its gentle light to everyone, is inconceivable 
26   to those who see a world of hatred rising from attack, poised to avenge, to murder and 
27   destroy.
28   W-pI.189.4. Yet is the world of hatred equally unseen and inconceivable to those who 
29   feel God's Love in them. 2 Their world reflects the quietness and peace that shines in them;
30    the gentleness and innocence they see surrounding them; the joy with which they look 
31   out from the endless wells of joy within. 3 What they have felt in them they look upon, 
32   and see its sure reflection everywhere.
33   W-pI.189.5. What would you see? 2 The choice is given you. 3 But learn and do not let 
34   your mind forget this law of seeing: You will look upon that which you feel within. 4 If 
35   hatred finds a place within your heart, you will perceive a fearful world, held cruelly in 
36   death's sharp-pointed, bony fingers. 5 If you feel the Love of God within you, you will look 
37   out on a world of mercy and of love.
38   W-pI.189.6. Today we pass illusions, as we seek to reach to what is true in us, and 
39   feel its all-embracing tenderness, its Love which knows us perfect as itself, its sight 
40   which is the gift its Love bestows on us. 2 We learn the way today. 3 It is as sure as Love 
41   itself, to which it carries us. 4 For its simplicity avoids the snares the foolish 
42   convolutions of the world's apparent reasoning but serve to hide.
43   W-pI.189.7. Simply do this: Be still, and lay aside all thoughts of what you are and 
44   what God is; all concepts you have learned about the world; all images you hold about 
45   yourself. 2 Empty your mind of everything it thinks is either true or false, or good or bad, of
46   every thought it judges worthy, and all the ideas of which it is ashamed. 3 Hold onto 
47   nothing. 4 Do not bring with you one thought the past has taught, nor one belief you ever 
48   learned before from anything. 5 Forget this world, forget this course, and come with wholly 
49   empty hands unto your God.
50   W-pI.189.8. Is it not He Who knows the way to you? 2 You need not know the way to Him. 
0594
 1   3 Your part is simply to allow all obstacles that you have interposed between the Son 
 2   and God the Father to be quietly removed forever. 4 God will do His part in joyful and 
 3   immediate response. 5 Ask and receive. 6 But do not make demands, nor point the road to God by 
 4   which He should appear to you. 7 The way to reach Him is merely to let Him be. 8 For in that
 5   way is your reality proclaimed as well.
 6   W-pI.189.9. And so today we do not choose the way in which we go to Him. 2 But we do 
 7   choose to let Him come. 3 And with this choice we rest. 4 And in our quiet hearts and open 
 8   minds, His Love will blaze its pathway of itself. 5 What has not been denied is surely there,
 9    if it be true and can be surely reached. 6 God knows His Son, and knows the way to him.
10    7 He does not need His Son to show Him how to find His way. 8 Through every opened 
11   door His Love shines outward from its home within, and lightens up the world in innocence.
12   
13   W-pI.189.10.  <Father, we do not know the way to You. 2 But we have called, and You 
14   have answered us. 3 We will not interfere. 4 Salvation's ways are not our own, for they 
15   belong to You. 5 And it is unto You we look for them. 6 Our hands are open to receive Your 
16   gifts. 7 We have no thoughts we think apart from You, and cherish no beliefs of what we are,
17   or Who created us. 8 Yours is the way that we would find and follow. 9 And we ask but 
18   that Your Will, which is our own as well, be done in us and in the world, that it become a 
19   part of Heaven now. 10 Amen.>
