0600
 1   LESSON 194.
 2   
 3   I place the future in the Hands of God.
 4   W-pI.194.1. Today's idea takes another step toward quick salvation, and a giant stride 
 5   it is indeed! 2 So great the distance is that it encompasses, it sets you down just short
 6   of Heaven, with the goal in sight and obstacles behind. 3 Your foot has reached the 
 7   lawns that welcome you to Heaven's gate; the quiet place of peace, where you await with 
 8   certainty the final step of God. 4 How far are we progressing now from earth! 5 How close are we
 9   approaching to our goal! 6 How short the journey still to be pursued!
10   W-pI.194.2. Accept today's idea, and you have passed all anxiety, all pits of hell, all
11   blackness of depression, thoughts of sin, and devastation brought about by guilt. 2 
12   Accept today's idea, and you have released the world from all imprisonment by loosening the 
13   heavy chains that locked the door to freedom on it. 3 You are saved, and your salvation thus
14   becomes the gift you give the world, because you have received.
15   W-pI.194.3. In no one instant is depression felt, or pain experienced or loss perceived.
16    2 In no one instant sorrow can be set upon a throne, and worshipped faithfully. 3 In 
17   no one instant can one even die. 4 And so each instant given unto God in passing, with 
18   the next one given Him already, is a time of your release from sadness, pain and even 
19   death itself.
20   W-pI.194.4. God holds your future as He holds your past and present. 2 They are one to 
21   Him, and so they should be one to you. 3 Yet in this world, the temporal progression still
22   seems real. 4 And so you are not asked to understand the lack of sequence really found 
23   in time. 5 You are but asked to let the future go, and place it in God's Hands. 6 And you
24   will see by your experience that you have laid the past and present in His Hands as 
25   well, because the past will punish you no more, and future dread will now be meaningless.
26   W-pI.194.5. Release the future. 2 For the past is gone, and what is present, freed from
27   its bequest of grief and misery, of pain and loss, becomes the instant in which time 
28   escapes the bondage of illusions where it runs its pitiless, inevitable course. 3 Then is each
29   instant which was slave to time transformed into a holy instant, when the light that 
30   was kept hidden in God's Son is freed to bless the world. 4 Now is he free, and all his 
31   glory shines upon a world made free with him, to share his holiness.
32   W-pI.194.6. If you can see the lesson for today as the deliverance it really is, you 
33   will not hesitate to give as much consistent effort as you can, to make it be a part of you.
34    2 As it becomes a thought that rules your mind, a habit in your problem-solving 
35   repertoire, a way of quick reaction to temptation, you extend your learning to the world. 3 And 
36   as you learn to see salvation in all things, so will the world perceive that it is saved.
37   W-pI.194.7. What worry can beset the one who gives his future to the loving Hands of 
38   God? 2 What can he suffer? 3 What can cause him pain, or bring experience of loss to him? 
39   4 What can he fear? 5 And what can he regard except with love? 6 For he who has escaped 
40   all fear of future pain has found his way to present peace, and certainty of care the 
41   world can never threaten. 7 He is sure that his perception may be faulty, but will never 
42   lack correction. 8 He is free to choose again when he has been deceived; to change his mind
43   when he has made mistakes.
44   W-pI.194.8. Place, then, your future in the Hands of God. 2 For thus you call the 
45   memory of Him to come again, replacing all your thoughts of sin and evil with the truth of 
46   love. 3 Think you the world could fail to gain thereby, and every living creature not 
47   respond with healed perception? 4 Who entrusts himself to God has also placed the world within
48   the Hands to which he has himself appealed for comfort and security. 5 He lays aside 
49   the sick illusions of the world along with his, and offers peace to both.
50   W-pI.194.9. Now are we saved indeed. 2 For in God's Hands we rest untroubled, sure that
0601
 1   only good can come to us. 3 If we forget, we will be gently reassured. 4 If we accept 
 2   an unforgiving thought, it will be soon replaced by love's reflection. 5 And if we are 
 3   tempted to attack, we will appeal to Him Who guards our rest to make the choice for us that 
 4   leaves temptation far behind. 6 No longer is the world our enemy, for we have chosen that we 
 5   be its friend.
 6   
 7   
 8   
 9   LESSON 195.
10   
11   Love is the way I walk in gratitude.
12   W-pI.195.1. Gratitude is a lesson hard to learn for those who look upon the world amiss.
13    2 The most that they can do is see themselves as better off than others. 3 And they 
14   try to be content because another seems to suffer more than they. 4 How pitiful and 
15   deprecating are such thoughts! 5 For who has cause for thanks while others have less cause? 6 And 
16   who could suffer less because he sees another suffer more? 7 Your gratitude is due to Him 
17   alone Who made all cause of sorrow disappear throughout the world.
18   W-pI.195.2. It is insane to offer thanks because of suffering. 2 But it is equally 
19   insane to fail in gratitude to One Who offers you the certain means whereby all pain is 
20   healed, and suffering replaced with laughter and with happiness. 3 Nor could the even partly 
21   sane refuse to take the steps which He directs, and follow in the way He sets before them, 
22   to escape a prison that they thought contained no door to the deliverance they now 
23   perceive.
24   W-pI.195.3. Your brother is your "enemy" because you see in him the rival for your 
25   peace; a plunderer who takes his joy from you, and leaves you nothing but a black despair so
26   bitter and relentless that there is no hope remaining. 2 Now is vengeance all there is 
27   to wish for. 3 Now can you but try to bring him down to lie in death with you, as useless
28   as yourself; as little left within his grasping fingers as in yours.
29   W-pI.195.4. You do not offer God your gratitude because your brother is more slave than
30   you, nor could you sanely be enraged if he seems freer. 2 Love makes no comparisons. 3 
31   And gratitude can only be sincere if it be joined to love. 4 We offer thanks to God our 
32   Father that in us all things will find their freedom. 5 It will never be that some are loosed
33   while others still are bound. 6 For who can bargain in the name of love?
34   W-pI.195.5. Therefore give thanks, but in sincerity. 2 And let your gratitude make room
35   for all who will escape with you; the sick, the weak, the needy and afraid, and those 
36   who mourn a seeming loss or feel apparent pain, who suffer cold or hunger, or who walk the
37   way of hatred and the path of death. 3 All these go with you. 4 Let us not compare 
38   ourselves with them, for thus we split them off from our awareness of the unity we share with 
39   them, as they must share with us.
40   W-pI.195.6. We thank our Father for one thing alone; that we are separate from no 
41   living thing, and therefore one with Him. 2 And we rejoice that no exceptions ever can be 
42   made which would reduce our wholeness, nor impair or change our function to complete the 
43   One Who is Himself completion. 3 We give thanks for every living thing, for otherwise we 
44   offer thanks for nothing, and we fail to recognize the gifts of God to us.
45   W-pI.195.7. Then let our brothers lean their tired heads against our shoulders as they 
46   rest a while. 2 We offer thanks for them. 3 For if we can direct them to the peace that we 
47   would find, the way is opening at last to us. 4 An ancient door is swinging free again; a 
48   long forgotten Word re-echoes in our memory, and gathers clarity as we are willing once 
49   again to hear.
50   W-pI.195.8. Walk, then, in gratitude the way of love. 2 For hatred is forgotten when we
0602
 1   lay comparisons aside. 3 What more remains as obstacles to peace? 4 The fear of God is 
 2   now undone at last, and we forgive without comparing. 5 Thus we cannot choose to overlook 
 3   some things, and yet retain some other things still locked away as "sins." 6 When your 
 4   forgiveness is complete you will have total gratitude, for you will see that everything has earned
 5   the right to love by being loving, even as your Self.
 6   W-pI.195.9. Today we learn to think of gratitude in place of anger, malice and revenge.
 7   2 We have been given everything. 3 If we refuse to recognize it, we are not entitled 
 8   therefore to our bitterness, and to a self-perception which regards us in a place of merciless 
 9   pursuit, where we are badgered ceaselessly, and pushed about without a thought or care for us 
10   or for our future. 4 Gratitude becomes the single thought we substitute for these insane 
11   perceptions. 5 God has cared for us, and calls us Son. 6 Can there be more than this?
12   W-pI.195.10. Our gratitude will pave the way to Him, and shorten our learning time by 
13   more than you could ever dream of. 2 Gratitude goes hand in hand with love, and where one 
14   is the other must be found. 3 For gratitude is but an aspect of the Love which is the 
15   Source of all creation. 4 God gives thanks to you, His Son, for being what you are; His Own 
16   completion and the Source of love, along with Him. 5 Your gratitude to Him is one with His to you.
17    6 For love can walk no road except the way of gratitude, and thus we go who walk the 
18   way to God.
19   
20   
21   
22   LESSON 196.
23   
24   It can be but myself I crucify.
25   W-pI.196.1. When this is firmly understood and kept in full awareness, you will not 
26   attempt to harm yourself, nor make your body slave to vengeance. 2 You will not attack 
27   yourself, and you will realize that to attack another is but to attack yourself. 3 You will be 
28   free of the insane belief that to attack a brother saves yourself. 4 And you will 
29   understand his safety is your own, and in his healing you are healed.
30   W-pI.196.2. Perhaps at first you will not understand how mercy, limitless and with all 
31   things held in its sure protection, can be found in the idea we practice for today. 2 It may,
32   in fact, appear to be a sign that punishment can never be escaped because the ego, 
33   under what it sees as threat, is quick to cite the truth to save its lies. 3 Yet must it 
34   fail to understand the truth it uses thus. 4 But you can learn to see these foolish 
35   applications, and deny the meaning they appear to have.
36   W-pI.196.3. Thus do you also teach your mind that you are not an ego. 2 For the ways in
37   which the ego would distort the truth will not deceive you longer. 3 You will not 
38   believe you are a body to be crucified. 4 And you will see within today's idea the light of 
39   resurrection, looking past all thoughts of crucifixion and of death, to thoughts of liberation and 
40   of life.
41   W-pI.196.4. Today's idea is one step we take in leading us from bondage to the state of
42   perfect freedom. 2 Let us take this step today, that we may quickly go the way 
43   salvation shows us, taking every step in its appointed sequence, as the mind relinquishes its 
44   burdens one by one. 3 It is not time we need for this. 4 It is but willingness. 5 For what 
45   would seem to need a thousand years can easily be done in just one instant by the grace of 
46   God.
47   W-pI.196.5. The dreary, hopeless thought that you can make attacks on others and escape
48   yourself has nailed you to the cross. 2 Perhaps it seemed to be salvation. 3 Yet it 
49   merely stood for the belief the fear of God is real. 4 And what is that but hell? 5 Who could
50   believe his Father is his deadly enemy, separate from him, and waiting to destroy his 
0603
 1   life and blot him from the universe, without the fear of hell upon his heart?
 2   W-pI.196.6. Such is the form of madness you believe, if you accept the fearful thought 
 3   you can attack another and be free yourself. 2 Until this form is changed, there is no 
 4   hope. 3 Until you see that this, at least, must be entirely impossible, how could there be 
 5   escape? 4 The fear of God is real to anyone who thinks this thought is true. 5 And he will 
 6   not perceive its foolishness, or even see that it is there, so that it would be possible 
 7   to question it.
 8   W-pI.196.7. To question it at all, its form must first be changed at least as much as 
 9   will permit fear of retaliation to abate, and the responsibility returned to some extent to
10   you. 2 From there you can at least consider if you want to go along this painful path. 
11   3 Until this shift has been accomplished, you can not perceive that it is but your 
12   thoughts that bring you fear, and your deliverance depends on you.
13   W-pI.196.8. Our next steps will be easy, if you take this one today. 2 From there we go
14   ahead quite rapidly. 3 For once you understand it is impossible that you be hurt except
15   by your own thoughts, the fear of God must disappear. 4 You cannot then believe that 
16   fear is caused without. 5 And God, Whom you had thought to banish, can be welcomed back 
17   within the holy mind He never left.
18   W-pI.196.9. Salvation's song can certainly be heard in the idea we practice for today. 
19   2 If it can but be you you crucify, you did not hurt the world, and need not fear its 
20   vengeance and pursuit. 3 Nor need you hide in terror from the deadly fear of God projection 
21   hides behind. 4 The thing you dread the most is your salvation. 5 You are strong, and it is 
22   strength you want. 6 And you are free, and glad of freedom. 7 You have sought to be both weak 
23   and bound, because you feared your strength and freedom. 8 Yet salvation lies in them.
24   W-pI.196.10. There is an instant in which terror seems to grip your mind so wholly that
25   escape appears quite hopeless. 2 When you realize, once and for all, that it is you you
26   fear, the mind perceives itself as split. 3 And this had been concealed while you 
27   believed attack could be directed outward, and returned from outside to within. 4 It seemed to 
28   be an enemy outside you had to fear. 5 And thus a god outside yourself became your mortal
29   enemy; the source of fear.
30   W-pI.196.11. Now, for an instant, is a murderer perceived within you, eager for your 
31   death, intent on plotting punishment for you until the time when it can kill at last. 2 Yet 
32   in this instant is the time as well in which salvation comes. 3 For fear of God has 
33   disappeared. 4 And you can call on Him to save you from illusions by His Love, calling Him Father 
34   and yourself His Son. 5 Pray that the instant may be soon,--today. 6 Step back from fear, 
35   and make advance to love.
36   W-pI.196.12. There is no Thought of God that does not go with you to help you reach 
37   that instant, and to go beyond it quickly, surely and forever. 2 When the fear of God is 
38   gone, there are no obstacles that still remain between you and the holy peace of God. 3 How
39   kind and merciful is the idea we practice! 4 Give it welcome, as you should, for it is 
40   your release. 5 It is indeed but you your mind can try to crucify. 6 Yet your redemption, 
41   too, will come from you.
42   
43   
44   
45   LESSON 197.
46   
47   It can be but my gratitude I earn.
48   W-pI.197.1. Here is the second step we take to free your mind from the belief in 
49   outside force pitted against your own. 2 You make attempts at kindness and forgiveness. 3 Yet 
50   you turn them to attack again, unless you find external gratitude and lavish thanks. 4 
0604
 1   Your gifts must be received with honor, lest they be withdrawn. 5 And so you think God's 
 2   gifts are loans at best; at worst, deceptions which would cheat you of defenses, to ensure 
 3   that when He strikes He will not fail to kill.
 4   W-pI.197.2. How easily are God and guilt confused by those who know not what their 
 5   thoughts can do. 2 Deny your strength, and weakness must become salvation to you. 3 See 
 6   yourself as bound, and bars become your home. 4 Nor will you leave the prison house, or claim 
 7   your strength, until guilt and salvation are not seen as one, and freedom and salvation are
 8   perceived as joined, with strength beside them, to be sought and claimed, and found and
 9   fully recognized.
10   W-pI.197.3. The world must thank you when you offer it release from your illusions. 2 
11   Yet your thanks belong to you as well, for its release can only mirror yours. 3 Your 
12   gratitude is all your gifts require, that they be a lasting offering of a thankful heart, 
13   released from hell forever. 4 Is it this you would undo by taking back your gifts, because they
14   were not honored? 5 It is you who honor them and give them fitting thanks, for it is 
15   you who have received the gifts.
16   W-pI.197.4. It does not matter if another thinks your gifts unworthy. 2 In his mind 
17   there is a part that joins with yours in thanking you. 3 It does not matter if your gifts 
18   seem lost and ineffectual. 4 They are received where they are given. 5 In your gratitude 
19   are they accepted universally, and thankfully acknowledged by the Heart of God Himself. 6 
20   And would you take them back, when He has gratefully accepted them?
21   W-pI.197.5. God blesses every gift you give to Him, and every gift is given Him, 
22   because it can be given only to yourself. 2 And what belongs to God must be His Own. 3 Yet you
23   will never realize His gifts are sure, eternal, changeless, limitless, forever giving 
24   out, extending love and adding to your never-ending joy while you forgive but to attack 
25   again.
26   W-pI.197.6. Withdraw the gifts you give, and you will think that what is given you has 
27   been withdrawn. 2 But learn to let forgiveness take away the sins you think you see outside
28   yourself, and you can never think the gifts of God are lent but for a little while, 
29   before He snatches them away again in death. 3 For death will have no meaning for you then.
30   W-pI.197.7. And with the end of this belief is fear forever over. 2 Thank your Self for
31   this, for He is grateful only unto God, and He gives thanks for you unto Himself. 3 To 
32   everyone who lives will Christ yet come, for everyone must live and move in Him. 4 His Being in
33   His Father is secure, because Their Will is One. 5 Their gratitude to all They have 
34   created has no end, for gratitude remains a part of love.
35   W-pI.197.8. Thanks be to you, the holy Son of God. 2 For as you were created, you 
36   contain all things within your Self. 3 And you are still as God created you. 4 Nor can you dim
37   the light of your perfection. 5 In your heart the Heart of God is laid. 6 He holds you 
38   dear, because you are Himself. 7 All gratitude belongs to you, because of what you are.
39   W-pI.197.9. Give thanks as you receive it. 2 Be you free of all ingratitude to anyone 
40   who makes your Self complete. 3 And from this Self is no one left outside. 4 Give thanks 
41   for all the countless channels which extend this Self. 5 All that you do is given unto Him.
42    6 All that you think can only be His Thoughts, sharing with Him the holy Thoughts of 
43   God. 7 Earn now the gratitude you have denied yourself when you forgot the function God 
44   has given you. 8 But never think that He has ever ceased to offer thanks to you.
45   
46   
47   
48   LESSON 198.
49   
50   Only my condemnation injures me.
0605
 1   W-pI.198.1. Injury is impossible. 2 And yet illusion makes illusion. 3 If you can 
 2   condemn, you can be injured. 4 For you have believed that you can injure, and the right you 
 3   have established for yourself can be now used against you, till you lay it down as 
 4   valueless, unwanted and unreal. 5 Then does illusion cease to have effects, and those it seemed 
 5   to have will be undone. 6 Then are you free, for freedom is your gift, and you can now 
 6   receive the gift you gave.
 7   W-pI.198.2. Condemn and you are made a prisoner. 2 Forgive and you are freed. 3 Such is
 8   the law that rules perception. 4 It is not a law that knowledge understands, for 
 9   freedom is a part of knowledge. 5 To condemn is thus impossible in truth. 6 What seems to be 
10   its influence and its effects have not occurred at all. 7 Yet must we deal with them a 
11   while as if they had. 8 Illusion makes illusion. 9 Except one. 10 Forgiveness is illusion 
12   that is answer to the rest.
13   W-pI.198.3. Forgiveness sweeps all other dreams away, and though it is itself a dream, 
14   it breeds no others. 2 All illusions save this one must multiply a thousandfold. 3 But 
15   this is where illusions end. 4 Forgiveness is the end of dreams, because it is a dream of 
16   waking. 5 It is not itself the truth. 6 Yet does it point to where the truth must be, and 
17   gives direction with the certainty of God Himself. 7 It is a dream in which the Son of God 
18   awakens to his Self and to his Father, knowing They are One.
19   W-pI.198.4. Forgiveness is the only road that leads out of disaster, past all suffering,
20    and finally away from death. 2 How could there be another way, when this one is the 
21   plan of God Himself? 3 And why would you oppose it, quarrel with it, seek to find a 
22   thousand ways in which it must be wrong; a thousand other possibilities?
23   W-pI.198.5. Is it not wiser to be glad you hold the answer to your problems in your 
24   hand? 2 Is it not more intelligent to thank the One Who gives salvation, and accept His 
25   gift with gratitude? 3 And is it not a kindness to yourself to hear His Voice and learn the
26   simple lessons He would teach, instead of trying to dismiss His words, and substitute 
27   your own in place of His?
28   W-pI.198.6. His words will work. 2 His words will save. 3 His words contain all hope, 
29   all blessing and all joy that ever can be found upon this earth. 4 His words are born in 
30   God, and come to you with Heaven's love upon them. 5 Those who hear His words have heard 
31   the song of Heaven. 6 For these are the words in which all merge as one at last. 7 And as 
32   this one will fade away, the Word of God will come to take its place, for it will be 
33   remembered then and loved.
34   W-pI.198.7. This world has many seeming separate haunts where mercy has no meaning, and
35   attack appears as justified. 2 Yet all are one; a place where death is offered to God's
36   Son and to his Father. 3 You may think They have accepted. 4 But if you will look again
37   upon the place where you beheld Their blood, you will perceive a miracle instead. 5 How
38   foolish to believe that They could die! 6 How foolish to believe you can attack! 7 How 
39   mad to think that you could be condemned, and that the holy Son of God can die!
40   W-pI.198.8. The stillness of your Self remains unmoved, untouched by thoughts like 
41   these, and unaware of any condemnation which could need forgiveness. 2 Dreams of any kind 
42   are strange and alien to the truth. 3 And what but truth could have a Thought which builds
43   a bridge to it that brings illusions to the other side?
44   W-pI.198.9. Today we practice letting freedom come to make its home with you. 2 The 
45   truth bestows these words upon your mind, that you may find the key to light and let the 
46   darkness end: 
47   
48   3 Only my condemnation injures me. 
49   4 Only my own forgiveness sets me free. 
50   
0606
 1   5 Do not forget today that there can be no form of suffering that fails to hide an 
 2   unforgiving thought. 6 Nor can there be a form of pain forgiveness cannot heal.
 3   W-pI.198.10. Accept the one illusion which proclaims there is no condemnation in God's 
 4   Son, and Heaven is remembered instantly; the world forgotten, all its weird beliefs 
 5   forgotten with it, as the face of Christ appears unveiled at last in this one dream. 2 This is 
 6   the gift the Holy Spirit holds for you from God your Father. 3 Let today be celebrated 
 7   both on earth and in your holy home as well. 4 Be kind to Both, as you forgive the 
 8   trespasses you thought Them guilty of, and see your innocence shining upon you from the face of 
 9   Christ.
10   W-pI.198.11. Now is there silence all around the world. 2 Now is there stillness where 
11   before there was a frantic rush of thoughts that made no sense. 3 Now is there tranquil light
12   across the face of earth, made quiet in a dreamless sleep. 4 And now the Word of God 
13   alone remains upon it. 5 Only that can be perceived an instant longer. 6 Then are symbols 
14   done, and everything you ever thought you made completely vanished from the mind that God 
15   forever knows to be His only Son.
16   W-pI.198.12. There is no condemnation in him. 2 He is perfect in his holiness. 3 He 
17   needs no thoughts of mercy. 4 Who could give him gifts when everything is his? 5 And who 
18   could dream of offering forgiveness to the Son of Sinlessness Itself, so like to Him Whose 
19   Son he is, that to behold the Son is to perceive no more, and only know the Father? 6 In 
20   this vision of the Son, so brief that not an instant stands between this single sight and 
21   timelessness itself, you see the vision of yourself, and then you disappear forever into God.
22   W-pI.198.13. Today we come still nearer to the end of everything that yet would stand 
23   between this vision and our sight. 2 And we are glad that we have come this far, and recognize
24   that He Who brought us here will not forsake us now. 3 For He would give to us the gift
25   that God has given us through Him today. 4 Now is the time for your deliverance. 5 The 
26   time has come. 6 The time has come today.
27   
28   
29   
30   LESSON 199.
31   
32   I am not a body. am free.
33   W-pI.199.1. Freedom must be impossible as long as you perceive a body as yourself. 2 
34   The body is a limit. 3 Who would seek for freedom in a body looks for it where it can not 
35   be found. 4 The mind can be made free when it no longer sees itself as in a body, firmly 
36   tied to it and sheltered by its presence. 5 If this were the truth, the mind were 
37   vulnerable indeed!
38   W-pI.199.2. The mind that serves the Holy Spirit is unlimited forever, in all ways, 
39   beyond the laws of time and space, unbound by any preconceptions, and with strength and power
40   to do whatever it is asked. 2 Attack thoughts cannot enter such a mind, because it has 
41   been given to the Source of love, and fear can never enter in a mind that has attached 
42   itself to love. 3 It rests in God. 4 And who can be afraid who lives in Innocence, and only 
43   loves?
44   W-pI.199.3. It is essential for your progress in this course that you accept today's 
45   idea, and hold it very dear. 2 Be not concerned that to the ego it is quite insane. 3 The 
46   ego holds the body dear because it dwells in it, and lives united with the home that it 
47   has made. 4 It is a part of the illusion that has sheltered it from being found illusory 
48   itself.
49   W-pI.199.4. Here does it hide, and here it can be seen as what it is. 2 Declare your 
50   innocence and you are free. 3 The body disappears, because you have no need of it except the 
0607
 1   need the Holy Spirit sees. 4 For this, the body will appear as useful form for what the 
 2   mind must do. 5 It thus becomes a vehicle which helps forgiveness be extended to the 
 3   all-inclusive goal that it must reach, according to God's plan.
 4   W-pI.199.5. Cherish today's idea, and practice it today and every day. 2 Make it a part
 5   of every practice period you take. 3 There is no thought that will not gain thereby in 
 6   power to help the world, and none which will not gain in added gifts to you as well. 4 We 
 7   sound the call of freedom round the world with this idea. 5 And would you be exempt from the
 8   acceptance of the gifts you give?
 9   W-pI.199.6. The Holy Spirit is the home of minds that seek for freedom. 2 In Him they 
10   have found what they have sought. 3 The body's purpose now is unambiguous. 4 And it becomes
11   perfect in the ability to serve an undivided goal. 5 In conflict-free and unequivocal 
12   response to mind with but the thought of freedom as its goal, the body serves, and serves its 
13   purpose well. 6 Without the power to enslave, it is a worthy servant of the freedom which the 
14   mind within the Holy Spirit seeks.
15   W-pI.199.7. Be free today. 2 And carry freedom as your gift to those who still believe 
16   they are enslaved within a body. 3 Be you free, so that the Holy Spirit can make use of 
17   your escape from bondage, to set free the many who perceive themselves as bound and 
18   helpless and afraid. 4 Let love replace their fears through you. 5 Accept salvation now, and 
19   give your mind to Him Who calls to you to make this gift to Him. 6 For He would give you 
20   perfect freedom, perfect joy, and hope that finds its full accomplishment in God.
21   W-pI.199.8. You are God's Son. 2 In immortality you live forever. 3 Would you not 
22   return your mind to this? 4 Then practice well the thought the Holy Spirit gives you for 
23   today. 5 Your brothers stand released with you in it; the world is blessed along with you, 
24   God's Son will weep no more, and Heaven offers thanks for the increase of joy your practice 
25   brings even to it. 6 And God Himself extends His Love and happiness each time you say: 
26   
27   7 I am not a body. 8 I am free. 9 I hear the Voice that God has given me, and it is 
28   only this my mind obeys.
29   
30   
31   
32   LESSON 200.
33   
34   There is no peace except the peace of God.
35   W-pI.200.1. Seek you no further. 2 You will not find peace except the peace of God. 3 
36   Accept this fact, and save yourself the agony of yet more bitter disappointments, bleak 
37   despair, and sense of icy hopelessness and doubt. 4 Seek you no further. 5 There is nothing 
38   else for you to find except the peace of God, unless you seek for misery and pain.
39   W-pI.200.2. This is the final point to which each one must come at last, to lay aside 
40   all hope of finding happiness where there is none; of being saved by what can only hurt; 
41   of making peace of chaos, joy of pain, and Heaven out of hell. 2 Attempt no more to win 
42   through losing, nor to die to live. 3 You cannot but be asking for defeat.
43   W-pI.200.3. Yet you can ask as easily for love, for happiness, and for eternal life in 
44   peace that has no ending. 2 Ask for this, and you can only win. 3 To ask for what you have 
45   already must succeed. 4 To ask that what is false be true can only fail. 5 Forgive yourself 
46   for vain imaginings, and seek no longer what you cannot find. 6 For what could be more 
47   foolish than to seek and seek and seek again for hell, when you have but to look with open 
48   eyes to find that Heaven lies before you, through a door that opens easily to welcome you?
49   W-pI.200.4. Come home. 2 You have not found your happiness in foreign places and in 
50   alien forms that have no meaning to you, though you sought to make them meaningful. 3 This 
0608
 1   world is not where you belong. 4 You are a stranger here. 5 But it is given you to find the 
 2   means whereby the world no longer seems to be a prison house or jail for anyone.
 3   W-pI.200.5. Freedom is given you where you beheld but chains and iron doors. 2 But you 
 4   must change your mind about the purpose of the world, if you would find escape. 3 You will 
 5   be bound till all the world is seen by you as blessed, and everyone made free of your 
 6   mistakes and honored as he is. 4 You made him not; no more yourself. 5 And as you free the one,
 7   the other is accepted as he is.
 8   W-pI.200.6. What does forgiveness do? 2 In truth it has no function, and does nothing. 
 9   3 For it is unknown in Heaven. 4 It is only hell where it is needed, and where it must 
10   serve a mighty function. 5 Is not the escape of God's beloved Son from evil dreams that he 
11   imagines, yet believes are true, a worthy purpose? 6 Who could hope for more, while there 
12   appears to be a choice to make between success and failure; love and fear?
13   W-pI.200.7. There is no peace except the peace of God, because He has one Son who 
14   cannot make a world in opposition to God's Will and to his own, which is the same as His. 2 
15   What could he hope to find in such a world? 3 It cannot have reality, because it never was 
16   created. 4 Is it here that he would seek for peace? 5 Or must he see that, as he looks on it, 
17   the world can but deceive? 6 Yet can he learn to look on it another way, and find the 
18   peace of God.
19   W-pI.200.8. Peace is the bridge that everyone will cross, to leave this world behind. 2
20   But peace begins within the world perceived as different, and leading from this fresh 
21   perception to the gate of Heaven and the way beyond. 3 Peace is the answer to conflicting goals, 
22   to senseless journeys, frantic, vain pursuits, and meaningless endeavors. 4 Now the way 
23   is easy, sloping gently toward the bridge where freedom lies within the peace of God.
24   W-pI.200.9. Let us not lose our way again today. 2 We go to Heaven, and the path is 
25   straight. 3 Only if we attempt to wander can there be delay, and needless wasted time on thorny
26   byways. 4 God alone is sure, and He will guide our footsteps. 5 He will not desert His 
27   Son in need, nor let him stray forever from his home. 6 The Father calls; the Son will 
28   hear. 7 And that is all there is to what appears to be a world apart from God, where bodies
29   have reality.
30   W-pI.200.10. Now is there silence. 2 Seek no further. 3 You have come to where the road
31   is carpeted with leaves of false desires, fallen from the trees of hopelessness you 
32   sought before. 4 Now are they underfoot. 5 And you look up and on toward Heaven, with the 
33   body's eyes but serving for an instant longer now. 6 Peace is already recognized at last, and
34   you can feel its soft embrace surround your heart and mind with comfort and with love.
35   W-pI.200.11. Today we seek no idols. 2 Peace can not be found in them. 3 The peace of 
36   God is ours, and only this will we accept and want. 4 Peace be to us today. 5 For we have 
37   found a simple, happy way to leave the world of ambiguity, and to replace our shifting goals
38   and solitary dreams with single purpose and companionship. 6 For peace is union, if it 
39   be of God. 7 We seek no further. 8 We are close to home, and draw still nearer every time
40   we say: 
41   
42   9 There is no peace except the peace of God, And I am glad and thankful it is so.
43   
44   
45   
46   REVIEW VI
47   
48   Introduction
49   W-pI.rVI.in.1. For this review we take but one idea each day, and practice it as often 
50   as is possible. 2 Besides the time you give morning and evening, which should not be less
0609
 1   than fifteen minutes, and the hourly remembrances you make throughout the day, use the 
 2   idea as often as you can between them. 3 Each of these ideas alone would be sufficient for 
 3   salvation, if it were learned truly. 4 Each would be enough to give release to you and to the 
 4   world from every form of bondage, and invite the memory of God to come again.
 5   W-pI.rVI.in.2. With this in mind we start our practicing, in which we carefully review 
 6   the thoughts the Holy Spirit has bestowed on us in our last twenty lessons. 2 Each 
 7   contains the whole curriculum if understood, practiced, accepted, and applied to all the 
 8   seeming happenings throughout the day. 3 One is enough. 4 But from that one, there must be no 
 9   exceptions made. 5 And so we need to use them all and let them blend as one, as each contributes 
10   to the whole we learn.
11   W-pI.rVI.in.3. These practice sessions, like our last review, are centered round a 
12   central theme with which we start and end each lesson. 2 It is this: 
13   
14   3 I am not a body. 4 I am free. 
15   5 For I am still as God created me. 
16   
17   6 The day begins and ends with this. 7 And we repeat it every time the hour strikes, or
18   we remember, in between, we have a function that transcends the world we see. 8 Beyond 
19   this, and a repetition of the special thought we practice for the day, no form of exercise 
20   is urged, except a deep relinquishment of everything that clutters up the mind, and makes
21   it deaf to reason, sanity and simple truth.
22   W-pI.rVI.in.4. We will attempt to get beyond all words and special forms of practicing 
23   for this review. 2 For we attempt, this time, to reach a quickened pace along a shorter 
24   path to the serenity and peace of God. 3 We merely close our eyes, and then forget all that
25   we thought we knew and understood. 4 For thus is freedom given us from all we did not 
26   know and failed to understand.
27   W-pI.rVI.in.5. There is but one exception to this lack of structuring. 2 Permit no idle
28   thought to go unchallenged. 3 If you notice one, deny its hold and hasten to assure 
29   your mind that this is not what it would have. 4 Then gently let the thought which you 
30   denied be given up, in sure and quick exchange for the idea we practice for the day.
31   W-pI.rVI.in.6. When you are tempted, hasten to proclaim your freedom from temptation, 
32   as you say: 
33   
34   2 This thought I do not want. 3 I choose instead ___ 
35   
36   4 And then repeat the idea for the day, and let it take the place of what you thought. 
37   5 Beyond such special applications of each day's idea, we will add but a few formal 
38   expressions or specific thoughts to aid in practicing. 6 Instead, we give these times of quiet to 
39   the Teacher Who instructs in quiet, speaks of peace, and gives our thoughts whatever 
40   meaning they may have.
41   W-pI.rVI.in.7. To Him I offer this review for you. 2 I place you in His charge, and let
42   Him teach you what to do and say and think, each time you turn to Him. 3 He will not 
43   fail to be available to you, each time you call to Him to help you. 4 Let us offer Him the 
44   whole review we now begin, and let us also not forget to Whom it has been given, as we 
45   practice day by day, advancing toward the goal He set for us; allowing Him to teach us how to 
46   go, and trusting Him completely for the way each practice period can best become a loving
47   gift of freedom to the world.
