34   
35   PART II
36   
37   
38    Introduction
39   
40   
41   W-pII.in.1. Words will mean little now. 2 We use them but as guides on which we do not 
42   now depend. 3 For now we seek direct experience of truth alone. 4 The lessons that remain 
43   are merely introductions to the times in which we leave the world of pain, and go to enter
44   peace. 5 Now we begin to reach the goal this course has set, and find the end toward 
45   which our practicing was always geared.
46   W-pII.in.2. Now we attempt to let the exercise be merely a beginning. 2 For we wait in 
47   quiet expectation for our God and Father. 3 He has promised He will take the final step 
48   Himself. 4 And we are sure His promises are kept. 5 We have come far along the road, and now 
49   we wait for Him. 6 We will continue spending time with Him each morning and at night, as 
50   long as makes us happy. 7 We will not consider time a matter of duration now. 8 We use as 
0616
 1   much as we will need for the result that we desire. 9 Nor will we forget our hourly 
 2   remembrance in between, calling to God when we have need of Him as we are tempted to forget our 
 3   goal.
 4   W-pII.in.3. We will continue with a central thought for all the days to come, and we 
 5   will use that thought to introduce our times of rest, and calm our minds at need. 2 Yet we 
 6   will not content ourselves with simple practicing in the remaining holy instants which 
 7   conclude the year that we have given God. 3 We say some simple words of welcome, and expect our
 8   Father to reveal Himself, as He has promised. 4 We have called on Him, and He has 
 9   promised that His Son will not remain unanswered when he calls His Name.
10   W-pII.in.4. Now do we come to Him with but His Word upon our minds and hearts, and wait
11   for Him to take the step to us that He has told us, through His Voice, He would not 
12   fail to take when we invited Him. 2 He has not left His Son in all his madness, nor 
13   betrayed his trust in Him. 3 Has not His faithfulness earned Him the invitation that He seeks 
14   to make us happy? 4 We will offer it, and it will be accepted. 5 So our times with Him 
15   will now be spent. 6 We say the words of invitation that His Voice suggests, and then we 
16   wait for Him to come to us.
17   W-pII.in.5. Now is the time of prophecy fulfilled. 2 Now are all ancient promises 
18   upheld and fully kept. 3 No step remains for time to separate from its accomplishment. 4 For 
19   now we cannot fail. 5 Sit silently and wait upon your Father. 6 He has willed to come to 
20   you when you have recognized it is your will He do so. 7 And you could have never come 
21   this far unless you saw, however dimly, that it is your will.
22   W-pII.in.6. I am so close to you we cannot fail. 2 Father, we give these holy times to 
23   You, in gratitude to Him Who taught us how to leave the world of sorrow in exchange for 
24   its replacement, given us by You. 3 We look not backward now. 4 We look ahead, and fix our
25   eyes upon the journey's end. 5 Accept these little gifts of thanks from us, as through 
26   Christ's vision we behold a world beyond the one we made, and take that world to be the full 
27   replacement of our own.
28   W-pII.in.7. And now we wait in silence, unafraid and certain of Your coming. 2 We have 
29   sought to find our way by following the Guide You sent to us. 3 We did not know the way, but 
30   You did not forget us. 4 And we know that You will not forget us now. 5 We ask but that 
31   Your ancient promises be kept which are Your Will to keep. 6 We will with You in asking 
32   this. 7 The Father and the Son, Whose holy Will created all that is, can fail in nothing. 8
33   In this certainty, we undertake these last few steps to You, and rest in confidence 
34   upon Your Love, which will not fail the Son who calls to You.
35   W-pII.in.8. And so we start upon the final part of this one holy year, which we have 
36   spent together in the search for truth and God, Who is its one Creator. 2 We have found the 
37   way He chose for us, and made the choice to follow it as He would have us go. 3 His Hand 
38   has held us up. 4 His Thoughts have lit the darkness of our minds. 5 His Love has called 
39   to us unceasingly since time began.
40   W-pII.in.9. We had a wish that God would fail to have the Son whom He created for 
41   Himself. 2 We wanted God to change Himself, and be what we would make of Him. 3 And we 
42   believed that our insane desires were the truth. 4 Now we are glad that this is all undone, and
43   we no longer think illusions true. 5 The memory of God is shimmering across the wide 
44   horizons of our minds. 6 A moment more, and it will rise again. 7 A moment more, and we who are
45   God's Sons are safely home, where He would have us be.
46   W-pII.in.10. Now is the need for practice almost done. 2 For in this final section, we 
47   will come to understand that we need only call to God, and all temptations disappear. 3 
48   Instead of words, we need but feel His Love. 4 Instead of prayers, we need but call His Name. 
49   5 Instead of judging, we need but be still and let all things be healed. 6 We will 
50   accept the way God's plan will end, as we received the way it started. 7 Now it is complete. 
0617
 1   8 This year has brought us to eternity.
 2   W-pII.in.11. One further use for words we still retain. 2 From time to time, 
 3   instructions on a theme of special relevance will intersperse our daily lessons and the periods of 
 4   wordless, deep experience which should come afterwards. 3 These special thoughts should be 
 5   reviewed each day, each one of them to be continued till the next is given you. 4 They should 
 6   be slowly read and thought about a little while, preceding one of the holy and blessed 
 7   instants in the day. 5 We give the first of these instructions now.
 8   
 9   
10   1. What Is Forgiveness?
11   W-pII.1.1. Forgiveness recognizes what you thought your brother did to you has not 
12   occurred. 2 It does not pardon sins and make them real. 3 It sees there was no sin. 4 And in 
13   that view are all your sins forgiven. 5 What is sin, except a false idea about God's Son? 6
14   Forgiveness merely sees its falsity, and therefore lets it go. 7 What then is free to 
15   take its place is now the Will of God.
16   W-pII.1.2. An unforgiving thought is one which makes a judgment that it will not raise 
17   to doubt, although it is not true. 2 The mind is closed, and will not be released. 3 The 
18   thought protects projection, tightening its chains, so that distortions are more veiled and 
19   more obscure; less easily accessible to doubt, and further kept from reason. 4 What can 
20   come between a fixed projection and the aim that it has chosen as its wanted goal?
21   W-pII.1.3. An unforgiving thought does many things. 2 In frantic action it pursues its 
22   goal, twisting and overturning what it sees as interfering with its chosen path. 3 
23   Distortion is its purpose, and the means by which it would accomplish it as well. 4 It sets about
24   its furious attempts to smash reality, without concern for anything that would appear 
25   to pose a contradiction to its point of view.
26   W-pII.1.4. Forgiveness, on the other hand, is still, and quietly does nothing. 2 It 
27   offends no aspect of reality, nor seeks to twist it to appearances it likes. 3 It merely looks,
28    and waits, and judges not. 4 He who would not forgive must judge, for he must justify 
29   his failure to forgive. 5 But he who would forgive himself must learn to welcome truth 
30   exactly as it is.
31   W-pII.1.5. Do nothing, then, and let forgiveness show you what to do, through Him Who 
32   is your Guide, your Savior and Protector, strong in hope, and certain of your ultimate 
33   success. 2 He has forgiven you already, for such is His function, given Him by God. 3 Now must
34   you share His function, and forgive whom He has saved, whose sinlessness He sees, and 
35   whom He honors as the Son of God.
36   
37   
38   
39   LESSON 221.
40   
41   Peace to my mind. Let all my thoughts be still.
42   W-pII.221.1.  <Father, I come to You today to seek the peace that You alone can give. 2
43   I come in silence. 3 In the quiet of my heart, the deep recesses of my mind, I wait and
44   listen for Your Voice. 4 My Father, speak to me today. 5 I come to hear Your Voice in 
45   silence and in certainty and love, sure You will hear my call and answer me.>
46   
47   W-pII.221.2. Now do we wait in quiet. 2 God is here, because we wait together. 3 I am 
48   sure that He will speak to you, and you will hear. 4 Accept my confidence, for it is yours.
49   5 Our minds are joined. 6 We wait with one intent; to hear our Father's answer to our 
50   call, to let our thoughts be still and find His peace, to hear Him speak to us of what we 
0618
 1   are, and to reveal Himself unto His Son.
 2   
 3   
 4   
 5   LESSON 222.
 6   
 7   God is with me. I live and move in Him.
 8   W-pII.222.1. God is with me. 2 He is my Source of life, the life within, the air I 
 9   breathe, the food by which I am sustained, the water which renews and cleanses me. 3 He is my 
10   home, wherein I live and move; the Spirit which directs my actions, offers me Its Thoughts,
11   and guarantees my safety from all pain. 4 He covers me with kindness and with care, and
12   holds in love the Son He shines upon, who also shines on Him. 5 How still is he who 
13   knows the truth of what He speaks today!
14   
15   W-pII.222.2.  <Father, we have no words except Your Name upon our lips and in our minds,
16    as we come quietly into Your Presence now, and ask to rest with You in peace a while.>
17   
18   
19   
20   LESSON 223.
21   
22   God is my life. I have no life but His.
23   W-pII.223.1. I was mistaken when I thought I lived apart from God, a separate entity 
24   that moved in isolation, unattached, and housed within a body. 2 Now I know my life is 
25   God's, I have no other home, and I do not exist apart from Him. 3 He has no Thoughts that 
26   are not part of me, and I have none but those which are of Him.
27   
28   W-pII.223.2.  <Our Father, let us see the face of Christ instead of our mistakes. 2 For
29   we who are Your holy Son are sinless. 3 We would look upon our sinlessness, for guilt 
30   proclaims that we are not Your Son. 4 And we would not forget You longer. 5 We are lonely here, 
31   and long for Heaven, where we are at home. 6 Today we would return. 7 Our Name is Yours, 
32   and we acknowledge that we are Your Son.>
33   
34   
35   
36   LESSON 224.
37   
38   God is my Father, and He loves His Son.
39   W-pII.224.1. My true Identity is so secure, so lofty, sinless, glorious and great, 
40   wholly beneficent and free from guilt, that Heaven looks to It to give it light. 2 It lights 
41   the world as well. 3 It is the gift my Father gave to me; the one as well I give the world.
42    4 There is no gift but this that can be either given or received. 5 This is reality, 
43   and only this. 6 This is illusion's end. 7 It is the truth.
44   
45   W-pII.224.2.  <My Name, O Father, still is known to You. 2 I have forgotten It, and do 
46   not know where I am going, who I am, or what it is I do. 3 Remind me, Father, now, for I 
47   am weary of the world I see. 4 Reveal what You would have me see instead.>
48   
49   
50   
0619
 1   LESSON 225.
 2   
 3   God is my Father, and His Son loves Him.
 4   W-pII.225.1.  <Father, I must return Your Love for me, for giving and receiving are the
 5   same, and You have given all Your Love to me. 2 I must return it, for I want it mine in
 6   full awareness, blazing in my mind and keeping it within its kindly light, inviolate, 
 7   beloved, with fear behind and only peace ahead. 3 How still the way Your loving Son is led 
 8   along to You!>
 9   
10   W-pII.225.2. Brother, we find that stillness now. 2 The way is open. 3 Now we follow it
11   in peace together. 4 You have reached your hand to me, and I will never leave you. 5 We
12   are one, and it is but this oneness that we seek, as we accomplish these few final 
13   steps which end a journey that was not begun.
14   
15   
16   
17   LESSON 226.
18   
19   My home awaits me. I will hasten there.
20   W-pII.226.1. If I so choose, I can depart this world entirely. 2 It is not death which 
21   makes this possible, but it is change of mind about the purpose of the world. 3 If I believe
22   it has a value as I see it now, so will it still remain for me. 4 But if I see no value
23   in the world as I behold it, nothing that I want to keep as mine or search for as a 
24   goal, it will depart from me. 5 For I have not sought for illusions to replace the truth.
25   
26   W-pII.226.2.  <Father, my home awaits my glad return. 2 Your Arms are open and I hear 
27   Your Voice. 3 What need have I to linger in a place of vain desires and of shattered dreams,
28    when Heaven can so easily be mine?>
29   
30   
31   
32   LESSON 227.
33   
34   This is my holy instant of release.
35   W-pII.227.1.  <Father, it is today that I am free, because my will is Yours. 2 I 
36   thought to make another will. 3 Yet nothing that I thought apart from You exists. 4 And I am 
37   free because I was mistaken, and did not affect my own reality at all by my illusions. 5 
38   Now I give them up, and lay them down before the feet of truth, to be removed forever from
39   my mind. 6 This is my holy instant of release. 7 Father, I know my will is one with 
40   Yours.>
41   
42   W-pII.227.2. And so today we find our glad return to Heaven, which we never really left.
43    2 The Son of God this day lays down his dreams. 3 The Son of God this day comes home 
44   again, released from sin and clad in holiness, with his right mind restored to him at last.
45   
