48   LESSON 228.
49   
50   God has condemned me not. No more do I.
0620
 1   W-pII.228.1. My Father knows my holiness. 2 Shall I deny His knowledge, and believe in 
 2   what His knowledge makes impossible? 3 Shall I accept as true what He proclaims as false? 4
 3   Or shall I take His Word for what I am, since He is my Creator, and the One Who knows 
 4   the true condition of His Son?
 5   
 6   W-pII.228.2.  <Father, I was mistaken in myself, because I failed to realize the Source
 7   from which I came. 2 I have not left that Source to enter in a body and to die. 3 My 
 8   holiness remains a part of me, as I am part of You. 4 And my mistakes about myself are dreams. 
 9   5 I let them go today. 6 And I stand ready to receive Your Word alone for what I really 
10   am.>
11   
12   
13   
14   LESSON 229.
15   
16   Love, which created me, is what I am.
17   W-pII.229.1. I seek my own Identity, and find It in these words: "Love, which created 
18   me, is what I am." 2 Now need I seek no more. 3 Love has prevailed. 4 So still It waited 
19   for my coming home, that I will turn away no longer from the holy face of Christ. 5 And 
20   what I look upon attests the truth of the Identity I sought to lose, but which my Father 
21   has kept safe for me.
22   
23   W-pII.229.2.  <Father, my thanks to You for what I am; for keeping my Identity 
24   untouched and sinless, in the midst of all the thoughts of sin my foolish mind made up. 2 And 
25   thanks to You for saving me from them. 3 Amen.>
26   
27   
28   
29   LESSON 230.
30   
31   Now will I seek and find the peace of God.
32   W-pII.230.1. In peace I was created. 2 And in peace do I remain. 3 It is not given me 
33   to change my Self. 4 How merciful is God my Father, that when He created me He gave me 
34   peace forever. 5 Now I ask but to be what I am. 6 And can this be denied me, when it is 
35   forever true?
36   
37   W-pII.230.2.  <Father, I seek the peace You gave as mine in my creation. 2 What was 
38   given then must be here now, for my creation was apart from time, and still remains beyond 
39   all change. 3 The peace in which Your Son was born into Your Mind is shining there 
40   unchanged. 4 I am as You created me. 5 I need but call on You to find the peace You gave. 6 It 
41   is Your Will that gave it to Your Son.>
42   
43   
44   2. What Is Salvation?
45   W-pII.2.1. Salvation is a promise, made by God, that you would find your way to Him at 
46   last. 2 It cannot but be kept. 3 It guarantees that time will have an end, and all the 
47   thoughts that have been born in time will end as well. 4 God's Word is given every mind which 
48   thinks that it has separate thoughts, and will replace these thoughts of conflict with the 
49   Thought of peace.
50   W-pII.2.2. The Thought of peace was given to God's Son the instant that his mind had 
0621
 1   thought of war. 2 There was no need for such a Thought before, for peace was given without 
 2   opposite, and merely was. 3 But when the mind is split there is a need of healing. 4 So the 
 3   Thought that has the power to heal the split became a part of every fragment of the mind that 
 4   still was one, but failed to recognize its oneness. 5 Now it did not know itself, and 
 5   thought its own Identity was lost.
 6   W-pII.2.3. Salvation is undoing in the sense that it does nothing, failing to support 
 7   the world of dreams and malice. 2 Thus it lets illusions go. 3 By not supporting them, it 
 8   merely lets them quietly go down to dust. 4 And what they hid is now revealed; an altar to 
 9   the holy Name of God whereon His Word is written, with the gifts of your forgiveness laid 
10   before it, and the memory of God not far behind.
11   W-pII.2.4. Let us come daily to this holy place, and spend a while together. 2 Here we 
12   share our final dream. 3 It is a dream in which there is no sorrow, for it holds a hint of 
13   all the glory given us by God. 4 The grass is pushing through the soil, the trees are 
14   budding now, and birds have come to live within their branches. 5 Earth is being born again in
15   new perspective. 6 Night has gone, and we have come together in the light.
16   W-pII.2.5. From here we give salvation to the world, for it is here salvation was 
17   received. 2 The song of our rejoicing is the call to all the world that freedom is returned, 
18   that time is almost over, and God's Son has but an instant more to wait until his Father is
19   remembered, dreams are done, eternity has shined away the world, and only Heaven now 
20   exists at all.
21   
22   
23   
24   LESSON 231.
25   
26   Father, I will but to remember You.
27   W-pII.231.1.  <What can I seek for, Father, but Your Love? 2 Perhaps I think I seek for
28   something else; a something I have called by many names. 3 Yet is Your Love the only 
29   thing I seek, or ever sought. 4 For there is nothing else that I could ever really want to 
30   find. 5 Let me remember You. 6 What else could I desire but the truth about myself?>
31   
32   W-pII.231.2. This is your will, my brother. 2 And you share this will with me, and with
33   the One as well Who is our Father. 3 To remember Him is Heaven. 4 This we seek. 5 And 
34   only this is what it will be given us to find.
35   
36   
37   
38   LESSON 232.
39   
40   Be in my mind, my Father, through the day.
41   W-pII.232.1.  <Be in my mind, my Father, when I wake, and shine on me throughout the 
42   day today. 2 Let every minute be a time in which I dwell with You. 3 And let me not forget
43   my hourly thanksgiving that You have remained with me, and always will be there to hear
44   my call to You and answer me. 4 As evening comes, let all my thoughts be still of You 
45   and of Your Love. 5 And let me sleep sure of my safety, certain of Your care, and happily 
46   aware I am Your Son.>
47   
48   W-pII.232.2. This is as every day should be. 2 Today, practice the end of fear. 3 Have 
49   faith in Him Who is your Father. 4 Trust all things to Him. 5 Let Him reveal all things to 
50   you, and be you undismayed because you are His Son.
0622
 1   
 2   
