 4   LESSON 233.
 5   
 6   I give my life to God to guide today.
 7   W-pII.233.1.  <Father, I give You all my thoughts today. 2 I would have none of mine. 3
 8   In place of them, give me Your Own. 4 I give You all my acts as well, that I may do 
 9   Your Will instead of seeking goals which cannot be obtained, and wasting time in vain 
10   imaginings. 5 Today I come to You. 6 I will step back and merely follow You. 7 Be You the Guide, 
11   and I the follower who questions not the wisdom of the Infinite, nor Love whose tenderness
12   I cannot comprehend, but which is yet Your perfect gift to me.>
13   
14   W-pII.233.2. Today we have one Guide to lead us on. 2 And as we walk together, we will 
15   give this day to Him with no reserve at all. 3 This is His day. 4 And so it is a day of 
16   countless gifts and mercies unto us.
17   
18   
