20   LESSON 234.
21   
22   Father, today I am Your Son again.
23   W-pII.234.1. Today we will anticipate the time when dreams of sin and guilt are gone, 
24   and we have reached the holy peace we never left. 2 Merely a tiny instant has elapsed 
25   between eternity and timelessness. 3 So brief the interval there was no lapse in continuity, 
26   nor break in thoughts which are forever unified as one. 4 Nothing has ever happened to 
27   disturb the peace of God the Father and the Son. 5 This we accept as wholly true today.
28   
29   W-pII.234.2.  <We thank You, Father, that we cannot lose the memory of You and of Your 
30   Love. 2 We recognize our safety, and give thanks for all the gifts You have bestowed on us,
31   for all the loving help we have received, for Your eternal patience, and the Word which
32   You have given us that we are saved.>
33   
34   
35   
36   LESSON 235.
37   
38   God in His mercy wills that I be saved.
39   W-pII.235.1. I need but look upon all things that seem to hurt me, and with perfect 
40   certainty assure myself, "God wills that I be saved from this," and merely watch them disappear.
41   2 I need but keep in mind my Father's Will for me is only happiness, to find that only 
42   happiness has come to me. 3 And I need but remember that God's Love surrounds His Son and keeps 
43   his sinlessness forever perfect, to be sure that I am saved and safe forever in His Arms. 
44   4 I am the Son He loves. 5 And I am saved because God in His mercy wills it so.
45   
46   W-pII.235.2.  <Father, Your Holiness is mine. 2 Your Love created me, and made my 
47   sinlessness forever part of You. 3 I have no guilt nor sin in me, for there is none in You.>
