0623
 1   LESSON 236.
 2   
 3   I rule my mind, which I alone must rule.
 4   W-pII.236.1. I have a kingdom I must rule. 2 At times, it does not seem I am its king 
 5   at all. 3 It seems to triumph over me, and tell me what to think, and what to do and feel.
 6    4 And yet it has been given me to serve whatever purpose I perceive in it. 5 My mind 
 7   can only serve. 6 Today I give its service to the Holy Spirit to employ as He sees fit. 7 
 8   I thus direct my mind, which I alone can rule. 8 And thus I set it free to do the Will 
 9   of God.
10   
