12   LESSON 240.
13   
14   Fear is not justified in any form.
15   W-pII.240.1. Fear is deception. 2 It attests that you have seen yourself as you could 
16   never be, and therefore look upon a world which is impossible. 3 Not one thing in this world
17   is true. 4 It does not matter what the form in which it may appear. 5 It witnesses but 
18   to your own illusions of yourself. 6 Let us not be deceived today. 7 We are the Sons of 
19   God. 8 There is no fear in us, for we are each a part of Love Itself.
20   
21   W-pII.240.2.  <How foolish are our fears! 2 Would You allow Your Son to suffer? 3 Give 
22   us faith today to recognize Your Son, and set him free. 4 Let us forgive him in Your Name,
23    that we may understand his holiness, and feel the love for him which is Your Own as 
24   well.>
25   
26   
27   3. What Is the World?
28   W-pII.3.1. The world is false perception. 2 It is born of error, and it has not left 
29   its source. 3 It will remain no longer than the thought that gave it birth is cherished. 4
30   When the thought of separation has been changed to one of true forgiveness, will the 
31   world be seen in quite another light; and one which leads to truth, where all the world must
32   disappear and all its errors vanish. 5 Now its source has gone, and its effects are 
33   gone as well.
34   W-pII.3.2. The world was made as an attack on God. 2 It symbolizes fear. 3 And what is 
35   fear except love's absence? 4 Thus the world was meant to be a place where God could enter 
36   not, and where His Son could be apart from Him. 5 Here was perception born, for knowledge 
37   could not cause such insane thoughts. 6 But eyes deceive, and ears hear falsely. 7 Now 
38   mistakes become quite possible, for certainty has gone.
39   W-pII.3.3. The mechanisms of illusion have been born instead. 2 And now they go to find
40   what has been given them to seek. 3 Their aim is to fulfill the purpose which the world
41   was made to witness and make real. 4 They see in its illusions but a solid base where 
42   truth exists, upheld apart from lies. 5 Yet everything that they report is but illusion 
43   which is kept apart from truth.
44   W-pII.3.4. As sight was made to lead away from truth, it can be redirected. 2 Sounds 
45   become the call for God, and all perception can be given a new purpose by the One Whom God 
46   appointed Savior to the world. 3 Follow His light, and see the world as He beholds it. 4 Hear 
47   His Voice alone in all that speaks to you. 5 And let Him give you peace and certainty, 
48   which you have thrown away, but Heaven has preserved for you in Him.
49   W-pII.3.5. Let us not rest content until the world has joined our changed perception. 2
50   Let us not be satisfied until forgiveness has been made complete. 3 And let us not 
0625
 1   attempt to change our function. 4 We must save the world. 5 For we who made it must behold it 
 2   through the eyes of Christ, that what was made to die can be restored to everlasting life.
 3   
 4   
 5   
