0629
 1   
 2   The Son of God is my Identity.
 3   W-pII.252.1. My Self is holy beyond all the thoughts of holiness of which I now 
 4   conceive. 2 Its shimmering and perfect purity is far more brilliant than is any light that I 
 5   have ever looked upon. 3 Its love is limitless, with an intensity that holds all things 
 6   within it, in the calm of quiet certainty. 4 Its strength comes not from burning impulses 
 7   which move the world, but from the boundless Love of God Himself. 5 How far beyond this 
 8   world my Self must be, and yet how near to me and close to God!
 9   
10   W-pII.252.2.  <Father, You know my true Identity. 2 Reveal It now to me who am Your Son,
11    that I may waken to the truth in You, and know that Heaven is restored to me.>
