15   LESSON 253.
16   
17   My Self is ruler of the universe.
18   W-pII.253.1. It is impossible that anything should come to me unbidden by myself. 2 
19   Even in this world, it is I who rule my destiny. 3 What happens is what I desire. 4 What 
20   does not occur is what I do not want to happen. 5 This must I accept. 6 For thus am I led 
21   past this world to my creations, children of my will, in Heaven where my holy Self abides 
22   with them and Him Who has created me.
23   
24   W-pII.253.2.  <You are the Self Whom You created Son, creating like Yourself and One 
25   with You. 2 My Self, which rules the universe, is but Your Will in perfect union with my 
26   own, which can but offer glad assent to Yours, that it may be extended to Itself.>
