32   Let every voice but God's be still in me.
33   W-pII.254.1.  <Father, today I would but hear Your Voice. 2 In deepest silence I would 
34   come to You, to hear Your Voice and to receive Your Word. 3 I have no prayer but this: I 
35   come to You to ask You for the truth. 4 And truth is but Your Will, which I would share 
36   with You today.>
37   
38   W-pII.254.2. Today we let no ego thoughts direct our words or actions. 2 When such 
39   thoughts occur, we quietly step back and look at them, and then we let them go. 3 We do not 
40   want what they would bring with them. 4 And so we do not choose to keep them. 5 They are 
41   silent now. 6 And in the stillness, hallowed by His Love, God speaks to us and tells us of 
