17   where you are? 4 Who would still be uncertain? 5 Who could be unsure of who he is? 6 
18   And who would yet remain asleep, in heavy clouds of doubt about the holiness of him whom 
19   God created sinless? 7 Here we can but dream. 8 But we can dream we have forgiven him in 
20   whom all sin remains impossible, and it is this we choose to dream today. 9 God is our goal;
21    forgiveness is the means by which our minds return to Him at last.
