30   
31   Let me remember what my purpose is.
32   W-pII.257.1. If I forget my goal I can be but confused, unsure of what I am, and thus 
33   conflicted in my actions. 2 No one can serve contradicting goals and serve them well. 3 Nor can 
34   he function without deep distress and great depression. 4 Let us therefore be determined 
35   to remember what we want today, that we may unify our thoughts and actions meaningfully, 
36   and achieve only what God would have us do this day.
37   
38   W-pII.257.2.  <Father, forgiveness is Your chosen means for our salvation. 2 Let us not
39   forget today that we can have no will but Yours. 3 And thus our purpose must be Yours 
40   as well, if we would reach the peace You will for us.>
