47   W-pII.258.1. All that is needful is to train our minds to overlook all little senseless
48   aims, and to remember that our goal is God. 2 His memory is hidden in our minds, 
49   obscured but by our pointless little goals which offer nothing, and do not exist. 3 Shall we 
50   continue to allow God's grace to shine in unawareness, while the toys and trinkets of the world
0631
 1   are sought instead? 4 God is our only goal, our only Love. 5 We have no aim but to 
 2   remember Him.
 3   
 4   W-pII.258.2.  <Our goal is but to follow in the way that leads to You. 2 We have no 
 5   goal but this. 3 What could we want but to remember You? 4 What could we seek but our 
