10   LESSON 259.
11   
12   Let me remember that there is no sin.
13   W-pII.259.1. Sin is the only thought that makes the goal of God seem unattainable. 2 
14   What else could blind us to the obvious, and make the strange and the distorted seem more 
15   clear? 3 What else but sin engenders our attacks? 4 What else but sin could be the source of
16   guilt, demanding punishment and suffering? 5 And what but sin could be the source of 
17   fear, obscuring God's creation; giving love the attributes of fear and of attack?
18   
19   W-pII.259.2.  <Father, I would not be insane today. 2 I would not be afraid of love, 
20   nor seek for refuge in its opposite. 3 For love can have no opposite. 4 You are the Source
21   of everything there is. 5 And everything that is remains with You, and You with it.>
