25   LESSON 260.
26   
27   Let me remember God created me.
28   W-pII.260.1.  <Father, I did not make myself, although in my insanity I thought I did. 
29   2 Yet, as Your Thought, I have not left my Source, remaining part of Who created me. 3 
30   Your Son, my Father, calls on You today. 4 Let me remember You created me. 5 Let me 
31   remember my Identity. 6 And let my sinlessness arise again before Christ's vision, through 
32   which I would look upon my brothers and myself today.>
33   
34   W-pII.260.2. Now is our Source remembered, and Therein we find our true Identity at 
35   last. 2 Holy indeed are we, because our Source can know no sin. 3 And we who are His Sons 
36   are like each other, and alike to Him.
37   
38   
39   5. What Is the Body?
40   W-pII.5.1. The body is a fence the Son of God imagines he has built, to separate parts 
41   of his Self from other parts. 2 It is within this fence he thinks he lives, to die as it 
42   decays and crumbles. 3 For within this fence he thinks that he is safe from love. 4 
43   Identifying with his safety, he regards himself as what his safety is. 5 How else could he be 
44   certain he remains within the body, keeping love outside?
45   W-pII.5.2. The body will not stay. 2 Yet this he sees as double safety. 3 For the Son 
46   of God's impermanence is "proof" his fences work, and do the task his mind assigns to 
47   them. 4 For if his oneness still remained untouched, who could attack and who could be 
48   attacked? 5 Who could be victor? 6 Who could be his prey? 7 Who could be victim? 8 Who the 
49   murderer? 9 And if he did not die, what "proof" is there that God's eternal Son can be 
50   destroyed?
0632
 1   W-pII.5.3. The body is a dream. 2 Like other dreams it sometimes seems to picture 
 2   happiness, but can quite suddenly revert to fear, where every dream is born. 3 For only love 
 3   creates in truth, and truth can never fear. 4 Made to be fearful, must the body serve the 
 4   purpose given it. 5 But we can change the purpose that the body will obey by changing what we 
 5   think that it is for.
 6   W-pII.5.4. The body is the means by which God's Son returns to sanity. 2 Though it was 
 7   made to fence him into hell without escape, yet has the goal of Heaven been exchanged for 
 8   the pursuit of hell. 3 The Son of God extends his hand to reach his brother, and to help 
 9   him walk along the road with him. 4 Now is the body holy. 5 Now it serves to heal the mind
10   that it was made to kill.
11   W-pII.5.5. You will identify with what you think will make you safe. 2 Whatever it may 
12   be, you will believe that it is one with you. 3 Your safety lies in truth, and not in 
13   lies. 4 Love is your safety. 5 Fear does not exist. 6 Identify with love, and you are safe.
14   7 Identify with love, and you are home. 8 Identify with love, and find your Self.
