20   God is my refuge and security.
21   W-pII.261.1. I will identify with what I think is refuge and security. 2 I will behold 
22   myself where I perceive my strength, and think I live within the citadel where I am safe and 
23   cannot be attacked. 3 Let me today seek not security in danger, nor attempt to find my peace 
24   in murderous attack. 4 I live in God. 5 In Him I find my refuge and my strength. 6 In Him
25   is my Identity. 7 In Him is everlasting peace. 8 And only there will I remember Who I 
26   really am.
