37   He is Your one creation. 4 Why should I perceive a thousand forms in what remains as 
38   one? 5 Why should I give this one a thousand names, when only one suffices? 6 For Your Son
39   must bear Your Name, for You created him. 7 Let me not see him as a stranger to his 
40   Father, nor as stranger to myself. 8 For he is part of me and I of him, and we are part of 
