30   6. What Is the Christ?
31   W-pII.6.1. Christ is God's Son as He created Him. 2 He is the Self we share, uniting us
32   with one another, and with God as well. 3 He is the Thought which still abides within 
33   the Mind that is His Source. 4 He has not left His holy home, nor lost the innocence in 
34   which He was created. 5 He abides unchanged forever in the Mind of God.
35   W-pII.6.2. Christ is the link that keeps you one with God, and guarantees that 
36   separation is no more than an illusion of despair, for hope forever will abide in Him. 2 Your 
37   mind is part of His, and His of yours. 3 He is the part in which God's Answer lies; where 
38   all decisions are already made, and dreams are over. 4 He remains untouched by anything 
39   the body's eyes perceive. 5 For though in Him His Father placed the means for your 
40   salvation, yet does He remain the Self Who, like His Father, knows no sin.
41   W-pII.6.3. Home of the Holy Spirit, and at home in God alone, does Christ remain at 
42   peace within the Heaven of your holy mind. 2 This is the only part of you that has reality 
43   in truth. 3 The rest is dreams. 4 Yet will these dreams be given unto Christ, to fade 
44   before His glory and reveal your holy Self, the Christ, to you at last.
45   W-pII.6.4. The Holy Spirit reaches from the Christ in you to all your dreams, and bids 
46   them come to Him, to be translated into truth. 2 He will exchange them for the final dream 
47   which God appointed as the end of dreams. 3 For when forgiveness rests upon the world and 
48   peace has come to every Son of God, what could there be to keep things separate, for what 
49   remains to see except Christ's face?
50   W-pII.6.5. And how long will this holy face be seen, when it is but the symbol that the
0636
 1   time for learning now is over, and the goal of the Atonement has been reached at last? 
 2   2 So therefore let us seek to find Christ's face and look on nothing else. 3 As we 
 3   behold His glory, will we know we have no need of learning or perception or of time, or 
 4   anything except the holy Self, the Christ Whom God created as His Son.
