 5   
 6   Let me not bind Your Son with laws I made.
 7   W-pII.277.1.  <Your Son is free, my Father. 2 Let me not imagine I have bound him with 
 8   the laws I made to rule the body. 3 He is not subject to any laws I made by which I try to
 9   make the body more secure. 4 He is not changed by what is changeable. 5 He is not slave
10   to any laws of time. 6 He is as You created him, because he knows no law except the law
11   of love.>
