26   believe, when I maintain the laws the world obeys must I obey; the frailties and the sins 
27   which I perceive are real, and cannot be escaped. 3 If I am bound in any way, I do not know 
28   my Father nor my Self. 4 And I am lost to all reality. 5 For truth is free, and what is 
29   bound is not a part of truth.
