 3   LESSON 280.
 4   
 5   What limits can I lay upon God's Son?
 6   W-pII.280.1. Whom God created limitless is free. 2 I can invent imprisonment for him, 
 7   but only in illusions, not in truth. 3 No Thought of God has left its Father's Mind. 4 No 
 8   Thought of God is limited at all. 5 No Thought of God but is forever pure. 6 Can I lay limits 
 9   on the Son of God, whose Father willed that he be limitless, and like Himself in freedom 
10   and in love?
11   
12   W-pII.280.2.  <Today let me give honor to Your Son, for thus alone I find the way to 
13   You. 2 Father, I lay no limits on the Son You love and You created limitless. 3 The honor 
14   that I give to him is Yours, and what is Yours belongs to me as well.>
