16   
17   7. What Is the Holy Spirit?
18   W-pII.7.1. The Holy Spirit mediates between illusions and the truth. 2 Since He must 
19   bridge the gap between reality and dreams, perception leads to knowledge through the grace 
20   that God has given Him, to be His gift to everyone who turns to Him for truth. 3 Across the
21   bridge that He provides are dreams all carried to the truth, to be dispelled before the
22   light of knowledge. 4 There are sights and sounds forever laid aside. 5 And where they 
23   were perceived before, forgiveness has made possible perception's tranquil end.
24   W-pII.7.2. The goal the Holy Spirit's teaching sets is just this end of dreams. 2 For 
25   sights and sounds must be translated from the witnesses of fear to those of love. 3 And when 
26   this is entirely accomplished, learning has achieved the only goal it has in truth. 4 For 
27   learning, as the Holy Spirit guides it to the outcome He perceives for it, becomes the means to
28   go beyond itself, to be replaced by the eternal truth.
29   W-pII.7.3. If you but knew how much your Father yearns to have you recognize your 
30   sinlessness, you would not let His Voice appeal in vain, nor turn away from His replacement for 
31   the fearful images and dreams you made. 2 The Holy Spirit understands the means you made, 
32   by which you would attain what is forever unattainable. 3 And if you offer them to Him, 
33   He will employ the means you made for exile to restore your mind to where it truly is at 
34   home.
35   W-pII.7.4. From knowledge, where He has been placed by God, the Holy Spirit calls to 
36   you, to let forgiveness rest upon your dreams, and be restored to sanity and peace of mind.
37    2 Without forgiveness will your dreams remain to terrify you. 3 And the memory of all 
38   your Father's Love will not return to signify the end of dreams has come.
39   W-pII.7.5. Accept your Father's gift. 2 It is a Call from Love to Love, that It be but 
40   Itself. 3 The Holy Spirit is His gift, by which the quietness of Heaven is restored to God's 
41   beloved Son. 4 Would you refuse to take the function of completing God, when all He wills is 
42   that you be complete?
43   
44   
45   
46   LESSON 281.
47   
48   I can be hurt by nothing but my thoughts.
49   W-pII.281.1.  <Father, Your Son is perfect. 2 When I think that I am hurt in any way, 
50   it is because I have forgotten who I am, and that I am as You created me. 3 Your Thoughts
0640
 1   can only bring me happiness. 4 If ever I am sad or hurt or ill, I have forgotten what 
 2   You think, and put my little meaningless ideas in place of where Your Thoughts belong, and
 3   where they are. 5 I can be hurt by nothing but my thoughts. 6 The Thoughts I think with
 4   You can only bless. 7 The Thoughts I think with You alone are true.>
 5   
 6   W-pII.281.2. I will not hurt myself today. 2 For I am far beyond all pain. 3 My Father 
 7   placed me safe in Heaven, watching over me. 4 And I would not attack the Son He loves, for 
 8   what He loves is also mine to love.
