43   
44   I can elect to change all thoughts that hurt.
45   W-pII.284.1. Loss is not loss when properly perceived. 2 Pain is impossible. 3 There is
46   no grief with any cause at all. 4 And suffering of any kind is nothing but a dream. 5 
47   This is the truth, at first to be but said and then repeated many times; and next to be 
48   accepted as but partly true, with many reservations. 6 Then to be considered seriously more and
49   more, and finally accepted as the truth. 7 I can elect to change all thoughts that hurt.
50    8 And I would go beyond these words today, and past all reservations, and arrive at 
0641
 1   full acceptance of the truth in them.
