27   The hush of Heaven holds my heart today.
28   W-pII.286.1.  <Father, how still today! 2 How quietly do all things fall in place! 3 
29   This is the day that has been chosen as the time in which I come to understand the lesson 
30   that there is no need that I do anything. 4 In You is every choice already made. 5 In You 
31   has every conflict been resolved. 6 In You is everything I hope to find already given me. 
32   7 Your peace is mine. 8 My heart is quiet, and my mind at rest. 9 Your Love is Heaven, 
33   and Your Love is mine.>
34   
35   W-pII.286.2. The stillness of today will give us hope that we have found the way, and 
36   travelled far along it to a wholly certain goal. 2 Today we will not doubt the end which God 
37   Himself has promised us. 3 We trust in Him, and in our Self, Who still is One with Him.
