 7   LESSON 288.
 8   
 9   Let me forget my brother's past today.
10   W-pII.288.1.  <This is the thought that leads the way to You, and brings me to my goal.
11   2 I cannot come to You without my brother. 3 And to know my Source, I first must 
12   recognize what You created one with me. 4 My brother's is the hand that leads me on the way to 
13   You. 5 His sins are in the past along with mine, and I am saved because the past is gone. 
14   6 Let me not cherish it within my heart, or I will lose the way to walk to You. 7 My 
15   brother is my savior. 8 Let me not attack the savior You have given me. 9 But let me honor him
16   who bears Your Name, and so remember that It is my own.>
17   
