26   The past is over. It can touch me not.
27   W-pII.289.1. Unless the past is over in my mind, the real world must escape my sight. 2
28   For I am really looking nowhere; seeing but what is not there. 3 How can I then 
29   perceive the world forgiveness offers? 4 This the past was made to hide, for this the world 
30   that can be looked on only now. 5 It has no past. 6 For what can be forgiven but the past, 
31   and if it is forgiven it is gone.
32   
33   W-pII.289.2.  <Father, let me not look upon a past that is not there. 2 For You have 
34   offered me Your Own replacement, in a present world the past has left untouched and free of 
35   sin. 3 Here is the end of guilt. 4 And here am I made ready for Your final step. 5 Shall I
36   demand that You wait longer for Your Son to find the loveliness You planned to be the 
37   end of all his dreams and all his pain?>
