43   My present happiness is all I see.
44   W-pII.290.1. Unless I look upon what is not there, my present happiness is all I see. 2
45   Eyes that begin to open see at last. 3 And I would have Christ's vision come to me this
46   very day. 4 What I perceive without God's Own Correction for the sight I made is 
47   frightening and painful to behold. 5 Yet I would not allow my mind to be deceived by the belief 
48   the dream I made is real an instant longer. 6 This the day I seek my present happiness, 
49   and look on nothing else except the thing I seek.
