36   LESSON 294.
37   
38   My body is a wholly neutral thing.
39   W-pII.294.1. I am a Son of God. 2 And can I be another thing as well? 3 Did God create 
40   the mortal and corruptible? 4 What use has God's beloved Son for what must die? 5 And yet 
41   a neutral thing does not see death, for thoughts of fear are not invested there, nor is 
42   a mockery of love bestowed upon it. 6 Its neutrality protects it while it has a use. 7 
43   And afterwards, without a purpose, it is laid aside. 8 It is not sick nor old nor hurt. 9 
44   It is but functionless, unneeded and cast off. 10 Let me not see it more than this today;
45   of service for a while and fit to serve, to keep its usefulness while it can serve, and
46   then to be replaced for greater good.
47   
48   W-pII.294.2.  <My body, Father, cannot be Your Son. 2 And what is not created cannot be
49   sinful nor sinless; neither good nor bad. 3 Let me, then, use this dream to help Your 
50   plan that we awaken from all dreams we made.>
