34   Only an instant does this world endure.
35   W-pII.300.1. This is a thought which can be used to say that death and sorrow are the 
36   certain lot of all who come here, for their joys are gone before they are possessed, or even 
37   grasped. 2 Yet this is also the idea that lets no false perception keep us in its hold, nor 
38   represent more than a passing cloud upon a sky eternally serene. 3 And it is this serenity we 
39   seek, unclouded, obvious and sure, today.
