34   10. What Is the Last Judgment?
35   W-pII.10.1. Christ's Second Coming gives the Son of God this gift: to hear the Voice 
36   for God proclaim that what is false is false, and what is true has never changed. 2 And 
37   this the judgment is in which perception ends. 3 At first you see a world that has accepted
38   this as true, projected from a now corrected mind. 4 And with this holy sight, 
39   perception gives a silent blessing and then disappears, its goal accomplished and its mission 
40   done.
41   W-pII.10.2. The final judgment on the world contains no condemnation. 2 For it sees the
42   world as totally forgiven, without sin and wholly purposeless. 3 Without a cause, and 
43   now without a function in Christ's sight, it merely slips away to nothingness. 4 There it 
44   was born, and there it ends as well. 5 And all the figures in the dream in which the world
45   began go with it. 6 Bodies now are useless, and will therefore fade away, because the 
46   Son of God is limitless.
47   W-pII.10.3. You who believed that God's Last Judgment would condemn the world to hell 
48   along with you, accept this holy truth: God's Judgment is the gift of the Correction He 
49   bestowed on all your errors, freeing you from them, and all effects they ever seemed to have. 2
50   To fear God's saving grace is but to fear complete release from suffering, return to 
0651
 1   peace, security and happiness, and union with your own Identity.
 2   W-pII.10.4. God's Final Judgment is as merciful as every step in His appointed plan to 
 3   bless His Son, and call him to return to the eternal peace He shares with him. 2 Be not 
 4   afraid of love. 3 For it alone can heal all sorrow, wipe away all tears, and gently waken 
 5   from his dream of pain the Son whom God acknowledges as His. 4 Be not afraid of this. 5 
 6   Salvation asks you give it welcome. 6 And the world awaits your glad acceptance, which will set 
 7   it free.
 8   W-pII.10.5. This is God's Final Judgment: "You are still My holy Son, forever innocent,
 9   forever loving and forever loved, as limitless as your Creator, and completely 
10   changeless and forever pure. 2 Therefore awaken and return to Me. 3 I am your Father and you are 
11   My Son."
