14   
15   LESSON 311.
16   
17   I judge all things as I would have them be.
18   W-pII.311.1. Judgment was made to be a weapon used against the truth. 2 It separates 
19   what it is being used against, and sets it off as if it were a thing apart. 3 And then it 
20   makes of it what you would have it be. 4 It judges what it cannot understand, because it 
21   cannot see totality and therefore judges falsely. 5 Let us not use it today, but make a gift 
22   of it to Him Who has a different use for it. 6 He will relieve us of the agony of all the
23   judgments we have made against ourselves, and re-establish peace of mind by giving us 
24   God's Judgment of His Son.
25   
26   W-pII.311.2.  <Father, we wait with open mind today, to hear Your Judgment of the Son 
27   You love. 2 We do not know him, and we cannot judge. 3 And so we let Your Love decide what
28   he whom You created as Your Son must be.>
29   
30   
31   
32   LESSON 312.
33   
34   I see all things as I would have them be.
35   W-pII.312.1. Perception follows judgment. 2 Having judged, we therefore see what we 
36   would look upon. 3 For sight can merely serve to offer us what we would have. 4 It is 
37   impossible to overlook what we would see, and fail to see what we have chosen to behold. 5 How 
38   surely, therefore, must the real world come to greet the holy sight of anyone who takes the 
39   Holy Spirit's purpose as his goal for seeing. 6 And he cannot fail to look upon what Christ
40   would have him see, and share Christ's Love for what he looks upon.
41   
42   W-pII.312.2.  <I have no purpose for today except to look upon a liberated world, set 
43   free from all the judgments I have made. 2 Father, this is Your Will for me today, and 
44   therefore it must be my goal as well.>
45   
46   
47   
48   LESSON 313.
49   
50   Now let a new perception come to me.
0652
 1   W-pII.313.1.  <Father, there is a vision which beholds all things as sinless, so that 
 2   fear has gone, and where it was is love invited in. 2 And love will come wherever it is 
 3   asked. 3 This vision is Your gift. 4 The eyes of Christ look on a world forgiven. 5 In His 
 4   sight are all its sins forgiven, for He sees no sin in anything He looks upon. 6 Now let His
 5   true perception come to me, that I may waken from the dream of sin and look within upon
 6   my sinlessness, which You have kept completely undefiled upon the altar to Your holy 
 7   Son, the Self with which I would identify.>
 8   
 9   W-pII.313.2. Let us today behold each other in the sight of Christ. 2 How beautiful we 
10   are! 3 How holy and how loving! 4 Brother, come and join with me today. 5 We save the 
11   world when we have joined. 6 For in our vision it becomes as holy as the light in us.
