15   LESSON 314.
16   
17   I seek a future different from the past.
18   W-pII.314.1. From new perception of the world there comes a future very different from 
19   the past. 2 The future now is recognized as but extension of the present. 3 Past mistakes 
20   can cast no shadows on it, so that fear has lost its idols and its images, and being 
21   formless, it has no effects. 4 Death will not claim the future now, for life is now its goal, 
22   and all the needed means are happily provided. 5 Who can grieve or suffer when the present
23   has been freed, extending its security and peace into a quiet future filled with joy?
24   
25   W-pII.314.2.  <Father, we were mistaken in the past, and choose to use the present to 
26   be free. 2 Now do we leave the future in Your Hands, leaving behind our past mistakes, 
27   and sure that You will keep Your present promises, and guide the future in their holy 
28   light.>
