32   LESSON 315.
33   
34   All gifts my brothers give belong to me.
35   W-pII.315.1. Each day a thousand treasures come to me with every passing moment. 2 I am
36   blessed with gifts throughout the day, in value far beyond all things of which I can 
37   conceive. 3 A brother smiles upon another, and my heart is gladdened. 4 Someone speaks a word 
38   of gratitude or mercy, and my mind receives this gift and takes it as its own. 5 And 
39   everyone who finds the way to God becomes my savior, pointing out the way to me, and giving me 
40   his certainty that what he learned is surely mine as well.
41   
42   W-pII.315.2.  <I thank You, Father, for the many gifts that come to me today and every 
43   day from every Son of God. 2 My brothers are unlimited in all their gifts to me. 3 Now may
44   I offer them my thankfulness, that gratitude to them may lead me on to my Creator and 
45   His memory.>
