49   LESSON 316.
50   
0653
 1   All gifts I give my brothers are my own.
 2   W-pII.316.1. As every gift my brothers give is mine, so every gift I give belongs to me.
 3    2 Each one allows a past mistake to go, and leave no shadow on the holy mind my Father
 4   loves. 3 His grace is given me in every gift a brother has received throughout all time,
 5    and past all time as well. 4 My treasure house is full, and angels watch its open 
 6   doors that not one gift is lost, and only more are added. 5 Let me come to where my 
 7   treasures are, and enter in where I am truly welcome and at home, among the gifts that God has 
 8   given me.
 9   
10   W-pII.316.2.  <Father, I would accept Your gifts today. 2 I do not recognize them. 3 
11   Yet I trust that You Who gave them will provide the means by which I can behold them, see 
12   their worth, and cherish only them as what I want.>
