16   LESSON 317.
17   
18   I follow in the way appointed me.
19   W-pII.317.1. I have a special place to fill; a role for me alone. 2 Salvation waits 
20   until I take this part as what I choose to do. 3 Until I make this choice, I am the slave of
21   time and human destiny. 4 But when I willingly and gladly go the way my Father's plan 
22   appointed me to go, then will I recognize salvation is already here, already given all my 
23   brothers and already mine as well.
24   
25   W-pII.317.2.  <Father, Your way is what I choose today. 2 Where it would lead me do I 
26   choose to go; what it would have me do I choose to do. 3 Your way is certain, and the end 
27   secure. 4 The memory of You awaits me there. 5 And all my sorrows end in Your embrace, which 
28   You have promised to Your Son, who thought mistakenly that he had wandered from the sure 
29   protection of Your loving Arms.>
