33   LESSON 318.
34   
35   In me salvation's means and end are one.
36   W-pII.318.1. In me, God's holy Son, are reconciled all parts of Heaven's plan to save 
37   the world. 2 What could conflict, when all the parts have but one purpose and one aim? 3 
38   How could there be a single part that stands alone, or one of more or less importance than
39   the rest? 4 I am the means by which God's Son is saved, because salvation's purpose is 
40   to find the sinlessness that God has placed in me. 5 I was created as the thing I seek. 6
41   I am the goal the world is searching for. 7 I am God's Son, His one eternal Love. 8 I 
42   am salvation's means and end as well.
43   
44   W-pII.318.2.  <Let me today, my Father, take the role You offer me in Your request that
45   I accept Atonement for myself. 2 For thus does what is thereby reconciled in me become 
46   as surely reconciled to You.>
