50   LESSON 319.
0654
 1   
 2   I came for the salvation of the world.
 3   W-pII.319.1. Here is a thought from which all arrogance has been removed, and only 
 4   truth remains. 2 For arrogance opposes truth. 3 But when there is no arrogance the truth 
 5   will come immediately, and fill up the space the ego left unoccupied by lies. 4 Only the 
 6   ego can be limited, and therefore it must seek for aims which are curtailed and limiting. 
 7   5 The ego thinks that what one gains, totality must lose. 6 And yet it is the Will of 
 8   God I learn that what one gains is given unto all.
 9   
10   W-pII.319.2.  <Father, Your Will is total. 2 And the goal which stems from it shares 
11   its totality. 3 What aim but the salvation of the world could You have given me? 4 And 
12   what but this could be the Will my Self has shared with You?>
