16   LESSON 320.
17   
18   My Father gives all power unto me.
19   W-pII.320.1. The Son of God is limitless. 2 There are no limits on his strength, his 
20   peace, his joy, nor any attributes his Father gave in his creation. 3 What he wills with his
21   Creator and Redeemer must be done. 4 His holy will can never be denied, because his 
22   Father shines upon his mind, and lays before it all the strength and love in earth and Heaven.
23    5 I am he to whom all this is given. 6 I am he in whom the power of my Father's Will 
24   abides.
25   
26   W-pII.320.2.  <Your Will can do all things in me, and then extend to all the world as 
27   well through me. 2 There is no limit on Your Will. 3 And so all power has been given to 
28   Your Son.>
