31   11. What Is Creation?
32   W-pII.11.1. Creation is the sum of all God's Thoughts, in number infinite, and 
33   everywhere without all limit. 2 Only love creates, and only like itself. 3 There was no time when
34   all that it created was not there. 4 Nor will there be a time when anything that it 
35   created suffers any loss. 5 Forever and forever are God's Thoughts exactly as they were and as
36   they are, unchanged through time and after time is done.
37   W-pII.11.2. God's Thoughts are given all the power that their own Creator has. 2 For He
38   would add to love by its extension. 3 Thus His Son shares in creation, and must 
39   therefore share in power to create. 4 What God has willed to be forever One will still be One 
40   when time is over; and will not be changed throughout the course of time, remaining as it 
41   was before the thought of time began.
42   W-pII.11.3. Creation is the opposite of all illusions, for creation is the truth. 2 
43   Creation is the holy Son of God, for in creation is His Will complete in every aspect, making 
44   every part container of the whole. 3 Its oneness is forever guaranteed inviolate; forever 
45   held within His holy Will, beyond all possibility of harm, of separation, imperfection and 
46   of any spot upon its sinlessness.
47   W-pII.11.4. We are creation; we the Sons of God. 2 We seem to be discrete, and unaware 
48   of our eternal unity with Him. 3 Yet back of all our doubts, past all our fears, there 
49   still is certainty. 4 For love remains with all its Thoughts, its sureness being theirs. 5 
50   God's memory is in our holy minds, which know their oneness and their unity with their 
0655
 1   Creator. 6 Let our function be only to let this memory return, only to let God's Will be done 
 2   on earth, only to be restored to sanity, and to be but as God created us.
 3   W-pII.11.5. Our Father calls to us. 2 We hear His Voice, and we forgive creation in the
 4   Name of its Creator, Holiness Itself, Whose Holiness His Own creation shares; Whose 
 5   Holiness is still a part of us.
 6   
 7   
