 9   LESSON 321.
10   
11   Father, my freedom is in You alone.
12   W-pII.321.1.  <I did not understand what made me free, nor what my freedom is, nor 
13   where to look to find it. 2 Father, I have searched in vain until I heard Your Voice 
14   directing me. 3 Now I would guide myself no more. 4 For I have neither made nor understood the 
15   way to find my freedom. 5 But I trust in You. 6 You Who endowed me with my freedom as Your
16   holy Son will not be lost to me. 7 Your Voice directs me, and the way to You is opening
17   and clear to me at last. 8 Father, my freedom is in You alone. 9 Father, it is my will 
18   that I return.>
19   
20   W-pII.321.2. Today we answer for the world, which will be freed along with us. 2 How 
21   glad are we to find our freedom through the certain way our Father has established. 3 And 
22   how sure is all the world's salvation, when we learn our freedom can be found in God alone.
