27   LESSON 322.
28   
29   I can give up but what was never real.
30   W-pII.322.1. I sacrifice illusions; nothing more. 2 And as illusions go I find the 
31   gifts illusions tried to hide, awaiting me in shining welcome, and in readiness to give 
32   God's ancient messages to me. 3 His memory abides in every gift that I receive of Him. 4 And
33   every dream serves only to conceal the Self which is God's only Son, the likeness of 
34   Himself, the Holy One Who still abides in Him forever, as He still abides in me.
35   
36   W-pII.322.2.  <Father, to You all sacrifice remains forever inconceivable. 2 And so I 
37   cannot sacrifice except in dreams. 3 As You created me, I can give up nothing You gave me. 4 
38   What You did not give has no reality. 5 What loss can I anticipate except the loss of fear,
39   and the return of love into my mind?>
