 9   LESSON 324.
10   
11   I merely follow, for I would not lead.
12   W-pII.324.1.  <Father, You are the One Who gave the plan for my salvation to me. 2 You 
13   have set the way I am to go, the role to take, and every step in my appointed path. 3 I 
14   cannot lose the way. 4 I can but choose to wander off a while, and then return. 5 Your loving
15   Voice will always call me back, and guide my feet aright. 6 My brothers all can follow 
16   in the way I lead them. 7 Yet I merely follow in the way to You, as You direct me and 
17   would have me go.>
18   
19   W-pII.324.2. So let us follow One Who knows the way. 2 We need not tarry, and we cannot
20   stray except an instant from His loving Hand. 3 We walk together, for we follow Him. 4 
21   And it is He Who makes the ending sure, and guarantees a safe returning home.
