25   LESSON 325.
26   
27   All things I think I see reflect ideas.
28   W-pII.325.1. This is salvation's keynote: What I see reflects a process in my mind, 
29   which starts with my idea of what I want. 2 From there, the mind makes up an image of the 
30   thing the mind desires, judges valuable, and therefore seeks to find. 3 These images are 
31   then projected outward, looked upon, esteemed as real and guarded as one's own. 4 From 
32   insane wishes comes an insane world. 5 From judgment comes a world condemned. 6 And from 
33   forgiving thoughts a gentle world comes forth, with mercy for the holy Son of God, to offer him 
34   a kindly home where he can rest a while before he journeys on, and help his brothers 
35   walk ahead with him, and find the way to Heaven and to God.
36   
37   W-pII.325.2.  <Our Father, Your ideas reflect the truth, and mine apart from Yours but 
38   make up dreams. 2 Let me behold what only Yours reflect, for Yours and Yours alone 
39   establish truth.
40   
41   
42   
43   LESSON 326.
44   
45   I am forever an Effect of God.
46   W-pII.326.1.  <Father, I was created in Your Mind, a holy Thought that never left its 
47   home. 2 I am forever Your Effect, and You forever and forever are my Cause. 3 As You 
48   created me I have remained. 4 Where You established me I still abide. 5 And all Your 
49   attributes abide in me, because it is Your Will to have a Son so like his Cause that Cause and 
50   Its Effect are indistinguishable. 6 Let me know that I am an Effect of God, and so I have 
0657
 1   the power to create like You. 7 And as it is in Heaven, so on earth. 8 Your plan I follow 
 2   here, and at the end I know that You will gather Your effects into the tranquil Heaven of 
 3   Your Love, where earth will vanish, and all separate thoughts unite in glory as the Son of 
 4   God.>
 5   
 6   W-pII.326.2. Let us today behold earth disappear, at first transformed, and then, 
 7   forgiven, fade entirely into God's holy Will.
