11   LESSON 327.
12   
13   I need but call and You will answer me.
14   W-pII.327.1. I am not asked to take salvation on the basis of an unsupported faith. 2 
15   For God has promised He will hear my call, and answer me Himself. 3 Let me but learn from 
16   my experience that this is true, and faith in Him must surely come to me. 4 This is the 
17   faith that will endure, and take me farther and still farther on the road that leads to Him.
18   5 For thus I will be sure that He has not abandoned me and loves me still, awaiting but
19   my call to give me all the help I need to come to Him.
20   
21   W-pII.327.2.  <Father, I thank You that Your promises will never fail in my experience,
22   if I but test them out. 2 Let me attempt therefore to try them, and to judge them not. 
23   3 Your Word is one with You. 4 You give the means whereby conviction comes, and surety 
24   of Your abiding Love is gained at last.>
