28   LESSON 328.
29   
30   I choose the second place to gain the first.
31   W-pII.328.1. What seems to be the second place is first, for all things we perceive are
32   upside down until we listen to the Voice for God. 2 It seems that we will gain autonomy
33   but by our striving to be separate, and that our independence from the rest of God's 
34   creation is the way in which salvation is obtained. 3 Yet all we find is sickness, suffering 
35   and loss and death. 4 This is not what our Father wills for us, nor is there any second to
36   His Will. 5 To join with His is but to find our own. 6 And since our will is His, it is
37   to Him that we must go to recognize our will.
38   
39   W-pII.328.2.  <There is no will but Yours. 2 And I am glad that nothing I imagine 
40   contradicts what You would have me be. 3 It is Your Will that I be wholly safe, eternally at peace.
41    4 And happily I share that Will which You, my Father, gave as part of me.>
42   
