45   LESSON 329.
46   
47   I have already chosen what You will.
48   W-pII.329.1.  <Father, I thought I wandered from Your Will, defied it, broke its laws, 
49   and interposed a second will more powerful than Yours. 2 Yet what I am in truth is but 
50   Your Will, extended and extending. 3 This am I, and this will never change. 4 As You are 
0658
 1   One, so am I one with You. 5 And this I chose in my creation, where my will became forever
 2   one with Yours. 6 That choice was made for all eternity. 7 It cannot change, and be in 
 3   opposition to itself. 8 Father, my will is Yours. 9 And I am safe, untroubled and serene, in 
 4   endless joy, because it is Your Will that it be so.>
 5   
 6   W-pII.329.2. Today we will accept our union with each other and our Source. 2 We have 
 7   no will apart from His, and all of us are one because His Will is shared by all of us. 3 
 8   Through it we recognize that we are one. 4 Through it we find our way at last to God.
