12   LESSON 330.
13   
14   I will not hurt myself again today.
15   W-pII.330.1. Let us this day accept forgiveness as our only function. 2 Why should we 
16   attack our minds, and give them images of pain? 3 Why should we teach them they are powerless,
17    when God holds out His power and His Love, and bids them take what is already theirs? 
18   4 The mind that is made willing to accept God's gifts has been restored to spirit, and 
19   extends its freedom and its joy, as is the Will of God united with its own. 5 The Self which 
20   God created cannot sin, and therefore cannot suffer. 6 Let us choose today that He be our 
21   Identity, and thus escape forever from all things the dream of fear appears to offer us.
22   
23   W-pII.330.2.  <Father, Your Son can not be hurt. 2 And if we think we suffer, we but 
24   fail to know our one Identity we share with You. 3 We would return to It today, to be made 
25   free forever from all our mistakes, and to be saved from what we thought we were.>
26   
27   
28   12. What Is the Ego?
29   W-pII.12.1. The ego is idolatry; the sign of limited and separated self, born in a body,
30    doomed to suffer and to end its life in death. 2 It is the "will" that sees the Will 
31   of God as enemy, and takes a form in which it is denied. 3 The ego is the "proof" that 
32   strength is weak and love is fearful, life is really death, and what opposes God alone is true.
33   W-pII.12.2. The ego is insane. 2 In fear it stands beyond the Everywhere, apart from 
34   All, in separation from the Infinite. 3 In its insanity it thinks it has become a victor 
35   over God Himself. 4 And in its terrible autonomy it "sees" the Will of God has been 
36   destroyed. 5 It dreams of punishment, and trembles at the figures in its dreams; its enemies, 
37   who seek to murder it before it can ensure its safety by attacking them.
38   W-pII.12.3. The Son of God is egoless. 2 What can he know of madness and the death of 
39   God, when he abides in Him? 3 What can he know of sorrow and of suffering, when he lives 
40   in eternal joy? 4 What can he know of fear and punishment, of sin and guilt, of hatred 
41   and attack, when all there is surrounding him is everlasting peace, forever conflict-free 
42   and undisturbed, in deepest silence and tranquility?
43   W-pII.12.4. To know reality is not to see the ego and its thoughts, its works, its acts,
44    its laws and its beliefs, its dreams, its hopes, its plans for its salvation, and the 
45   cost belief in it entails. 2 In suffering, the price for faith in it is so immense that 
46   crucifixion of the Son of God is offered daily at its darkened shrine, and blood must flow before 
47   the altar where its sickly followers prepare to die.
48   W-pII.12.5. Yet will one lily of forgiveness change the darkness into light; the altar 
49   to illusions to the shrine of Life Itself. 2 And peace will be restored forever to the 
50   holy minds which God created as His Son, His dwelling place, His joy, His love, completely 
0659
 1   His, completely one with Him.
 2   
 3   
 4   
 5   LESSON 331.
 6   
 7   There is no conflict, for my will is Yours.
 8   W-pII.331.1.  <How foolish, Father, to believe Your Son could cause himself to suffer! 
 9   2 Could he make a plan for his damnation, and be left without a certain way to his 
10   release? 3 You love me, Father. 4 You could never leave me desolate, to die within a world of 
11   pain and cruelty. 5 How could I think that Love has left Itself? 6 There is no will except 
12   the Will of Love. 7 Fear is a dream, and has no will that can conflict with Yours. 8 
13   Conflict is sleep, and peace awakening. 9 Death is illusion; life, eternal truth. 10 There is 
14   no opposition to Your Will. 11 There is no conflict, for my will is Yours.>
15   
16   W-pII.331.2. Forgiveness shows us that God's Will is One, and that we share it. 2 Let 
17   us look upon the holy sights forgiveness shows today, that we may find the peace of God. 
18   3 Amen.
19   
20   
21   
22   LESSON 332.
23   
24   Fear binds the world. Forgiveness sets it free.
25   W-pII.332.1. The ego makes illusions. 2 Truth undoes its evil dreams by shining them 
26   away. 3 Truth never makes attack. 4 It merely is. 5 And by its presence is the mind 
27   recalled from fantasies, awaking to the real. 6 Forgiveness bids this presence enter in, and 
28   take its rightful place within the mind. 7 Without forgiveness is the mind in chains, 
29   believing in its own futility. 8 Yet with forgiveness does the light shine through the dream of 
30   darkness, offering it hope, and giving it the means to realize the freedom that is its 
31   inheritance.
32   
33   W-pII.332.2.  <We would not bind the world again today. 2 Fear holds it prisoner. 3 And
34   yet Your Love has given us the means to set it free. 4 Father, we would release it now.
35   5 For as we offer freedom, it is given us. 6 And we would not remain as prisoners, 
36   while You are holding freedom out to us.>
37   
38   
39   
40   LESSON 333.
41   
42   Forgiveness ends the dream of conflict here.
43   W-pII.333.1. Conflict must be resolved. 2 It cannot be evaded, set aside, denied, 
44   disguised, seen somewhere else, called by another name, or hidden by deceit of any kind, if it 
45   would be escaped. 3 It must be seen exactly as it is, where it is thought to be, in the 
46   reality which has been given it, and with the purpose that the mind accorded it. 4 For only 
47   then are its defenses lifted, and the truth can shine upon it as it disappears.
48   
49   W-pII.333.2.  <Father, forgiveness is the light You chose to shine away all conflict 
50   and all doubt, and light the way for our return to You. 2 No light but this can end our 
0660
 1   evil dream. 3 No light but this can save the world. 4 For this alone will never fail in 
 2   anything, being Your gift to Your beloved Son.>
 3   
 4   
 5   
 6   LESSON 334.
 7   
 8   Today I claim the gifts forgiveness gives.
 9   W-pII.334.1. I will not wait another day to find the treasures that my Father offers me.
10    2 Illusions are all vain, and dreams are gone even while they are woven out of 
11   thoughts that rest on false perceptions. 3 Let me not accept such meager gifts again today. 4 
12   God's Voice is offering the peace of God to all who hear and choose to follow Him. 5 This is
13   my choice today. 6 And so I go to find the treasures God has given me.
14   
15   W-pII.334.2.  <I seek but the eternal. 2 For Your Son can be content with nothing less 
16   than this. 3 What, then, can be his solace but what You are offering to his bewildered mind
17   and frightened heart, to give him certainty and bring him peace? 4 Today I would behold
18   my brother sinless. 5 This Your Will for me, for so will I behold my sinlessness.>
19   
20   
21   
22   LESSON 335.
23   
24   I choose to see my brother's sinlessness.
25   W-pII.335.1. Forgiveness is a choice. 2 I never see my brother as he is, for that is 
26   far beyond perception. 3 What I see in him is merely what I wish to see, because it stands
27   for what I want to be the truth. 4 It is to this alone that I respond, however much I 
28   seem to be impelled by outside happenings. 5 I choose to see what I would look upon, and 
29   this I see, and only this. 6 My brother's sinlessness shows me that I would look upon my 
30   own. 7 And I will see it, having chosen to behold my brother in its holy light.
31   
32   W-pII.335.2.  <What could restore Your memory to me, except to see my brother's 
33   sinlessness? 2 His holiness reminds me that he was created one with me, and like myself. 3 In him 
34   I find my Self, and in Your Son I find the memory of You as well.>
35   
36   
37   
38   LESSON 336.
39   
40   Forgiveness lets me know that minds are joined.
41   W-pII.336.1. Forgiveness is the means appointed for perception's ending. 2 Knowledge is
42   restored after perception first is changed, and then gives way entirely to what remains
43   forever past its highest reach. 3 For sights and sounds, at best, can serve but to 
44   recall the memory that lies beyond them all. 4 Forgiveness sweeps away distortions, and opens
45   the hidden altar to the truth. 5 Its lilies shine into the mind, and call it to return 
46   and look within, to find what it has vainly sought without. 6 For here, and only here, is 
47   peace of mind restored, for this the dwelling place of God Himself.
48   
49   W-pII.336.2.  <In quiet may forgiveness wipe away my dreams of separation and of sin. 2
50   Then let me, Father, look within, and find Your promise of my sinlessness is kept; Your
0661
 1   Word remains unchanged within my mind, Your Love is still abiding in my heart.>
 2   
 3   
 4   
 5   LESSON 337.
 6   
 7   My sinlessness protects me from all harm.
 8   W-pII.337.1. My sinlessness ensures me perfect peace, eternal safety, everlasting love,
 9   freedom forever from all thought of loss; complete deliverance from suffering. 2 And 
10   only happiness can be my state, for only happiness is given me. 3 What must I do to know 
11   all this is mine? 4 I must accept Atonement for myself, and nothing more. 5 God has 
12   already done all things that need be done. 6 And I must learn I need do nothing of myself, for
13   I need but accept my Self, my sinlessness, created for me, now already mine, to feel 
14   God's Love protecting me from harm, to understand my Father loves His Son; to know I am the 
15   Son my Father loves.
16   
17   W-pII.337.2.  <You Who created me in sinlessness are not mistaken about what I am. 2 I 
18   was mistaken when I thought I sinned, but I accept Atonement for myself. 3 Father, my 
19   dream is ended now. 4 Amen.>
20   
21   
22   
23   LESSON 338.
24   
25   I am affected only by my thoughts.
26   W-pII.338.1. It needs but this to let salvation come to all the world. 2 For in this 
27   single thought is everyone released at last from fear. 3 Now has he learned that no one 
28   frightens him, and nothing can endanger him. 4 He has no enemies, and he is safe from all 
29   external things. 5 His thoughts can frighten him, but since these thoughts belong to him alone,
30   he has the power to change them and exchange each fear thought for a happy thought of 
31   love. 6 He crucified himself. 7 Yet God has planned that His beloved Son will be redeemed.
32   
33   W-pII.338.2.  <Your plan is sure, my Father,--only Yours. 2 All other plans will fail. 
34   3 And I will have thoughts that will frighten me, until I learn that You have given me 
35   the only Thought that leads me to salvation. 4 Mine alone will fail, and lead me nowhere. 
36   5 But the Thought You gave me promises to lead me home, because it holds Your promise to
37   Your Son.>
38   
39   
40   
41   LESSON 339.
42   
43   I will receive whatever I request.
44   W-pII.339.1. No one desires pain. 2 But he can think that pain is pleasure. 3 No one 
45   would avoid his happiness. 4 But he can think that joy is painful, threatening and dangerous.
46    5 Everyone will receive what he requests. 6 But he can be confused indeed about the 
47   things he wants; the state he would attain. 7 What can he then request that he would want 
48   when he receives it? 8 He has asked for what will frighten him, and bring him suffering. 9 
49   Let us resolve today to ask for what we really want, and only this, that we may spend this
50   day in fearlessness, without confusing pain with joy, or fear with love.
0662
 1   
 2   W-pII.339.2.  <Father, this is Your day. 2 It is a day in which I would do nothing by 
 3   myself, but hear Your Voice in everything I do; requesting only what You offer me, accepting 
 4   only Thoughts You share with me.>
