 8   LESSON 340.
 9   
10   I can be free of suffering today.
11   W-pII.340.1.  <Father, I thank You for today, and for the freedom I am certain it will 
12   bring. 2 This day is holy, for today Your Son will be redeemed. 3 His suffering is done. 4 
13   For he will hear Your Voice directing him to find Christ's vision through forgiveness, and
14   be free forever from all suffering. 5 Thanks for today, my Father. 6 I was born into 
15   this world but to achieve this day, and what it holds in joy and freedom for Your holy Son 
16   and for the world he made, which is released along with him today.>
17   
18   W-pII.340.2. Be glad today! 2 Be glad! 3 There is no room for anything but joy and 
19   thanks today. 4 Our Father has redeemed His Son this day. 5 Not one of us but will be saved 
20   today. 6 Not one who will remain in fear, and none the Father will not gather to Himself, 
21   awake in Heaven in the Heart of Love.
22   
23   
24   13. What Is a Miracle?
25   W-pII.13.1. A miracle is a correction. 2 It does not create, nor really change at all. 
26   3 It merely looks on devastation, and reminds the mind that what it sees is false. 4 It 
27   undoes error, but does not attempt to go beyond perception, nor exceed the function of 
28   forgiveness. 5 Thus it stays within time's limits. 6 Yet it paves the way for the return of 
29   timelessness and love's awakening, for fear must slip away under the gentle remedy it brings.
30   W-pII.13.2. A miracle contains the gift of grace, for it is given and received as one. 
31   2 And thus it illustrates the law of truth the world does not obey, because it fails 
32   entirely to understand its ways. 3 A miracle inverts perception which was upside down before, 
33   and thus it ends the strange distortions that were manifest. 4 Now is perception open to 
34   the truth. 5 Now is forgiveness seen as justified.
35   W-pII.13.3. Forgiveness is the home of miracles. 2 The eyes of Christ deliver them to 
36   all they look upon in mercy and in love. 3 Perception stands corrected in His sight, and 
37   what was meant to curse has come to bless. 4 Each lily of forgiveness offers all the world 
38   the silent miracle of love. 5 And each is laid before the Word of God, upon the universal 
39   altar to Creator and creation in the light of perfect purity and endless joy.
40   W-pII.13.4. The miracle is taken first on faith, because to ask for it implies the mind
41   has been made ready to conceive of what it cannot see and does not understand. 2 Yet 
42   faith will bring its witnesses to show that what it rested on is really there. 3 And thus 
43   the miracle will justify your faith in it, and show it rested on a world more real than 
44   what you saw before; a world redeemed from what you thought was there.
45   W-pII.13.5. Miracles fall like drops of healing rain from Heaven on a dry and dusty 
46   world, where starved and thirsty creatures come to die. 2 Now they have water. 3 Now the 
47   world is green. 4 And everywhere the signs of life spring up, to show that what is born can 
48   never die, for what has life has immortality.
49   
50   
0663
 1   
 2   LESSON 341.
 3   
 4   I can attack but my own sinlessness, 
 5   And it is only that which keeps me safe.
 6   W-pII.341.1.  <Father, Your Son is holy. 2 I am he on whom You smile in love and 
 7   tenderness so dear and deep and still the universe smiles back on You, and shares Your Holiness. 
 8   3 How pure, how safe, how holy, then, are we, abiding in Your Smile, with all Your Love 
 9   bestowed upon us, living one with You, in brotherhood and Fatherhood complete; in sinlessness 
10   so perfect that the Lord of Sinlessness conceives us as His Son, a universe of Thought 
11   completing Him.>
12   
13   W-pII.341.2. Let us not, then, attack our sinlessness, for it contains the Word of God 
14   to us. 2 And in its kind reflection we are saved.
15   
