18   LESSON 342.
19   
20   I let forgiveness rest upon all things, 
21   For thus forgiveness will be given me.
22   W-pII.342.1.  <I thank You, Father, for Your plan to save me from the hell I made. 2 It
23   is not real. 3 And You have given me the means to prove its unreality to me. 4 The key 
24   is in my hand, and I have reached the door beyond which lies the end of dreams. 5 I stand
25   before the gate of Heaven, wondering if I should enter in and be at home. 6 Let me not 
26   wait again today. 7 Let me forgive all things, and let creation be as You would have it be 
27   and as it is. 8 Let me remember that I am Your Son, and opening the door at last, forget 
28   illusions in the blazing light of truth, as memory of You returns to me.>
29   
30   W-pII.342.2. Brother, forgive me now. 2 I come to you to take you home with me. 3 And 
31   as we go, the world goes with us on our way to God.
