0664
 1   
 2   
 3   LESSON 344.
 4   
 5   Today I learn the law of love; that what 
 6   I give my brother is my gift to me.
 7   W-pII.344.1.  <This is Your law, my Father, not my own. 2 I have not understood what 
 8   giving means, and thought to save what I desired for myself alone. 3 And as I looked upon the
 9   treasure that I thought I had, I found an empty place where nothing ever was or is or 
10   will be. 4 Who can share a dream? 5 And what can an illusion offer me? 6 Yet he whom I 
11   forgive will give me gifts beyond the worth of anything on earth. 7 Let my forgiven brothers 
12   fill my store with Heaven's treasures, which alone are real. 8 Thus is the law of love 
13   fulfilled. 9 And thus Your Son arises and returns to You.>
14   
15   W-pII.344.2. How near we are to one another, as we go to God. 2 How near is He to us. 3
16   How close the ending of the dream of sin, and the redemption of the Son of God.
