20   LESSON 345.
21   
22   I offer only miracles today, 
23   For I would have them be returned to me.
24   W-pII.345.1.  <Father, a miracle reflects Your gifts to me, Your Son. 2 And every one I
25   give returns to me, reminding me the law of love is universal. 3 Even here, it takes a 
26   form which can be recognized and seen to work. 4 The miracles I give are given back in just
27   the form I need to help me with the problems I perceive. 5 Father, in Heaven it is 
28   different, for there, there are no needs. 6 But here on earth, the miracle is closer to Your 
29   gifts than any other gift that I can give. 7 Then let me give this gift alone today, which, 
30   born of true forgiveness, lights the way that I must travel to remember You.>
31   
32   W-pII.345.2. Peace to all seeking hearts today. 2 The light has come to offer miracles 
33   to bless the tired world. 3 It will find rest today, for we will offer what we have 
34   received.
