38   LESSON 346.
39   
40   Today the peace of God envelops me, 
41   And I forget all things except His Love.
42   W-pII.346.1.  <Father, I wake today with miracles correcting my perception of all 
43   things. 2 And so begins the day I share with You as I will share eternity, for time has 
44   stepped aside today. 3 I do not seek the things of time, and so I will not look upon them. 4 
45   What I seek today transcends all laws of time and things perceived in time. 5 I would 
46   forget all things except Your Love. 6 I would abide in You, and know no laws except Your law 
47   of love. 7 And I would find the peace which You created for Your Son, forgetting all the 
48   foolish toys I made as I behold Your glory and my own.>
49   
50   W-pII.346.2. And when the evening comes today, we will remember nothing but the peace 
0665
 1   of God. 2 For we will learn today what peace is ours, when we forget all things except 
 2   God's Love.
