 6   LESSON 347.
 7   
 8   Anger must come from judgment. Judgment is 
 9   The weapon I would use against myself, 
10   To keep the miracle away from me.
11   W-pII.347.1.  <Father, I want what goes against my will, and do not want what is my 
12   will to have. 2 Straighten my mind, my Father. 3 It is sick. 4 But You have offered freedom,
13    and I choose to claim Your gift today. 5 And so I give all judgment to the One You 
14   gave to me to judge for me. 6 He sees what I behold, and yet He knows the truth. 7 He looks
15   on pain, and yet He understands it is not real, and in His understanding it is healed. 
16   8 He gives the miracles my dreams would hide from my awareness. 9 Let Him judge today. 
17   10 I do not know my will, but He is sure it is Your Own. 11 And He will speak for me, and
18   call Your miracles to come to me.>
19   
20   W-pII.347.2. Listen today. 2 Be very still, and hear the gentle Voice for God assuring 
21   you that He has judged you as the Son He loves.
