26   
27   I have no cause for anger or for fear, 
28   For You surround me. And in every need 
29   That I perceive, Your grace suffices me.
30   W-pII.348.1.  <Father, let me remember You are here, and I am not alone. 2 Surrounding 
31   me is everlasting Love. 3 I have no cause for anything except the perfect peace and joy I
32   share with You. 4 What need have I for anger or for fear? 5 Surrounding me is perfect 
33   safety. 6 Can I be afraid, when Your eternal promise goes with me? 7 Surrounding me is 
34   perfect sinlessness. 8 What can I fear, when You created me in holiness as perfect as Your Own?
35   >
