 9   LESSON 350.
10   
11   Miracles mirror God's eternal Love. 
12   To offer them is to remember Him, 
13   And through His memory to save the world.
14   W-pII.350.1.  <What we forgive becomes a part of us, as we perceive ourselves. 2 The 
15   Son of God incorporates all things within himself as You created him. 3 Your memory 
16   depends on his forgiveness. 4 What he is, is unaffected by his thoughts. 5 But what he looks 
17   upon is their direct result. 6 Therefore, my Father, I would turn to You. 7 Only Your 
18   memory will set me free. 8 And only my forgiveness teaches me to let Your memory return to me,
19    and give it to the world in thankfulness.>
20   
21   W-pII.350.2. And as we gather miracles from Him, we will indeed be grateful. 2 For as 
22   we remember Him, His Son will be restored to us in the reality of Love.
