25   14. What Am I?
26   W-pII.14.1.  <I am God's Son, complete and healed and whole, shining in the reflection 
27   of His Love. 2 In me is His creation sanctified and guaranteed eternal life. 3 In me is 
28   love perfected, fear impossible, and joy established without opposite. 4 I am the holy home
29   of God Himself. 5 I am the Heaven where His Love resides. 6 I am His holy Sinlessness 
30   Itself, for in my purity abides His Own.>
31   
32   W-pII.14.2. Our use for words is almost over now. 2 Yet in the final days of this one 
33   year we gave to God together, you and I, we found a single purpose that we shared. 3 And 
34   thus you joined with me, so what I am are you as well. 4 The truth of what we are is not 
35   for words to speak of nor describe. 5 Yet we can realize our function here, and words can 
36   speak of this and teach it, too, if we exemplify the words in us.
37   W-pII.14.3. We are the bringers of salvation. 2 We accept our part as saviors of the 
38   world, which through our joint forgiveness is redeemed. 3 And this, our gift, is therefore 
39   given us. 4 We look on everyone as brother, and perceive all things as kindly and as good. 5
40   We do not seek a function that is past the gate of Heaven. 6 Knowledge will return when
41   we have done our part. 7 We are concerned only with giving welcome to the truth.
42   W-pII.14.4. Ours are the eyes through which Christ's vision sees a world redeemed from 
43   every thought of sin. 2 Ours are the ears that hear the Voice for God proclaim the world as 
44   sinless. 3 Ours the minds that join together as we bless the world. 4 And from the oneness 
45   that we have attained we call to all our brothers, asking them to share our peace and 
46   consummate our joy.
47   W-pII.14.5. We are the holy messengers of God who speak for Him, and carrying His Word 
48   to everyone whom He has sent to us, we learn that it is written on our hearts. 2 And thus
49   our minds are changed about the aim for which we came, and which we seek to serve. 3 We
50   bring glad tidings to the Son of God, who thought he suffered. 4 Now is he redeemed. 5 
0667
 1   And as he sees the gate of Heaven stand open before him, he will enter in and disappear 
 2   into the Heart of God.
 3   
 4   
 5   
 6   LESSON 351.
 7   
 8   My sinless brother is my guide to peace. 
 9   My sinful brother is my guide to pain. 
10   And which I choose to see I will behold.
11   W-pII.351.1.  <Who is my brother but Your holy Son? 2 And if I see him sinful I 
12   proclaim myself a sinner, not a Son of God; alone and friendless in a fearful world. 3 Yet this
13   perception is a choice I make, and can relinquish. 4 I can also see my brother sinless,
14   as Your holy Son. 5 And with this choice I see my sinlessness, my everlasting Comforter
15   and Friend beside me, and my way secure and clear. 6 Choose, then, for me, my Father, 
16   through Your Voice. 7 For He alone gives judgment in Your Name.>
17   
18   
19   
20   LESSON 352.
21   
22   Judgment and love are opposites. From one 
23   Come all the sorrows of the world. But from 
24   The other comes the peace of God Himself.
25   W-pII.352.1.  <Forgiveness looks on sinlessness alone, and judges not. 2 Through this I
26   come to You. 3 Judgment will bind my eyes and make me blind. 4 Yet love, reflected in 
27   forgiveness here, reminds me You have given me a way to find Your peace again. 5 I am redeemed 
28   when I elect to follow in this way. 6 You have not left me comfortless. 7 I have within me 
29   both the memory of You, and One Who leads me to it. 8 Father, I would hear Your Voice and 
30   find Your peace today. 9 For I would love my own Identity, and find in It the memory of You.
31   >
32   
33   
34   
35   LESSON 353.
36   
37   My eyes, my tongue, my hands, my feet today 
38   Have but one purpose; to be given Christ 
39   To use to bless the world with miracles.
40   W-pII.353.1.  <Father, I give all that is mine today to Christ, to use in any way that 
41   best will serve the purpose that I share with Him. 2 Nothing is mine alone, for He and I 
42   have joined in purpose. 3 Thus has learning come almost to its appointed end. 4 A while I 
43   work with Him to serve His purpose. 5 Then I lose myself in my Identity, and recognize that
44   Christ is but my Self.>
