38   
39   LESSON 357.
40   
41   Truth answers every call we make to God, 
42   Responding first with miracles, and then 
43   Returning unto us to be itself.
44   W-pII.357.1.  <Forgiveness, truth's reflection, tells me how to offer miracles, and 
45   thus escape the prison house in which I think I live. 2 Your holy Son is pointed out to me,
46   first in my brother; then in me. 3 Your Voice instructs me patiently to hear Your Word,
47   and give as I receive. 4 And as I look upon Your Son today, I hear Your Voice 
48   instructing me to find the way to You, as You appointed that the way shall be: 5 "Behold his 
49   sinlessness, and be you healed.>"
