0669
 1   
 2   
 3   LESSON 358.
 4   
 5   No call to God can be unheard nor left 
 6   Unanswered. And of this I can be sure; 
 7   His answer is the one I really want.
 8   W-pII.358.1.  <You Who remember what I really am alone remember what I really want. 2 
 9   You speak for God, and so You speak for me. 3 And what You give me comes from God Himself.
10   4 Your Voice, my Father, then is mine as well, and all I want is what You offer me, in 
11   just the form You choose that it be mine. 5 Let me remember all I do not know, and let my 
12   voice be still, remembering. 6 But let me not forget Your Love and care, keeping Your 
13   promise to Your Son in my awareness always. 7 Let me not forget myself is nothing, but my Self
14   is all.>
15   
