17   
18   LESSON 359.
19   
20   God's answer is some form of peace. All pain 
21   Is healed; all misery replaced with joy. 
22   All prison doors are opened. And all sin 
23   Is understood as merely a mistake.
24   W-pII.359.1.  <Father, today we will forgive Your world, and let creation be Your Own. 
25   2 We have misunderstood all things. 3 But we have not made sinners of the holy Sons of 
26   God. 4 What You created sinless so abides forever and forever. 5 Such are we. 6 And we 
27   rejoice to learn that we have made mistakes which have no real effects on us. 7 Sin is 
28   impossible, and on this fact forgiveness rests upon a certain base more solid than the shadow 
29   world we see. 8 Help us forgive, for we would be redeemed. 9 Help us forgive, for we would 
30   be at peace.>
31   
32   
33   
34   LESSON 360.
35   
36   Peace be to me, the holy Son of God. 
37   Peace to my brother, who is one with me. 
38   Let all the world be blessed with peace through us.
39   W-pII.360.1.  <Father, it is Your peace that I would give, receiving it of You. 2 I am 
40   Your Son, forever just as You created me, for the Great Rays remain forever still and 
41   undisturbed within me. 3 I would reach to them in silence and in certainty, for nowhere else can 
42   certainty be found. 4 Peace be to me, and peace to all the world. 5 In holiness were we created,
43   and in holiness do we remain. 6 Your Son is like to You in perfect sinlessness. 7 And 
44   with this thought we gladly say "Amen.">
