48   FINAL LESSONS.
49   
50   Introduction
0670
 1   W.fl.in.1. Our final lessons will be left as free of words as possible. 2 We use them 
 2   but at the beginning of our practicing, and only to remind us that we seek to go beyond 
 3   them. 3 Let us turn to Him Who leads the way and makes our footsteps sure. 4 To Him we 
 4   leave these lessons, as to Him we give our lives henceforth. 5 For we would not return again
 5   to the belief in sin that made the world seem ugly and unsafe, attacking and destroying,
 6    dangerous in all its ways, and treacherous beyond the hope of trust and the escape 
 7   from pain.
 8   W.fl.in.2. His is the only way to find the peace that God has given us. 2 It is His way
 9   that everyone must travel in the end, because it is this ending God Himself appointed. 
10   3 In the dream of time it seems to be far off. 4 And yet, in truth, it is already here; 
11   already serving us as gracious guidance in the way to go. 5 Let us together follow in the way 
12   that truth points out to us. 6 And let us be the leaders of our many brothers who are 
13   seeking for the way, but find it not.
14   W.fl.in.3. And to this purpose let us dedicate our minds, directing all our thoughts to
15   serve the function of salvation. 2 Unto us the aim is given to forgive the world. 3 It 
16   is the goal that God has given us. 4 It is His ending to the dream we seek, and not our 
17   own. 5 For all that we forgive we will not fail to recognize as part of God Himself. 6 And
18   thus His memory is given back, completely and complete.
19   W.fl.in.4. It is our function to remember Him on earth, as it is given us to be His Own
20   completion in reality. 2 So let us not forget our goal is shared, for it is that 
21   remembrance which contains the memory of God, and points the way to Him and to the Heaven of His 
22   peace. 3 And shall we not forgive our brother, who can offer this to us? 4 He is the way, 
23   the truth and life that shows the way to us. 5 In him resides salvation, offered us 
24   through our forgiveness, given unto him.
25   W.fl.in.5. We will not end this year without the gift our Father promised to His holy 
26   Son. 2 We are forgiven now. 3 And we are saved from all the wrath we thought belonged to 
27   God, and found it was a dream. 4 We are restored to sanity, in which we understand that 
28   anger is insane, attack is mad, and vengeance merely foolish fantasy. 5 We have been saved 
29   from wrath because we learned we were mistaken. 6 Nothing more than that. 7 And is a father
30   angry at his son because he failed to understand the truth?
31   W.fl.in.6. We come in honesty to God and say we did not understand, and ask Him to help
32   us to learn His lessons, through the Voice of His Own Teacher. 2 Would He hurt His Son?
33   3 Or would He rush to answer him, and say, "This is My Son, and all I have is his"? 4 
34   Be certain He will answer thus, for these are His Own words to you. 5 And more than that 
35   can no one ever have, for in these words is all there is, and all that there will be 
36   throughout all time and in eternity.
37   
38   
39   
40   LESSONS 361 to 365.
41   
42   This holy instant would I give to You. 
43   Be You in charge. For I would follow You, 
44   Certain that Your direction gives me peace.
45   W-pII.361-5.1. And if I need a word to help me, He will give it to me. 2 If I need a 
46   thought, that will He also give. 3 And if I need but stillness and a tranquil, open mind, 
47   these are the gifts I will receive of Him. 4 He is in charge by my request. 5 And He will 
48   hear and answer me, because He speaks for God my Father and His holy Son.
49   
50   
0671
 1   
 2   EPILOGUE
 3   
 4   W.ep.1. This course is a beginning, not an end. 2 Your Friend goes with you. 3 You are 
 5   not alone. 4 No one who calls on Him can call in vain. 5 Whatever troubles you, be certain
 6   that He has the answer, and will gladly give it to you, if you simply turn to Him and 
 7   ask it of Him. 6 He will not withhold all answers that you need for anything that seems to
 8   trouble you. 7 He knows the way to solve all problems, and resolve all doubts. 8 His 
 9   certainty is yours. 9 You need but ask it of Him, and it will be given you.
10   W.ep.2. You are as certain of arriving home as is the pathway of the sun laid down 
11   before it rises, after it has set, and in the half-lit hours in between. 2 Indeed, your 
12   pathway is more certain still. 3 For it can not be possible to change the course of those whom
13   God has called to Him. 4 Therefore obey your will, and follow Him Whom you accepted as 
14   your voice, to speak of what you really want and really need. 5 His is the Voice for God 
15   and also yours. 6 And thus He speaks of freedom and of truth.
16   W.ep.3. No more specific lessons are assigned, for there is no more need of them. 2 
17   Henceforth, hear but the Voice for God and for your Self when you retire from the world, to seek 
18   reality instead. 3 He will direct your efforts, telling you exactly what to do, how to direct 
19   your mind, and when to come to Him in silence, asking for His sure direction and His 
20   certain Word. 4 His is the Word that God has given you. 5 His is the Word you chose to be your
21   own.
22   W.ep.4. And now I place you in His hands, to be His faithful follower, with Him as 
23   Guide through every difficulty and all pain that you may think is real. 2 Nor will He give 
24   you pleasures that will pass away, for He gives only the eternal and the good. 3 Let Him 
25   prepare you further. 4 He has earned your trust by speaking daily to you of your Father and 
26   your brother and your Self. 5 He will continue. 6 Now you walk with Him, as certain as is 
27   He of where you go; as sure as He of how you should proceed; as confident as He is of the
28   goal, and of your safe arrival in the end.
29   W.ep.5. The end is certain, and the means as well. 2 To this we say "Amen." 3 You will 
30   be told exactly what God wills for you each time there is a choice to make. 4 And He will
31   speak for God and for your Self, thus making sure that hell will claim you not, and 
32   that each choice you make brings Heaven nearer to your reach. 5 And so we walk with Him 
33   from this time on, and turn to Him for guidance and for peace and sure direction. 6 Joy 
34   attends our way. 7 For we go homeward to an open door which God has held unclosed to welcome 
35   us.
36   W.ep.6. We trust our ways to Him and say "Amen." 2 In peace we will continue in His way,
37    and trust all things to Him. 3 In confidence we wait His answers, as we ask His Will 
38   in everything we do. 4 He loves God's Son as we would love him. 5 And He teaches us how 
39   to behold him through His eyes, and love him as He does. 6 You do not walk alone. 7 God's
40   angels hover near and all about. 8 His Love surrounds you, and of this be sure; that I 
41   will never leave you comfortless.